INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1, 63, '1.  Creating a Brief', '1', 'ee222e2', '<p>Some incredible works of copywriting can fall victim to simple grammatical errors, inconsistent spelling and awkward phrasing that disrupts the tone of your writing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you want to know five effective ways to prevent this from happening to your work, saving your craftsmanship from taints such as repetitive words and spelling mistakes? Read on to learn how to protect your projects!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>1. Creating a Brief</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Every well-executed piece of copywriting starts with a solid brief that will guide you to the very last word. Want to impress your clients, bring onboard new companies and create a strong rapport with those you work with?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The best way to begin your expansion is to exhibit the planning and organisation skills that a well-constructed brief presents.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We understand that the world of working in copywriting is challenging at the minute, and your workload may be drying up. Still, time spent developing your skills in proofreading will do nothing but better your quality of work and prepare you for your future success!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So how do you create or read a brief?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be trusted to write as you please for client work, or you may be writing for your platform on LinkedIn, for example.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No matter the case, there are some critical parts to a brief. A detailed overview, a specific target audience, the key message you wish to deliver, the tone and style of your piece, and project deliverables all work together to form your foundation to write.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How will this help you catch errors in proofreading?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading can become a difficult task if you are not informed about what corrections you are looking for, and understanding your well-versed brief created by you or your client will help you to catch those errors like a pro!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The clear guidelines and expectations of your finished piece will aid you in catching those off-brand sentences and phrases that just don&rsquo;t quite fit the brief, making your work concise and well-crafted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nobody likes waffle!</p>', '2023-04-18 07:47:07', '2023-04-18 07:47:07'),
(2, 63, '2. Following the Formatting', '1', '1-creating-a-brief', '<h2>2. Following the Formatting</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Following your brief&#39;s formatting is a great way to catch errors within your work and can help reach your target audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As copywriters, we can alter our voice and choose to speak to our readers in whatever <a href=\"https://demo91.co.in/dev/affiliatecontent/public/blog/ultimate-guide-to-tone-of-voice-examples\">tone and style</a> necessary -&nbsp; it&rsquo;s what makes us good at our job!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether your formatting requires a tone of the utmost urgency, a caring and friendly hand to lend or an abundance of knowledge to enlighten the reader, you can do it all.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading your writing with tone in mind can change a simple sentence such as &ldquo;sign up today&rdquo; into a gripping call to action. For example, how does this sound?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Have we caught your attention? Join our copywriting community today and continue flourishing and growing in your craft!&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Editing tone and style like this is easy. Just make sure you proofread with it in mind!</p>', '2023-04-18 07:42:17', '2023-04-18 07:42:17'),
(3, 63, '3.  Proofreading with a Fresh Pair of Eyes', '1', '3-proofreading-with-a-fresh-pair-of-eyes', '<h2>3. Proofreading with a Fresh Pair of Eyes</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ve all heard the saying &lsquo;read it with a fresh pair of eyes&rsquo;, but what does that really mean?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Writing can become almost robotic when you do it daily, and we&rsquo;ve all had moments when the words are almost moving around the screen, trying to escape your gaze.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sometimes taking a moment, and revisiting that article, blog post or social media advert after a break can be the best thing for its quality. Proofreading after a short break for a cup of tea or leaving it till later in the day is sometimes all it takes for those errors to jump out at you, we promise!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you return to your writing, try to read aloud. We know it may feel silly at first, but presenting your content to a non-existent crowd (almost like performing a speech) is a fantastic way to help you test out sentence structure and ensure your work has a perfect flow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maybe even read to your dog! Anything that aids in your ability to proofread will be worth the results.</p>', '2023-04-18 08:01:33', '2023-04-18 08:01:33'),
(4, 63, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact', '<h2><strong>Key Fact</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>According to Recruiter.com and its research surrounding employment,&nbsp;the need for proofreaders is expected to rise by 2029, with 3510 new jobs forecast to appear!</p>', '2023-05-08 07:43:26', '2023-05-08 07:43:26'),
(5, 63, '4.  Tools to Help You Proofread', '1', '4-tools-to-help-you-proofread', '<h2>4. Tools to Help You Proofread</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Some great tools out there will help you create a perfect copy, one of the most popular and known being Grammarly.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This tool will help you improve conciseness, fix tonal issues, and suggest different words and phrasing to optimise your writing. This is a must-have tool for proofreading those important texts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An upgrade from Google Docs and its &lsquo;spelling and grammar&rsquo; check for definite.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another brilliant tool that is sure to bump up your copywriting is <a href=\"https://demo91.co.in/dev/affiliatecontent/public/tool/surfer-seo\">Surfer SEO</a>. Their AI technology is great for those last-minute checks and integrating better keyword data.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Separate your writing from the crowd by proofreading on Surfer SEO and getting some brilliant suggestions based on Google search data, helping you get your work out into the world!</p>', '2023-04-18 08:05:37', '2023-04-18 08:05:37'),
(6, 63, '5.  Clarity and Consistency', '1', '5-clarity-and-consistency', '<h2>5. Clarity and Consistency</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating clear and consistent copy is the key to copywriting success, so proofreading with these objectives in mind is the best way to pick out errors in inconsistent capitalisation and punctuation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From using the wrong &lsquo;your&rsquo; to double-check that you&rsquo;re using one form of apostrophe&hellip; you&rsquo;ll be surprised how often you trip up and use both &lsquo; and &#39; without knowing it!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Why is inconsistency so bad for your writing?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is the art of creating content that persuades your reader to take a desired action, such as purchasing a product or signing up for a service. Inconsistency will deprive your work of credibility, and the brand it represents may be labelled as unreliable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To the blind eye, mistakes like this can be difficult to spot.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Doing something as simple as proofreading with <a href=\"https://demo91.co.in/dev/affiliatecontent/public/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly</a> will remove this worry by thoroughly cleaning your content until it&#39;s squeaky clean!</p>', '2023-04-18 08:06:40', '2023-04-18 08:06:40'),
(7, 63, 'Frequently Asked Questions', '1', 'frequently-asked-questions', '<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>What are some Important Things to Look for When Proofreading Work?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When proofreading, try to look out for sentence fragments, run-on sentences, and commonly confused words. Errors may slip through the net if you&rsquo;re not proofreading with full concentration!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What are 4 Proofreading Tips?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Four tips when proofreading your writing are to read your work aloud, print out a copy so that you are reading it from a different angle, check the spellings of proper nouns and take a break if copywriting for long stints.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How does Proofreading Improve the Quality of Copywriting?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading your copy ensures that you provide the best quality of work possible. Proofreading will provide clarity and conciseness in your work by fixing grammatical errors, technical linguistic issues and misused punctuation.</p>', '2023-04-19 03:27:05', '2023-04-19 03:27:05'),
(8, 63, 'About Us', '1', 'about-us', '<h2>About Us</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Enjoyed reading about these helpful tips on proofreading? We&rsquo;ve got more where that came from! Optimise your writing and take your copywriting career to the next level today with the help of our experts at <a href=\"https://demo91.co.in/dev/affiliatecontent/public/\">The Author&rsquo;s Pad</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Become a part of the community we are building.</strong></p>', '2023-04-18 08:08:07', '2023-04-18 08:08:07'),
(9, 66, 'How to Use Copywriting Skills to Improve Your Resume', '1', 'how-to-use-copywriting-skills-to-improve-your-resume', '<p>Whether you&rsquo;re writing an email to pitch your services or a resume to apply for a job, copywriters can use their skills to improve what they produce. Many copywriting skills are applicable across various platforms, and you should use them to boost your career chances.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Discover the importance of using your copywriting skills to improve your resume.</p>', '2023-04-18 09:48:38', '2023-04-18 09:48:38'),
(10, 66, 'What does a copywriter do on a resume?', '1', 'what-does-a-copywriter-do-on-a-resume-2', '<h2>What does a copywriter do on a resume?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A copywriter uses their resume to sell their talents and provide a history of their relevant work experiences. The resume is only half of a copywriter&rsquo;s application. Copywriters also submit portfolios of their work so hiring managers can see their abilities in action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are some steps to maximise your copywriting abilities when creating your resume.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Use keywords</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Most businesses use Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS) to make hiring more efficient. For candidates, the ATS will automatically screen your resume and either send it to a hiring manager or eliminate it from the process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Just as you would use keywords to boost the SEO of an article, you need to use the appropriate keywords to ensure your application makes it through the initial vetting stage. Most businesses looking for a copywriter will have some combination of these keywords in their ATS:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Writing</li>\r\n	<li>Search Engine Optimisation (SEO)</li>\r\n	<li>Keyword research</li>\r\n	<li>WordPress / Microsoft Word&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Creative</li>\r\n	<li>Editing</li>\r\n	<li>Style guides</li>\r\n	<li>Open-minded</li>\r\n	<li>Marketing</li>\r\n	<li>Independent</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Start your resume with a summary of your professional identity and include these keywords to appease the ATS and get to the human hiring stage. The section of your resume dedicated to your skills is also an excellent opportunity to use more of these important keywords.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color:#212529; font-style:normal\">Highlight skills</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You can highlight your relevant skills in your resume&rsquo;s introductory summary and the &lsquo;Skills&rsquo; section. The summary is an excellent place to write about your in-depth knowledge of programs like <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/wordpress\">WordPress</a> and<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\"> Grammarly</a>. You can also reference your understanding of the importance of SEO and keyword research in this section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The &lsquo;Skills&rsquo; portion of your resume should be single words that describe your abilities without further context. Keywords in this section can relate more to your personal attributes than industry-specific terms. Highlight that you are open-minded, creative, and detail-oriented.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color:#212529; font-style:normal\">Customise applications&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Customising your application to the role might sound obvious, but hiring managers dismiss many resumes for being too vague. Using the company&rsquo;s name and the position you&rsquo;re interested in shows the hiring manager that you are a serious candidate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is a vast field. You can specialise in almost any subject, so ensure your resume is specific to the job. Some businesses need technical writers who can produce compelling copy for industries like engineering, medicine, and finance. Other companies, however, are looking for writers who can research and investigate a range of topics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You might be a great copywriter who can excel in both types of content creation. Hiring managers only want to know about your suitability for the role they offer. Highlight skills that are most relevant to the job.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color:#212529; font-style:normal\">Reference portfolios</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Resumes are one component of a copywriter&rsquo;s job application, while portfolios comprise the other half. Your portfolio demonstrates that you can produce high-quality, compelling content that fits your client&rsquo;s brief. Hiring managers want proof that you can deliver on the skills and experience you mention in your resume.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many copywriting roles will ask for a portfolio when you apply, but you should provide it whether or not they ask. If you have an online portfolio, attach a link to your resume so the hiring manager can access your past samples immediately.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Experienced copywriters might have multiple portfolios or pages to keep their work organised by industry or style. If you have a range of portfolios to show, only send the one most relevant to the job. Hiring managers spend lots of time sorting through applications, so making it as quick and easy as possible is essential.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"color:#212529; font-style:normal\">Proofread thoroughly</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Lastly, proofread your resume. This step also sounds obvious, but we all know how easily a typo can slip through the cracks. If you&rsquo;re sending out various applications customised to their businesses and roles, it&rsquo;s even easier to make a mistake.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading is a core skill for copywriters. If you send a resume that proudly boasts your detail-oriented work but is filled with errors and typos, it won&rsquo;t look good. It&rsquo;s well worth reading your resume a second and third time to ensure you&rsquo;re putting your best foot forward.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:37:55', '2023-04-19 08:37:55'),
(16, 66, 'How do I add freelance copywriting to my resume?', '1', 'how-do-i-add-freelance-copywriting-to-my-resume', '<h2>How do I add freelance copywriting to my resume?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Freelancers use their resumes more than most professionals. Rather than applying for jobs every few years, they consistently reach out to new clients and seek opportunities depending on how and when they want to work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A freelance copywriter&rsquo;s resume mostly resembles a full-time copywriter&rsquo;s. However, freelancers can include their rates in their resumes or portfolio. Streamlining the hiring process like this is more efficient for candidates and hiring managers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can add freelance projects to your resume under the &lsquo;Experience&rsquo; heading. It&rsquo;s also good for freelancers to highlight their portfolios to hiring managers to understand their client history better. Instead of referees, freelance copywriters might also have a section of testimonials on their portfolio that hiring teams can reference.</p>', '2023-04-18 09:51:12', '2023-04-18 09:51:12'),
(17, 66, 'Does freelancing look good on a resume?', '1', 'does-freelancing-look-good-on-a-resume', '<h2>Does freelancing look good on a resume?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Freelancing definitely looks good on a resume. If you have a gap in your full-time employment where you have freelanced, including this information seems much better than leaving the gap unexplained.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether you have recently become a freelancer or there is a period of freelancing in your work history, be prepared to answer questions about it in an interview. Most recruiters want to know why you went freelance or returned to the full-time workforce.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Having a history of freelance can highlight your ability to work independently and follow a brief. Use your freelance work in your resume to pinpoint your research and time management skills.</p>', '2023-04-18 09:52:09', '2023-04-18 09:52:09'),
(18, 66, 'How do I pitch myself as a freelance copywriter?', '1', 'how-do-i-pitch-myself-as-a-freelance-copywriter', '<h2>How do I pitch myself as a freelance copywriter?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Reaching out to potential clients is one of the main ways freelance copywriters pitch themselves. Freelance copywriters must be more proactive than full-time workers when looking for work. Drafting resumes and solid portfolios are the keys to generating new freelance business.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cold pitching is a significant component of getting work as a freelancer. Once you have a solid portfolio and know which companies you want to contact, you can develop a resume using these copywriting tips and start drafting those pitch emails.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your resume is your first impression. You can refine and improve your resume using copywriting techniques to have the best chance at advancing to an interview. At The Author&rsquo;s Pad, we can provide clear guidance to help you write your first resume, create your copywriting portfolio, and confidently grow your career.</p>', '2023-04-18 09:52:42', '2023-04-18 09:52:42'),
(19, 66, 'FAQs', '1', 'faqs', '<h2>FAQs</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are a few frequently asked questions about entering the copywriting field.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Can I be a copywriter with no experience?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You can be a copywriter with no experience. One of the most complex parts of entering the freelance copywriting world is getting those crucial early jobs that give you experience. You can create briefs for yourself or even offer your services for free to develop your skills if you&rsquo;re worried about copywriting with no experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Which type of copywriting is easiest?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Although all areas of copywriting have their challenges, business-to-business (B2B) copywriting is one of the most accessible fields. There is an incredibly high demand for copy oriented around B2B services and interactions, so even new copywriters stand a decent chance at getting experience in this area.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How do I know if I am good at copywriting?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The key to knowing if you&rsquo;re good at copywriting is if you love writing. Writers find joy in all kinds of writing styles and love learning the ins and outs of a new format. Copywriting poses a new challenge for writers, and those who excel do so because they love to write. If you regularly read and enjoy reading about various topics, you are a great candidate for copywriting.</p>', '2023-04-18 09:54:44', '2023-04-18 09:54:44'),
(20, 53, 'Feature Story Ideas: How to Write Them and Get Hired', '1', 'feature-story-ideas-how-to-write-them-and-get-hired', '<p>Feature stories are a great way to get your name and work out there. They can also help your career in journalism and other media fields.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, writing feature stories is not as easy as it sounds &ndash; you need to find an interesting topic, research it, interview people involved in the story, write up your research and make it interesting for readers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this article, we&rsquo;ll look at how to do all these steps successfully so you can write your own great feature story!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>The value of feature stories</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A feature story is a long, in-depth article usually written by a single reporter. Feature stories are often (but not always) accompanied by pictures and graphics. They&#39;re typically published in the local newspaper or magazine section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The word &quot;feature&quot; can be confusing because it means both &quot;special&quot; and &quot;characteristic.&quot; Features can be about people, places, events or ideas&mdash;but whatever they are about should have special significance for your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, a recent local story about an alligator living in Lake Ontario was considered newsworthy because of its novelty value (it&#39;s never happened before). Still, it doesn&#39;t focus on anything specific about gators, lakes, or Toronto that would make this topic particularly interesting to the readership. So we wouldn&#39;t consider running it as a feature story (even though the piece was well-written).</p>', '2023-04-18 13:11:11', '2023-04-18 13:11:11'),
(21, 53, 'Feature ideas', '1', 'feature-ideas', '<h2><strong>Feature ideas</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Feature story ideas are everywhere. The trick is finding them. Here are some of my favorite ways to find story ideas:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Current events</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the best ways to find story ideas is to find a current event that is interesting to people. A feature would be a longer follow-up piece to the breaking story. A follow-up to a breaking story or an exclusive will likely interest a major outlet.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Most readers are interested in people</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>People are interesting. Therefore, the best feature story ideas focus on interesting people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People are more interesting than places and things. An interesting person trumps events, ideas, facts and data &mdash; so think about how you can make your story about them (and not just what they did).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Listen to the people around you</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A great place to start is the people around you. Listen to your friends and family because they are often a good source of inspiration. They will be able to tell you about their own experiences with whatever topic you&#39;re interested in, and these stories can make for good storytelling material.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also listen to people that aren&#39;t in your life all that much, e.g., those who work at the grocery store or drive an ice cream truck down your street.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The more time you spend observing others, the more likely you might find something interesting about their lives or jobs that could spark feature story ideas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, it&#39;s important not only to listen but take note of what you&#39;re hearing. Write down good ideas as they come up, so there&#39;s no chance of forgetting them when it comes time for brainstorming sessions later on down the line.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Search for topics using keyword tools</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When you start researching a topic, you&#39;ll want to use keyword tools to find the most popular keywords for that topic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A keyword tool will give you a quick overview of what people are searching for about your topic and how many searches there are for each term. These are valuable metrics because they show what consumers are interested in at any given time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, if you search &quot;how much money do artists make?&quot; on Google Trends, it gives a graph showing that this question has been asked frequently over the last year (and even longer).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The graph also shows how often people searched for each variation of this question, like &quot;how much money do writers make?&quot; or &quot;what&#39;s an artist&#39;s salary.&quot; This is helpful information when deciding which idea is best suited for your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Attend cultural events in your community</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Attending cultural events in your community is a great way to find story ideas. You can meet new people, learn about different cultures and experience new things.</p>', '2023-04-19 03:31:42', '2023-04-19 03:31:42'),
(27, 53, 'Researching your idea', '1', 'researching-your-idea', '<h2><strong>Researching your idea</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To write a good feature story, you need to start with research. Here are some things you should do:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Google it. If there are companies or people that specialize in what it is you want to write about, Google those keywords and see if they come up on the first page of results. Also, look for other places that might be able to help&mdash;local newspapers and magazines, industry publications, etc., as well as any blogs or podcasts related to your topic (or even unrelated).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use your own experience. If there&#39;s something in your work background that relates&mdash;whether it&#39;s having worked at a certain company or being familiar with certain technical terms&mdash;use them. Readers love seeing someone who knows what they&#39;re talking about taking them on an insightful journey through their field of expertise so long as they don&rsquo;t come across as pretentious or arrogant.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Talk to people who have experience in this area, too, both professionals working in the industry and non-professionals who may just be enthusiasts. This way, there&#39;ll be more voices contributing great ideas, which makes your feature story stronger than just relying upon one person alone.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2023-04-18 13:15:23', '2023-04-18 13:15:23'),
(28, 53, 'Interviewing', '1', 'interviewing', '<h2><strong>Interviewing</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Interviewing is a great way to get your story ideas and fill in the details. You can interview people who have experienced or studied whatever it is you&#39;re writing about, whether it&#39;s an expert in the field or just someone who has been through something similar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re writing a story about becoming a professional ice skater, for example, interviewing other athletes might give you insight into what their training regimen was like and what challenges they had to overcome.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to write about how technology affects our relationships with friends and family members, interviewing people who love Facebook Messenger might give them enough material for an entire article.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When interviewing people, focus on getting information rather than making them feel uncomfortable or stressed out&mdash;that way, they&#39;ll be more likely to open up with deep thoughts and feelings instead of just giving short answers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ask open-ended questions like: &quot;What made this experience difficult?&quot; or &quot;How did this affect your life?&quot; These questions will help guide them toward talking about their experiences without coming off as manipulative (which could lead them away from being willing to share).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When recording an interview on the phone (or via video chat), use good equipment so that everything sounds clear when transcribed later on.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hold conversations in quiet rooms if possible. Find headphones that don&#39;t make noises when clicking around buttons.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Record at least two different perspectives even if one person may have said something better than another person would&#39;ve been able to say themselves.</p>', '2023-04-18 13:15:49', '2023-04-18 13:15:49'),
(29, 53, 'Creating a structure for your story', '1', 'creating-a-structure-for-your-story', '<h2><strong>Creating a structure for your story</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The story structure is the foundation of your story. You can&#39;t build a house without a solid foundation, and you can&#39;t write an article without one, either.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you start writing, take some time to plan out your story&#39;s structure by answering these questions:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>What are the main points I&#39;m trying to make?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>What order should I put them in?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>How much information do I need before I can begin making those points?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2023-04-18 13:16:10', '2023-04-18 13:16:10'),
(30, 53, 'Writing and revising your feature story', '1', 'writing-and-revising-your-feature-story', '<h2><strong>Writing and revising your feature story</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>After you finish writing the feature story, the next step is to revise it. If possible, you should use a spell checker and grammar checker before submitting your article to an editor.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Make sure that the piece is clear and concise by revising it repeatedly until every sentence makes sense on its own without needing any context from another sentence or paragraph (or from other articles).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Check that all of your facts are accurate. Make sure that your spelling, grammar, and punctuation are all correct. If anything is wrong with them, fix those errors before submitting a piece for publication.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2023-04-18 13:16:33', '2023-04-18 13:16:33'),
(31, 53, 'Finding your audience (getting hired)', '1', 'finding-your-audience-getting-hired', '<h2><strong>Finding your audience (getting hired)</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>For your feature story to be picked up by a newspaper or magazine, you need to know its audience. You should be able to answer these questions:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Who is this story for?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>What do they want to read?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>What are they interested in?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Why should they care about what I have to say? And how can I make them care more?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you know the answers to those questions, it&rsquo;s time for research. Go out and find some stories that have already been written on the subject (there are plenty of resources available online).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Read through them carefully and see what makes them interesting or unique. Think about what could make yours stand out from all others&mdash;what angle could make it more engaging for your target audience? Then use that as a starting point when writing out your own proposal.</p>', '2023-04-18 13:16:53', '2023-04-18 13:16:53'),
(32, 53, 'Conclusion', '1', 'conclusion', '<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As a features writer, your main goal is to find an interesting topic to write about, do the research and develop a story that other people also find interesting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You&#39;ll need to research to find out what the audience of a particular newspaper or magazine is interested in. You can then take this &#39;intel&#39; and create an interesting feature story that an editor would love to publish - good luck!</p>', '2023-04-18 13:17:11', '2023-04-18 13:17:11'),
(33, 59, 'From Hobby to Career: Building a Successful Copywriting Business', '1', 'from-hobby-to-career-building-a-successful-copywriting-business', '<p>If you want to start a copywriting business, it takes more than just writing skills. Building a successful career in copywriting requires hard work and time - and we have the advice you need. This article will explore what it takes to launch your own copywriting business and establish yourself in the industry.</p>', '2023-04-18 23:20:43', '2023-04-18 23:20:43'),
(34, 59, 'How To Take Your Business From A Hobby To A Copywriting Career', '1', 'how-to-take-your-business-from-a-hobby-to-a-copywriting-career', '<h2>How To Take Your Business From A Hobby To A Copywriting Career</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>So, just how do you go from hobbyist to professional copywriter? Here are a few key steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Define Your Niche</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To establish your copywriting business, it is crucial to identify your niche and focus on areas that interest you. Take into account your preferred projects and subjects that spark your curiosity; that way, you&#39;ll be able to target your copywriting services to the right clients and projects.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Identify Your Target Audience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To offer copywriting services, it&#39;s important to determine your target audience and the specific projects they require assistance with. This involves identifying ideal clients and the rates they&#39;re willing to pay for your work - crafting packages to match the needs of your target market is crucial, so get to know your clients, and boost your chances of success.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Consider Working With An Agency</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaborating with a copywriting agency that has experience can assist in launching your business. These agencies often offer resources like training, support, access to leads, and potential clients, and this can provide the necessary push to establish your business and gain industry experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Develop Your Portfolio and Brand</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your portfolio is crucial to your business, as it offers a compilation of your finest work - essential for demonstrating your abilities to potential clients. Therefore, it&#39;s essential to construct a portfolio and website that highlights your talents in the best possible way. Doing so will distinguish you from other copywriters and instil confidence in prospective clients, who will be more likely to hire you.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Develop A Pricing Model That Works For You</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When running a copywriting business, it is important to establish a pricing model that is reasonable and reflective of the quality of work provided. Factors to consider include hourly rates and project fees, and this can differ from client to client.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be Proactive About Gaining Exposure</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When starting a business, it&#39;s important to be proactive about gaining exposure for your services. This means taking advantage of social media platforms like Twitter, LinkedIn and Facebook to share your work and connect with potential clients. You can also start a blog or podcast related to copywriting and join relevant online groups to network with other writers in the industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be Prepared To Work Hard</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Lastly, it&#39;s important to be prepared to work hard. Don&#39;t expect success overnight - building a successful copywriting business takes time and dedication. Be patient and stay focused on your goals, and you&#39;ll eventually find yourself reaping the rewards of all your hard work.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:48:18', '2023-04-19 08:48:18'),
(39, 59, 'Case Study', '3', 'case-study', '<h3>Case Study<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSuccess Story: Samuel Jones</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Samuel was an avid copywriter and hobbyist, but he wanted to make it a career. He decided to take the plunge and invest in himself by taking on additional research, attending webinars, and reading all the latest articles on best practices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He found success quickly - within months, he had landed several clients who were happy with his work. He took the time to understand their goals and objectives, crafting content that spoke to them directly and achieved results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, Samuel is a full-time copywriter with a successful business. He credits his success to understanding the different writing styles, staying self-motivated, mastering key copywriting tools, honing his writing skills, and networking effectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;If you want to make a career out of your copywriting hobby, follow Samuel&#39;s footsteps - he has successfully converted his passion into a successful career!</p>', '2023-05-08 07:44:53', '2023-05-08 07:44:53'),
(43, 59, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact', '<h2><strong>Key Fact</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>40% of all businesses outsource their copywriting -if you are determined to succeed, there is a captive audience just waiting for your services.</p>', '2023-05-08 07:48:46', '2023-05-08 07:48:46'),
(44, 59, 'What Are The Benefits of Turning Your Hobby Into A Career?', '1', 'what-are-the-benefits-of-turning-your-hobby-into-a-career', '<h2>What Are The Benefits of Turning Your Hobby Into A Career?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is a great career if you have the right skills and personality. Here are some of the benefits of turning your hobby into a career:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>You Can Make A Living From Copywriting</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is a high-paying career option that can provide you with a stable income. As long as you have the skills and personality to excel in this field, you can make a good living by working as a copywriter.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>You Can Pursue Interesting Projects</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting offers a variety of projects across various industries, enabling individuals to explore new subjects and sustain their interest in their work while enhancing their skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>You Have The Potential To Make An Impact</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting has the potential to create an impact by effectively communicating business messages and promoting causes - if you are looking to make a difference in the world, this is one avenue that you can pursue.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>You Can Work From Anywhere</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The career of copywriting offers the flexibility to work from any location, which appeals to individuals seeking to work remotely or while travelling while still generating income. This makes copywriting an attractive option for many people, as it offers the freedom to work from home or any other location.</p>', '2023-04-19 03:44:02', '2023-04-19 03:44:02'),
(49, 59, 'What Skills Do I Need To Succeed As A Professional Copywriter?', '1', 'what-skills-do-i-need-to-succeed-as-a-professional-copywriter', '<h2>What Skills Do I Need To Succeed As A Professional Copywriter?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>While there are a few skills that apply equally to hobbyists and professionals, succeeding as a pro copywriter requires a specific set of skills. These include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Research Skills</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You&#39;ll need to be able to quickly find and interpret research material in order to write compelling copy for your clients. Use tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/ubersuggest\">UberSuggest</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/google-trends\">Google Trends</a> or <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hubspots-blog-topic-generator\">Hubspot&rsquo;s Blog Topic Generator</a> to come up with relevant, topical ideas.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Writing Ability</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a given, but your writing ability should be top-notch if you want to succeed as a professional copywriter. You should be able to craft engaging copy with a natural flow and write to the target audience - remember to use <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a>, and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/readable\">Readable</a> to craft great content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-19 03:47:14', '2023-04-19 03:47:14'),
(52, 59, 'KEY FACT', '2', 'key-fact-2', '<p>KEY FACT:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n55% of businesses said that quality content boosted the success of their business - so hone your skills, and you will never be short of work.</p>', '2023-04-28 06:14:54', '2023-04-28 06:14:54'),
(53, 59, 'Understanding Of Different Writing Styles', '1', 'understanding-of-different-writing-styles', '<h3>Understanding Of Different Writing Styles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You should have a good understanding of different writing styles, such as SEO writing, technical writing, and creative writing. This will help you when crafting content for different clients&#39; needs.</p>', '2023-04-18 23:31:21', '2023-04-18 23:31:21'),
(54, 59, 'Self-Motivation', '1', 'self-motivation', '<h3>Self-Motivation</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As a copywriter, you&#39;ll be working independently most of the time. This means you&#39;ll need to be able to motivate yourself and complete tasks on time.</p>', '2023-04-18 23:31:56', '2023-04-18 23:31:56'),
(55, 59, 'Knowledge Of Copywriting Tools', '1', 'knowledge-of-copywriting-tools', '<h3>Knowledge Of Copywriting Tools</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There are a variety of copywriting&nbsp;<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/\">tools </a>out there that can help you write better copy and make your job easier. You should have a strong understanding of these tools and know how to use them effectively - this includes key tools such as SEO tools and keyword research tools - <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/semrush\">SEMrush</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/surfer-seo\">Surfer SEO</a> and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/seo-powersuite\">SEO PowerSuite</a> are all major names in this category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You should also be able to use a range of spellcheck and grammar tools such as Grammarly and Hemingway for spelling and clarity, as well as design and editing software such as Adobe Creative Suite and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/canva\">Canva</a>.</p>', '2023-04-18 23:32:23', '2023-04-18 23:32:23'),
(56, 59, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Turning your hobby into a career can be incredibly rewarding, and copywriting is an excellent choice for those who have the right skills and dedication. With hard work and determination, you can make a living from copywriting and enjoy the benefits of pursuing interesting projects, making an impact in the world, and having the freedom to work from anywhere - sounds like a pretty sweet gig!</p>', '2023-04-18 23:32:51', '2023-04-18 23:32:51'),
(57, 65, 'What Is Cold Email Copywriting (And How To Optimize It)', '1', 'what-is-cold-email-copywriting-and-how-to-optimize-it', '<p>Cold Email. In the right hands, it can be an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://quickmail.io/cold-email-statistics\" target=\"_blank\">excellent tool</a>, helping to reach a wide audience directly, bypassing some of the need for things such as SEO. In the wrong hands, however, it can put potential clients off completely and can be a lot of effort for no return. Here we will explore cold emails in depth, to help you develop a solid understanding of this essential tool, increase your response rate, help you nail a compelling subject line, and keep you clear of the dreaded spam filter.</p>', '2023-04-19 01:58:31', '2023-04-19 01:58:31'),
(58, 65, 'What is it?', '1', 'what-is-it', '<h2>What is it?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>First, let us unpack what cold email copywriting actually is. Cold emails are unsolicited emails, which could be sent for almost any reason. Look through your own emails, you are sure to have a few in your inbox at all times, whether they are sales emails or cold outreach emails. You will likely be able to tell us the subject lines. Today, however, we are looking at how businesses can employ copywriters to use cold emails to their advantage. In this context, the cold email is sent to establish contact between the provider of a product or service, and a potential consumer.</p>', '2023-04-19 01:58:52', '2023-04-19 01:58:52'),
(59, 65, 'Why use it?', '1', 'why-use-it', '<h2>Why use it?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Why write cold emails? A cold email campaign has all of the benefits cold calling used to have, without half of the drawbacks. Cold emailing allows a business to make first contact with a large body of potential clients, without having to manually begin the sales process anew with each new potential customer. It is more proactive and less static than something like a blog post, which relies on traffic coming to it. Instead, cold emails can go direct<em>&nbsp;to</em>&nbsp;your target audience. It is, therefore, a highly time-efficient method.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is a highly efficient way to reach a target audience, as it allows for a copywriter to write one email, and then use it to cast a wide net reaching potential customers. From there, WIT those not interested will generally not, allowing the copywriter to then narrow down their focus and conduct follow-ups with those interested.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A good cold email campaign can also increase brand awareness; even if a potential customer does not respond directly to the e-mail, they are now aware of the brand and may consider it when they are in need of the product or service the company provides in the future.</p>', '2023-04-19 01:59:12', '2023-04-19 01:59:12');
INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(60, 65, 'Cold Email Copywriting Do\'s and Don\'ts', '1', 'cold-email-copywriting-dos-and-donts', '<h2>Cold Email Copywriting Do&#39;s and Don&#39;ts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s time to explore the keys to writing effective cold emails. Follow these do&#39;s and don&#39;ts and you will be writing engaging, successful cold emails that will grab readers&#39; attention, and turn them into customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Do Hook Them In</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The key to successful cold email campaigns lies in an effective subject line. The subject line is the first point of contact, the subject line must<em>&nbsp;grab the reader&#39;s attention</em>. It must frame what it is you are selling, and the essentials of what you want to get across while remaining simple and efficient. Research suggests 47% of recipients open emails entirely based on the quality of the subject line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Don&#39;t fall into the trap of trying to include everything in the subject line, bombarding the reader with information. Think about what it is that is most appealing about the product or service in question, and try to write something that distils what is being offered in as succinct language as possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Try using an open-ended question in your subject line or opening lines. Or highlight a pain point for customers of competition, and imply that a solution to this lies within the email body. Ensure those opening lines are strong and quick to the point, as they will show after the title in the recipient&#39;s inbox. Once you have them hooked, then you can elaborate, but for now, keep it short and sweet.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Do Establish Credibility</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The worst thing that can happen to your carefully crafted email is for it to end up in the spam folder. Or, for your subject line or opening lines of the email itself to be so suspect and full of spam words that it may as well end up in the spam folder. Avoid phrases like &#39;100% per cent satisfaction guaranteed. Avoid suspicious words, and under no circumstances should there be grammatical errors!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Credibility can also be established by adopting the correct tone of voice. A B2B email should be more formal, and professional. It can be more data-driven, showing the results and the hard proof is more likely to entice a business, driven by the bottom line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whereas the email body for a B2C campaign can afford to adopt a more personal, familiar tone. It should appeal to the reader as a person, and read as though it is&nbsp;<em>from&nbsp;</em>a real person. This is a key component of a good cold email; it must have a touch of humanity. Recipients don&#39;t like to feel as if they&#39;re receiving automated, robotic stuff.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Personalized emails will always have an advantage over impersonal, generic ones. So take your time in writing it, and think about what it is that is appealing about your product or service to a potential customer, and accentuate it, to appeal to their needs and wants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You are also advised to include the company name, and contact details in the email signature. Include a link to the company&#39;s landing page or a link to a blog post. Transparency is key to establishing credibility.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Do Include A Call To Action</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Any good sales pitch should include a call to action. You could have written the most compelling email body possible, but if there is no call to action followed by a simple and clear link to getting the reader started down that path, then it was all for nothing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Include links to a blog post, or reviews of the product on a trustworthy site, showing social proof of a real person showing the product or service&#39;s value.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Don&#39;t End Up In The Spam Folder!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the absolute most important mistake you cannot afford to make. Unfortunately, sometimes, it may happen, but that doesn&#39;t mean you can&#39;t do everything possible to prevent it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unfortunately, but for understandable reasons, email providers do not disclose what dictates their spam filters, so understanding how to avoid being consigned to the spam folder isn&#39;t an exact science.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Don&#39;t make outrageous claims in your subject line or body email. Make sure you make it possible for the recipient to reply to the email, as reply rates factor into whether an email will be considered spam or not going forward. Encourage readers to add the sender&#39;s email to their address book, which will prevent any future emails from being sent to spam or junk folders.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid all capitals in the subject line or opening lines, and make sure the email feels personalised enough so that the recipient doesn&#39;t just assume it is random spam not intended for them specifically. Do all of this and your cold email copywriting will be done the justice it deserves by seeing the light of day.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Don&#39;t Be Vague</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Related to the CTA mentioned earlier, cold emails cannot afford to be vague. The subject lines should be simple, but it should be clear who the target audience is. If this sound tricky, it&#39;s because it is; writing a simple subject line (and email copywriting in general) that is compelling is an art, but it is also essential.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If possible, the subject lines or the opening lines of your cold email should identify pain points, the body email should include social proof, value proposition, and should read as though it was written by a real person for a real person. This may sound silly, but too often cold emails can read like they were simply generated, and don&#39;t take time to communicate the way a real person would.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Leave out the boring stuff, vague descriptions and promises; be direct, concise, and compelling. Writing good cold emails is about sharpening what you have to say to its finest point. Your entire cold email should in a sense be a call to action generally, punctuated with a specific, easily followable call to action at the end. Don&#39;t hit at the general direction of the site, provide landing pages, or for example a blog post you recently wrote for your client, identify a unique pain point and demonstrate the solution to it;&nbsp;<em>be specific.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Don&#39;t Forget Follow Ups</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is key. Cold email campaigns are, in the best-case scenario, just the beginning of an ongoing relationship between your client and their customer, with you as a silent middleman. Keep track of your response rate, conduct follow-ups, and obtain reviews for further social proof, learning lessons from every negative and positive response will allow you to build on your momentum going forward. All of this also helps your future emails continue to avoid the spam filter. Get feedback, and ensure your target audience is being reached.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:41:57', '2023-04-19 08:41:57'),
(67, 65, 'You Are Now Ready To Write An Elite, Effective Cold Email Campaign', '1', 'you-are-now-ready-to-write-an-elite-effective-cold-email-campaign', '<h2>You Are Now Ready To Write An Elite, Effective Cold Email Campaign</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>But don&#39;t forget this last bit of advice; never get complacent. Never assume that you are so good that you can&#39;t continue to improve. As with all digital marketing, and copywriting generally, it is a constantly changing game, and you have to stay up to date on current trends and changes in the landscape to remain as effective as you can possibly be. So&nbsp;<em>never get complacent.</em></p>', '2023-04-19 02:02:18', '2023-04-19 02:02:18'),
(68, 64, 'The 4 Benefits of Proofreading in Copywriting', '1', 'the-4-benefits-of-proofreading-in-copywriting', '<p>As copywriters, we are always looking for the next step in bettering our writing skills, the next jump into expanding our client base, and the subsequent writing tool that will perfect our copy. As it turns out, we might be overlooking something that is always available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading is something that can guide us to success in our writing. It helps us to improve quality, remove mistakes and correct our writing inconsistencies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Because no matter how advanced, qualified and experienced we are, we are all human (except the AI-generated copywriters), and we all make mistakes!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here at <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/\">The Author&rsquo;s Pad</a>, we believe in improving your already brilliant copywriting skills, bettering yourself in the present and pushing yourself forward for new and exciting positions in the future.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So here are four great benefits proofreading will provide, opening doors you didn&rsquo;t know existed.</p>', '2023-04-19 02:08:31', '2023-04-19 02:08:31'),
(69, 64, '1.  Eliminating Errors', '1', '1-eliminating-errors', '<h2>1. Eliminating Errors</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re looking to enhance and optimise your skills as a copywriter, you should pay particular attention to common errors and mistakes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You might find yourself doing this without acknowledging it, for example, on your way to work or shopping for groceries!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finding misspelt words on pricing tags and an incorrect &lsquo;your&rsquo; on a construction sign is all signs of your expertise and cognitive brain constantly working towards a perfect copy. Focusing this brainpower on your copywriting is a great tool that you already own.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading your copywriting can help you catch errors like inconsistent spelling, incorrect capitalisation, and complex grammar mistakes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Can&rsquo;t you get the hang of checking out the minor faults in your work? There are some great tools that you can use as a helping hand. Here are a few <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool\">we recommend</a> for content editing</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n1.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/stackedit\">StackEdit</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/yoast\">Yoast</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/obsidian\">Obsidian</a></p>', '2023-04-19 02:09:17', '2023-04-19 02:09:17'),
(70, 64, '2. Confidence in Your Copywriting', '1', '2-confidence-in-your-copywriting', '<h2>2. Confidence in Your Copywriting</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Being confident in your work is essential. Nobody wants to worry about their content and its performance after the workday is done, but as copywriters, we are invested in the content we create, which is sometimes unavoidable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Passionate about our writing, there&rsquo;s no easy way to avoid this, but proofreading your work and feeling confident in the quality you send to your clients is the best way to get out of this habit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The confidence that you build through consistent proofreading will shine through your work in your tone and voice, helping you appear intelligent and trustworthy to potential readers (or clients!).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/about\">community</a> is a place to help like-minded copywriters. That&rsquo;s why sharing ways to benefit us mentally whilst working in a workplace full of positive and negative feedback is important to us.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-19 02:09:45', '2023-04-19 02:09:45'),
(71, 64, '3. Professionalism', '1', '3-professionalism', '<h2>3. Professionalism</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Professionalism can be crafted through numerous writing techniques, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Removing Distractions from your copywriting.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have all experienced that annoying moment when we are dragged away from our book and struggle to get back into reading it. This is precisely what we want to avoid in copywriting, and removing distractions from your copy is the perfect way to do it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Potential misinterpretations can break the flow of your readers, and keeping their attention is our key focus!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Solidifying Understanding</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Something as simple as a second reading of your copywriting can avoid the tendency to fill in the gaps when proofreading.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even the slightest mistake can lead to a misunderstanding, and the message of your content can be lost. Proofreading is an essential tool for avoiding this issue and can add a sense of clarity to your work!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Building Trust and Rapport</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s critical to have a cohort of readers that can trust you and continuously return to your content for their information, entertainment and more!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To gain their trust, you must provide high-quality copywriting that communicates effectively.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading is the best way to ensure your writing comes across as knowledgeable and trustworthy. Nobody will trust a site littered with spelling mistakes, incorrect grammar, and a confusing tone!</p>', '2023-04-19 02:15:47', '2023-04-19 02:15:47'),
(72, 64, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact-3', '<h2>Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Perceptual Restoration has been a concept surrounding our brains&#39; tendency to fill in gaps in written and spoken language since 1970.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, we don&rsquo;t fully understand how it works yet!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As copywriters, we automatically know what should be in this missing gap and are likelier to read a copy without realising it&#39;s missing.</p>', '2023-05-08 08:07:54', '2023-05-08 08:07:54'),
(73, 64, '4. Elevate Your Copywriting', '1', '4-elevate-your-copywriting', '<h2>4. Elevate Your Copywriting</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Elevating your copywriting is something we all aspire to do; that&rsquo;s why you&#39;re engaging with our community at The Author&rsquo;s Pad in the first place!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So how does proofreading directly improve your copywriting?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Apart from setting you out from the crowd with your excellent copywriting skills and content,&nbsp; proofreading is a great way to land that dream job.</p>', '2023-04-19 02:16:43', '2023-04-19 02:16:43'),
(74, 64, 'Case Study', '3', 'case-study', '<h2>Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Imagine your applying for that Junior Copywriter role, and you&#39;re eager to start your journey in the writing world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first thing you are required to do is apply.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ensuring your CV and cover letter are up to scratch is vital as it&#39;s the first impression you will make on any employer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What will ensure this first impression sticks? Perfect use of spelling, grammar and tone!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How can you achieve this? Proofreading!</p>', '2023-05-08 08:08:25', '2023-05-08 08:08:25'),
(75, 64, 'Frequently Asked Questions', '1', 'frequently-asked-questions-2', '<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>What is Professional Proofreading?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Professional proofreading is generally considered the practice in which you hire a professional proofreading service or person to do this step in editing copy for you. This practice is used by large-scale businesses to save time and effort.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How Important Are Proofreading Skills?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading skills will prove very important in the average person&#39;s life as they will be key to their success in education, such as studying for a degree at university. The skill continues to be important to those who choose a career path such as copywriting, marketing or editing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-19 08:44:16', '2023-04-19 08:44:16'),
(76, 43, 'How Much Do Copywriters Make?', '1', 'how-much-do-copywriters-make', '<p>Professional copywriters are in great demand in copywriting, and you have a huge market as a playing field. This article will familiarize you with the different copywriter salary ranges. But before getting into copywriting, you have to ask yourself whether an average copywriting salary can replace the primary income from your regular job.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ask yourself:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>How much do copywriters make?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>What level of copywriter salary can you expect to earn with your present copywriting skills?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>And, ultimately, will it pay the bills?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>With this in mind, it&rsquo;ll be best if you set your income goals. Do you want your sole income to come from copywriting, or do you want to look at your copywriting salary as a side income?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting salaries differ from country to country. You have to be realistic and determine the average income a copywriter can make in the country where you would be working.</p>', '2023-04-19 02:21:06', '2023-04-19 02:21:06'),
(77, 43, 'What are the average copywriter salaries in different countries?', '1', 'what-are-the-average-copywriter-salaries-in-different-countries', '<h2><strong>What are the average copywriter salaries in different countries?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s look at the average copywriting salaries in the USA, UK, Australia, and Canada.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember that several other factors affect copywriter salaries, such as the size of the company a copywriter is working for, whether they&rsquo;re a junior copywriter or senior copywriter, the location of the company in the country itself, and the industry the copywriter is engaged in.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How much do copywriters make in the USA?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriters in the US can expect a base salary of $69,450. You can expect an additional cash compensation of $5,000, which takes the total to $74,450.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, according to the US Bureau of Labor Statistics, the hourly rate for the lowest, medium, and highest copywriter categories is $15 an hour, $30 an hour, and $55 an hour, respectively. This means the highest copywriter salary is $121,600 a year, the medium of $62,000 a year, and the lowest is $31,700 a year.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How much do copywriters make in the UK?&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The average salary of a copywriter is lower in the UK compared to the copywriter salaries in the US, starting from a low of &pound;25,000 for junior copywriters and &pound;30,000 for medium-level copywriters. Senior copywriters can expect to make around &pound;45,000 or more.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How much do copywriters make in Australia?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriters in Australia have higher average salaries than their counterparts in the US and UK. A junior copywriter can expect an average salary of $76,000 a year. The medium-level copywriters make around $87,000 annually, while the senior copywriters earn an average of $122,000. The copywriter&#39;s salaries are also subject to location and industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How much do copywriters make in Canada?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A junior copywriter in Canada with less than one year of experience can expect an annual salary of C$41,000. A medium-level copywriter can expect to earn C$57,000, while a senior copywriter can earn up to C$105,000. All these averages include tips, bonuses, and overtime pay.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Do copywriters in different branches and locations have different salaries?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Copywriter salary by location</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Now that you&rsquo;re familiar with the copywriter salaries you may expect, it&rsquo;s time to find out your earning potential in different fields of copywriting.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether you&rsquo;re a &#39;write for fun&#39; type of copywriter or a workaholic copywriter, how much you earn will greatly impact your life.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The two main factors responsible for a copywriter&#39;s salary difference are location and experience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, a junior copywriter in a big city like New York can make $61,000 a year on average. In contrast, a junior copywriter in a smaller city will earn $42,000 a year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the same time, a senior copywriter in New York will make $93,000 a year, and if the same copywriter is based in a smaller city, he will earn $65,000 a year on average.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking at these numbers, you can understand that a copywriter&#39;s salary in a small town is in a comfortable range, while in a bigger city, it&rsquo;s a lucrative one (although living in a big city is more expensive).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, with the increase in remote working, the lines have blurred, and a copywriter can expect a good, big-city salary and still work wherever he wishes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Copywriter salary by different branches</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As a copywriter, you can be one of these three:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Agency copywriter</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>In-house copywriter</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Freelance copywriter&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriters usually start by working with an agency for a couple of years. They then move on to being an in-house copywriter. Later, when they have more experience, they may branch out on their own and work as a freelancer or have their own agency.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Agency copywriter salary</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Marketing and advertising agencies offer a great place to network and learn on the job. You can expect a good entry-level copywriter salary if you work for a competitive, successful agency.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The average salary for a junior copywriter is $47,000, and a senior copywriter working for an agency can expect an average salary of $88,000 (both estimates are for the US).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There isn&#39;t much data on average senior copywriter salaries because copywriters rarely stay long enough with an agency to reach seniority levels.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>In-house copywriter salary</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Working as an in-house copywriter offers mid-career salaries. In-house copywriters usually move towards marketing. You can position yourself to get lucrative offers from competing firms for your skills.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These days it is in the copywriter&#39;s best interests to move jobs to increase their salaries, as there are few chances of getting more than a couple of promotions. Also, the business you&rsquo;re working for as an in-house copywriter won&#39;t think twice about letting you go for their financial benefit if they need to.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want a steady, long-term paycheck and you&rsquo;re not ambitious enough to freelance or have your own agency, being an in-house copywriter could be the best job for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the US, the average salary of a junior copywriter is $48,000 a year, and a senior copywriter can expect to make $85,000 a year.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Freelance copywriter salary</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The possibility of remote work has made freelance copywriting more doable for copywriters. It&rsquo;s ideal for a freelance copywriter to work at an agency initially to make contacts and gain experience. Freelancing may offer the highest pay with the least work for a copywriter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But it&rsquo;s best to remember that once you decide to freelance, you are on your own. There are no healthcare benefits, you have to pay full taxes, and no 401K matching/retirement contributions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A freelance copywriter&rsquo;s salary is not dependent on a copywriter&#39;s junior or senior level. It depends on how many products/services you can sell your copy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While entry-level freelance copywriters struggle to make $20,000 a year, seasoned copywriters have been known to scale around $150,000 a year and more.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-19 03:03:31', '2023-04-19 03:03:31'),
(90, 43, 'Is copywriting for you? ', '1', 'is-copywriting-for-you', '<h2>Is copywriting for you?&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ve now become familiar with the common copywriter salaries and how they&rsquo;re dependent on the copywriting type, the location you are based, and the industry you&rsquo;re in.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you dive into the vast field of copywriting, it&rsquo;s in your best interests to crunch the numbers and set your income goals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you want to earn six figures, or are you just looking for a side income?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is suitable for every income goal, but you need to decide what that goal is and act accordingly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take action, explore high-paying copywriting jobs, and start your career as a professional copywriter.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-19 02:34:59', '2023-04-19 02:34:59'),
(99, 62, 'Writing Hacks:  8 Productivity Tips for Copywriters', '1', 'writing-hacks-8-productivity-tips-for-copywriters-2', '<p>Do you want to maximise your productivity as a writer? Creating something from nothing while staring down the barrel of the blank white page (or screen) can be intimidating. Learning to boost your productivity makes that first step so much easier and paves the way for you to create your best content.</p>', '2023-04-19 02:47:02', '2023-04-19 02:47:02'),
(100, 62, 'Productivity Tips', '1', 'productivity-tips', '<h2><strong>Explore our best productivity tips for copywriters and discover what can make you a better writer.</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Start the day right</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Boost your productivity by starting your day on a positive note. Walking outside at the start of your day is a great way to find some inspiration and get your blood pumping. Copywriting is a sedentary job unless you have a treadmill desk. Jobs that involve lots of sitting increase your likelihood of <a href=\"https://healthy-workplaces.eu/en/about-topic/priority-area/sedentary-work#:~:text=Many%20jobs%20involve%20prolonged%20sitting,as%20diabetes%20and%20heart%20disease.\">developing musculoskeletal disorders</a>, so getting adequate exercise is essential.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reading also sparks your creativity and gets your mind up and running, ready for a day of excellent writing. Podcasts are an ideal alternative if you want to walk and listen &zwnj;or prefer listening to reading. Find a novel or some non-fiction writing that fascinates you. Progressing more each day provides excellent structure and excitement to your mornings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, get your breakfast right. You don&rsquo;t have to eat a big breakfast to start your day. Some people find that large meals at the start of the day leave them feeling sluggish and ready to lie down. Instead, choose a balanced option that gives you the fuel to be productive. Writers are renowned for their love of coffee, but you need food to think properly.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Prioritise and plan</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Fail to prepare, and you prepare to fail. The old saying is correct: planning your day is crucial to productivity. Block your time in the day so you don&rsquo;t have to guess what you should do next. Having a plan for the day makes it much easier to stay on track and avoid distractions while you write.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;ve never heard of eating the frog, now&rsquo;s the time. The concept comes from <a href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/quotes/168105-eat-a-live-frog-first-thing-in-the-morning-and\">Mark Twain</a>, who wrote that if you ever had to eat a live frog, it&rsquo;s best to do it first thing in the morning as nothing worse will happen to you all day. For productive copywriting, this means tackling your &lsquo;scariest&rsquo; task first. Plan your day so that the most extensive, intimidating work comes first and the rest of your day is a breeze.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The only time Eat The Frog doesn&rsquo;t apply is when you have deadlines to meet. Organise your work according to when it&rsquo;s due to avoid last-minute stress writing. You become a more productive copywriter when you learn how to prioritise your workflow effectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Separate tasks</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Divide your tasks into their subsections to increase your productivity in each section. For example, completing the first drafts is a priority if you have three blogs to write. Edit them later to create some separation and give you a cleaner insight into their quality. Proofreading is more efficient and manageable when you&rsquo;ve had a proper break from the words.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For freelance copywriters, limit communication with clients to a specific section of the day. For example, if you write in the morning, contact your clients in the early afternoon, and then edit and proofread your work, you clearly define each task. Set firm boundaries with your clients so they understand you aren&rsquo;t available 24/7 to reduce stress and boost productivity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another way to separate your tasks is by setting small deadlines for yourself. For example, long-form writing with distant deadlines is easy to procrastinate. Rather than face the stress and low-quality work of last-minute writing, create deadlines for yourself to space out the work. It makes you more productive, and your writing is of higher quality.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Cultivate a productive atmosphere</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Writers know too well the importance of a good atmosphere. Ambience is subjective, so you must find something that works for you. Some people prefer to write in silence to concentrate, while others prefer background music. You can play the sound of a hairdryer or even ambient birdsong if it helps - find what works for you and enables you to concentrate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For some copywriters, working in public is the best way to feel productive. Whether it&rsquo;s the energy of the world around you, or the perceived pressure of being watched, writing in public can increase your productivity massively. Try writing in a local cafe or park to combine fresh air with work and see if it helps.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Those who work remotely from their homes can improve their productivity by setting boundaries with family members. Clearly (and politely) communicate your working schedule to family members/housemates so they know not to disturb you to ease your workflow. Working without sudden interruptions will improve the quality and quantity of your writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Set goals</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your writing is more productive and consistent when you have a daily word count you want to reach. Setting a goal like this pushes you to work harder and get more done daily. Be realistic about your word count and ensure it&rsquo;s a target you can consistently reach daily (5,000 words a day is not realistic).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Similarly, challenging yourself to produce a certain number of blogs in a week keeps you focused on your big-picture goals. Establish how many blogs you can comfortably create in a week with the right atmosphere and work setup. It is significantly easier to work consistently with a concrete idea of how much you know you can produce.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You also get a confidence boost on days and weeks when you go over your word count or weekly blog target. Those &lsquo;big win&rsquo; days motivate you to keep pushing yourself and striving for increased productivity whilst maintaining the integrity and quality of your writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Use productivity tools</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the most significant writing hacks that can increase your productivity is utilising digital and practical productivity tools. Strict Workflow is a plugin for your web browser that eliminates distractions. Click the tomato icon to block distracting sites for 25 minutes, after which you can click again for 5 minutes of full access.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A cornerstone of any writer&rsquo;s toolkit is Grammarly. This editing software reduces editing and proofreading time, giving you more time to create. You can customise your feedback based on your target audience and language preferences. Grammarly also highlights elements like passive voice many writers miss in their work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A more practical hack that doesn&rsquo;t need a tool is removing your phone from the equation. If you&rsquo;re entering a long block of writing, you might even want to switch to aeroplane mode. You can work much more productively without the distraction of your phone. Set it to silent, screen-side down, and keep it away from your computer for best results.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. Take breaks</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Effective productivity is as much about working as it is about resting. Your mind can only create high-quality work for so long before it needs a break. Exercise by walking after lunch to refresh your mind and allow your body to stretch and move before returning to work. Yoga or stretching is another good way to promote your blood flow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re social, a midday break is perfect for a quick phone call to catch up with friends and family. Relaxing for a period in the middle of your day breaks up the periods of concentration and makes it easier to focus again afterwards. A lunch date can combine the need for fresh air, socialisation, and fuel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the other end of the spectrum, relaxing in isolation will benefit some writers more. Take a break to meditate partway through your day to boost your productivity. Clearing your mind and letting thoughts flow naturally through your head clears your head like a walk might.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>8. Experiment with your schedule</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These hacks are helpful, but ultimately you need to configure your schedule to suit you best. Some writers find that working through the night makes them more productive and creative. <a href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/author/quotes/9494.H_P_Lovecraft#:~:text=No%20one%20knows%20whether%20or,has%20tried%20writing%20at%20night.%E2%80%9D\">H. P. Lovecraft</a> once wrote, &lsquo;No one knows whether or not he is a writer unless he has tried writing at night&rsquo;. Try it to see if it improves your work and mood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alternatively, waking up much earlier than usual and writing can leave you feeling accomplished. Finishing your work day when most people have lunch gives you the rest of the day to unwind, leaving you refreshed for the next day. Early birds and night owls should try these methods before writing themselves off as &lsquo;bad writers&rsquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Experiment with moving different tasks around within your work day to perfect your schedule. Writing first is best for some people, while others prefer to finish their day with writing assignments. Improving your productivity is much easier once you&rsquo;ve established a pattern you enjoy most.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These hacks can all have a positive effect on your writing and your work life. Copywriting can be freeing and enjoyable if you find the methods that work for you. At The Author&rsquo;s Pad, we can advise on the best tools for copywriters and how to make the most of your time to boost your copywriting career.</p>', '2023-04-19 02:49:49', '2023-04-19 02:49:49'),
(101, 62, 'FAQs', '1', 'faqs-2', '<h2>FAQs</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are some frequently asked questions about improving your productivity as a copywriter.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What are the 3 common mistakes a copywriter may make?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One mistake copywriters make is thinking they don&rsquo;t need help. If you&rsquo;re unsure about something in your brief, asking your client about it saves more time than trying to figure it out alone. Another mistake is neglecting your optimisation, which is crucial for effective copy. Finally, misusing words and industry terms is an error that you can avoid with research.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Why do most copywriters fail?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The copywriters who fail usually lack either confidence or ability. Training and practise can improve your writing abilities to make you a stronger copywriting, but confidence is all on you. Believing in yourself is essential to making it as a copywriter. If you practise your writing, you&rsquo;ll probably notice you become more confident as a result of your experience level.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What is the biggest challenge in copywriting?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Dealing with clients is one of the hardest parts of copywriting, from getting contracts with them to negotiating elements of the work. Other challenges copywriters face include: competitive environment, time management, difficult research, and motivation. If you can properly manage your time, the other challenges become easier to manage as well.</p>', '2023-04-19 02:50:20', '2023-04-19 02:50:20'),
(102, 46, 'How to Become a Copywriter with No Experience', '1', 'how-to-become-a-copywriter-with-no-experience', '<p>So you want to become a successful freelance copywriter but have zero experience. How do you get started?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike other career choices, you don&#39;t need formal education or qualifications. Copywriting clients want proof that you&#39;re a good copywriter. Evidence can come in the form of testimonials, glowing testimonials, and conversion statistics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That&#39;s great, but if you&#39;ve never written before and never had clients to build up a portfolio, how do you get started on your copywriting journey? Read on to discover the best route to become a copywriter with no experience.</p>', '2023-04-19 03:57:17', '2023-04-19 03:57:17');
INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(103, 46, 'Discover the best route to become a copywriter with no experience', '1', 'discover-the-best-route-to-become-a-copywriter-with-no-experience', '<h2>Discover the best route to become a copywriter with no experience&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1) Focus on a particular sector or industry</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is a great skill, but very few copywriters know that market knowledge trumps the slickest of wordsmiths. Clients will value a mediocre freelance copywriter with in depth knowledge of their industry. They will always outperform a gifted copywriter who has basic or no knowledge of an industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not only that, you lose major credibility if you say you can &#39;write anything.&#39; Clients don&#39;t want to teach freelance copywriters the basics of their industry. They want a good copywriter who can hit the ground running.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nearly every single successful freelance copywriter with a long-established copywriting career has niched down.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Perhaps you&#39;re a fan of keeping fit. You can now speak knowledgeably to copywriting clients in the fitness industry. Or you could write for adjacent industries such as wellness or supplements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maybe you&#39;re a female copywriter who&#39;s passionate about women&#39;s issues? You can write copy that proves your expertise to clients focusing on marketing to women.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you have a degree in accountancy but hate the idea of becoming an accountant? You can impress accountancy firms with your grasp of accounting terminology.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Clients like hiring writers they feel instantly comfortable with because they &#39;get&#39; them.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>2) Research the freelance copywriting market</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Now that you&#39;ve niched, to become a copywriter in demand, you need to find out what genuine paying clients in this area want.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is easy as all you have to do is look for freelance writer jobs or gigs online.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some platforms to find great copywriting job offers are:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Indeed</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mediabistro</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Problogger</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Journalismjobs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Freelancewritinggigs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>BloggingPro</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>To make it as easy as possible for you, &lt;NAME OF OUR PLATFORM&gt; goes through all the above sites and more to create a list of copywriting job offers in one place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These adverts will tell you what paying clients in your chosen industry want from freelance copywriters. The best adverts will also give you lots of information about the companies.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>3) Focus on a particular copywriting service</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When starting as a freelance copywriter, it could be tempting to say you can write &#39;anything.&#39; You just want to get started, and you&#39;re happy to turn your hand to articles, landing pages, adverts, emails, video scripts, product pages, ad copywriting, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Being a &#39;jack of all trades&#39; does not inspire confidence in potential clients. That will make you a mediocre freelance copywriter. Become a copywriter who&#39;s an expert in a particular service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A good copywriter will specialise in one or two copywriting services. For example, a direct response copywriter is skilled at improving conversions on a landing or sales page. It&#39;s &#39;direct response&#39; because a customer takes action immediately after reading. The action could be leaving an email address, booking a call, or buying something.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Direct response copywriting is a different skill compared to, for example, blog post writing or email marketing. Email marketing copywriters tend to focus on building momentum for sales over time. Blog post writers concentrate on keeping the reader on the site for as long as possible (for SEO ranking). Almost every successful copywriter has niched down into a particular area of expertise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you focus on a particular form of copywriting, you can quickly become a copywriter with an expert reputation. That&#39;s because you&#39;ll be doing the same thing again and again. You can&#39;t become great at something when you&#39;re learning a multitude of other skills at the same time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use the market research you did earlier and your copywriting preferences to niche into one or two key services.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>4) Read copywriting books to learn copywriting</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ve already stated that you don&#39;t need formal training to be a great copywriter. However, you can&#39;t expect to get paid copywriting jobs if you don&#39;t know anything about copywriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A good copywriter understands their job is to make their clients money by persuading people to buy from these clients. This differs from content writing for brand awareness, relationship building, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The better your copywriting skills, the more money you make for them. This means you can command more money too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The copywriting world has some famous copywriters who have written books on writing copy designed to persuade. This is a cost-effective way to learn copywriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some recommendations:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The Gary Halbert Letter - Gary Halbert</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scientific Advertising - Claude Hopkins</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Breakthrough Advertising - Eugene Schwartz</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ogilvy on Advertising - David Ogilvy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tested Advertising Methods - John Caples</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Integrated Marketing Communications - Don Schultz</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Advertising Secrets of the Written Word - Joseph Sugarman</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Copy Logic! - Mike Palmer and Michael Masterson</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The Copywriter&#39;s Handbook - Robert Bly</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, if you followed the earlier step and focused on a particular copywriting service, look for books that teach this. For example, The Ultimate Sales Letter by Dan Kennedy is a must-read if you wish to become a direct response copywriter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keep this in mind if you&#39;re worried that some of the recommended books are decades old. Human psychology has remained unchanged for centuries. The medium we use to communicate may change, but the vast majority of the psychology involved is the same.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It doesn&#39;t matter that some of these copywriting greats in the list above are dead and buried. It&#39;s irrelevant that they were writing for print when we are focused on online copywriting. The key skills required to persuade a person to buy from a particular company, brand or person remain unchanged.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>5) Take a copywriting course</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There are lots of courses out there that help you with the foundations of copywriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Make sure your chosen copywriting course is taught by a professional copywriter. They must have proven experience and success in copywriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember, you don&#39;t need any experience to become a copywriter. That&#39;s great for you. But it also means people without many copywriting skills can create copywriting courses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some recommendations:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1) American Writers &amp; Artists Institute</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is one of the world&#39;s leading copywriting training programs. They attract some heavyweight copywriters who create programs for them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Their vast library means you can find the perfect copywriting course for your chosen copywriting form. However, be aware that many of their programs can be expensive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2) &#39;Success Works&#39; Copywriting Course</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a three-month course that focuses on SEO copywriting. It&#39;s by Heather Lloyd-Martin, a copywriter that Forbes describes as &lsquo;the pioneer&#39; of SEO copywriting. As Google is such a huge factor in the success of most businesses, most copywriters need SEO knowledge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3) {Our program - add name when we have it}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course will show you how to write converting and SEO-optimised copy and gain clients. You&#39;ll also learn pricing strategies and negotiation skills. This will help you build a successful copywriting business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s something many people forget when looking to become a copywriter. They focus on learning copywriting and getting clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, the most successful copywriters don&#39;t have a tonne of clients. The best copywriters have a small number of clients who pay them well. This program will show you how to achieve this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4) The Blackford Centre</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This copywriting course not only teaches you great copywriting, but you&#39;ll also learn how to run a freelance writing business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You&#39;re also assigned a tutor who will keep you on track. This is great for anyone who struggles to motivate themselves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5) Sell Like Hell</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a course from renowned copywriter Carmine MasterPierro. It focuses on sales conversion copy, so it&#39;s ideal if you want to get into the direct response form of copywriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6) Transmedia</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course is for those who wish to work as an in house copywriter for corporates. You&#39;ll learn how to write effective copy by understanding branding and corporate identity. This allows you to pursue corporate copywriter jobs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6) Start writing!</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s incredible how many people want to become a copywriter, yet they don&#39;t write regularly. They don&#39;t even keep a diary!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, a copywriting career has an element of &#39;learning on the job&#39;. But no client will be happy for you to learn basic copywriting techniques on their dime.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reading books and doing copywriting courses will give you the theory, but then you need to put it into practice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Why not start writing copy for your own blog or website showcasing what you&#39;ve learnt so far? In a matter of weeks, you could have a simple copywriting portfolio, despite having no clients. You can also offer to write for small websites and bloggers for free. The added benefit is that you get valuable feedback on your writing style and skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most copywriters think of their writing skills as a muscle. If it&#39;s not used, it will atrophy. Even when no money is involved, most writers will still write, even if it&#39;s for nobody&#39;s eyes but their own.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you don&#39;t know where to start, here&#39;s a trick made famous by Gary Halbert, one of the world&#39;s best-known copywriters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1.&nbsp; Search for copywriting content that you like</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>What content has stopped you in your tracks? What content made you want to buy, sign up, book an appointment, etc.? Look at your own online behaviour to pick content that persuaded you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Something the best copywriters do is to create a &#39;swipe file&#39; of great copywriting they come across. It&#39;s called a swipe file because it&#39;s the ideal place to &#39;swipe&#39; some inspiration when you&#39;re struck with writer&#39;s block.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Create a folder where you can bookmark great sales pages, landing pages, blog posts or adverts as and when you discover them online. Create a folder in your email inbox to save great emails that made you take action of some sort. All social media platforms have a &#39;save&#39; function where you can save great posts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Within weeks you will have built up a portfolio of fantastic copywriting to inspire you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.&nbsp; Copy the content you find, word for word</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The point of this strategy is that, while you&#39;re copying down the content, you not only learn good copywriting, you keep it long-term. Perhaps you remember revising for exams when you were in school. We bet you couldn&#39;t just read a textbook and expect to do well. In most cases, revising involves writing. The act of writing helps you to remember.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some proponents of this tactic insist on writing copy with pen and paper. Others have reported good results by typing on a keyboard. Whether you write copy or type, either will be much better than simply reading great copywriting and expecting it to sink into your brain.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Find some great copywriting and start writing or typing it, word for word. Set aside an hour a day to do this, and, within weeks, you will have tuned your brain on what is converting, persuasive copywriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dan Kennedy (one of the world&#39;s highest-paid copywriters) has written over 500 sales letters. Of course, this copied content should not go on your public blog or website, if you have one, as you are copying someone else&#39;s work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.&nbsp; Create &#39;better&#39; versions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Try to write better versions of the content you&#39;ve found. How could you have made it even more appealing? Could a punchier email subject line have increased open rates?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It doesn&#39;t matter, at this stage, whether your version is better. Just trying to &#39;outdo&#39; great copywriting hones your skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also showcase this work on your blog or website. You could even do explanation articles with side-by-side comparisons.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the world&#39;s best copywriters with decades of experience still have swipe files. They add any content that inspires them to keep learning and stay at the top of their game.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The above steps are the inside secret on how to become a copywriter with no experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>6) Apply for freelance copywriter jobs</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Now that you have some copywriting skills and a portfolio of work, it&#39;s time to pitch yourself to clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use&nbsp;&lt;NAME OF OUR PLATFORM&gt; to go through all the major job sites and create a list of copywriting job offers that appeal to you. Now, start applying.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is where our earlier advice of niching down into an industry and copywriting form will help you stand out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most writers have CVs that scream &#39;generalist.&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Imagine your chosen industry is finance, and you&#39;re specialising in direct response copywriting. You see an advert for a landing page copywriter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most of your competition will send prospective clients CVs and portfolios with all kinds of work. You can direct them to your blog/website, where you have many landing page examples in the finance sector. Perhaps you&#39;ve even written a blog post on how to increase landing page conversions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Clients are busy people. They don&#39;t want to wade through many applications to find the perfect person. People hire copywriters who can quickly prove they are the right person for the job.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>7) Make a &#39;can&#39;t say no&#39; offer to potential prospects</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your potential clients know they need a good copywriter. But saying yes is difficult. Will this person deliver what I want? How much time will I spend explaining things to them? Will they learn the ropes fast enough? Will I waste money and need to rehire? These are typical questions clients have when they&#39;re hiring a freelance copywriter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To stand head and shoulders above others, make them an offer they can&#39;t refuse by taking this pressure off them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Offer to write the first piece of copy for free. If they need an email marketing copywriter, offer to write an email sequence; if they don&#39;t like it, they don&#39;t have to pay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Who can say no to this? They&#39;re not under any pressure to hire you without checking out what a great freelance copywriter you are. Any fears they have of wasting money, making the wrong choice and needing to rehire, or feeling like an idiot in front of their superiors vanishes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please note. Don&#39;t offer to do huge jobs for free. We&#39;re talking about a small email sequence, a landing page (not a big sales page), etc. Write copy that doesn&#39;t take you a long time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If they say no, it&#39;s no big deal. You got in some copywriting practice, and the results can be used to bolster your portfolio on your own website or blog.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>8) Partner with an influencer</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This little-known tactic can quickly put you ahead of other writers, even writers with far more experience than you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have implemented the earlier steps, you will have determined your target prospect based on your industry/sector and services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now you need to find someone whose audience is full of these prospects. They could have a big following on social media, a high-traffic blog, an active email list, or a popular podcast. In other words, an influencer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get in touch with them by offering to help them with something. Do not ask them for help. Don&#39;t ask them for anything - especially in the first email or message!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most people think that influencers must get a ton of messages every day, and their messages will be ignored. They&#39;re right because most people send messages asking for something. They focus on &#39;what&#39;s in it for them&#39; instead of what the influencer needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Imagine waking up to an inbox full of strangers wanting you to do stuff for them. How would it make you feel? This is a daily reality for influencers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead, stand out by talking about how you can help them. Find out if they have problems that you can solve. Don&#39;t talk about yourself and what you want until they ask you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check out their website, blog, social media presence, etc. Is there something you can improve? Offer to improve it for free.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Join their email list and read their emails. Are there little tweaks you can do to increase conversions? If so, create a fantastic email autoresponder sequence and send it to them without expecting any payment. Or give them a list of great subject lines they can use for future emails.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you can help their blog convert better, or their sales page, homepage, adverts, social media posts, etc., don&#39;t tell them you can do it, just&nbsp;<em>do&nbsp;</em>it. Add value to their business and life without expecting anything in return.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not only will you stand out like a beacon in a sea of &#39;me, me, me&#39; messages, but most influencers will also feel compelled to help you and return the favour. After all, one good deed deserves another.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you are in their good graces, they can introduce you to their audience. Perhaps they can email their list. Or they could interview you on their podcast, write a blog post or collaborate on social media.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to sweeten the pot, you could offer them a small commission for every new client they send your way from their marketing efforts. This will entice them to promote you over and over again.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Email/message example</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Hi &lt;name&gt;,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Love your website/podcast/blog/social media profile, etc. (delete as appropriate)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I particularly liked when you (mention something they said/wrote - this shows you&#39;re not sending a cut-and-paste message).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anyway, I couldn&#39;t help but notice (mention the small problem that you can help them with). I&#39;m a specialist in (your service) in (your industry), and I&#39;m sure I can increase your conversions with a few tweaks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&#39;s what you can do:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(outline in bullets what they need to change - don&#39;t hold back, tell them everything - wow them with your knowledge)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you use one or more of the above, let me know!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have a great day,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(your name)</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>9) Partner with an agency</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Another little-known tactic is to find online marketing agencies that will send you copywriting gigs. If you can partner up with a great one, it could be the speediest way to start your copywriting business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One option is to target dedicated copywriting agencies. However, please be aware that they will already have many agency copywriters on their books. This doesn&#39;t mean you won&#39;t get work from them. If they&#39;re a growing agency, where demand is outstripping capacity, they could still send you lots of work. But you need to be aware that you&#39;re competing with other writers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A cleverer tactic is to find other marketing agencies. They could do search engine optimization, website design, paid ads, social media marketing, etc. It doesn&#39;t matter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The goal is to find agencies with clients that might need your copywriting skills. For example, it&#39;s easy for a web design agency to upsell copywriting to their clients. They&#39;re experts in design and the technical side of websites. They&#39;re not content experts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How to find an agency to partner with</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use Google Maps or another online tool to find all the marketing agencies in your city or region.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Visit their offices to introduce yourself as a freelance copywriter looking for copywriting work. Visiting in person works far better than emailing or cold calling.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Make sure you regularly follow up with each agency.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>This takes a little effort and tenacity. But all it takes is one busy marketing agency to choose you as their copywriter of choice, and you&#39;ll have a flood of regular copywriting gig offers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>10) Network in successful copywriter groups</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There are many online groups dedicated to helping writers meet each other. You&#39;ll find groups on social media, such as Facebook and LinkedIn groups. You can also search for them on Google.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These groups can become a valuable place to pick up tips from more experienced writers. You&#39;ll also find they may post about writing opportunities. Why would they do that?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>First of all, writers are generally a nice bunch of people! But also, when a writer starts to become successful, they&#39;ll receive writing offers they don&#39;t have time to complete. Or they could receive offers that don&#39;t fit their style or niche of writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It makes sense for them to help these clients by finding an alternative writer.</p>', '2023-04-19 04:09:29', '2023-04-19 04:09:29'),
(104, 46, 'How to become a copywriter with no experience - believe in yourself!', '1', 'how-to-become-a-copywriter-with-no-experience-believe-in-yourself', '<h2><strong>How to become a copywriter with no experience - believe in yourself!</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Freelance copywriting isn&#39;t for everyone. You need tenacity and motivation to become a copywriter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A thick skin is a must. You need to handle constructive criticism. See negative feedback as a gift to learn what works. The best copywriters love all feedback because this hones their skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Make a commitment to yourself that you will master copywriting. Then, start going through the above steps, and you&#39;ll see how quickly a copywriter with no experience can succeed!</p>', '2023-04-19 03:59:56', '2023-04-19 03:59:56'),
(105, 54, 'How to Choose the Right Tone of Voice in Writing', '1', 'how-to-choose-the-right-tone-of-voice-in-writing', '<h2><strong>Introduction</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We all have a tone of voice, whether we realize it or not. It&#39;s how we speak to our friends and family members, express ourselves on social media and write emails at work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In short, our voice is who we are. But what exactly is voice? And how can you use your own authentic tone when writing?</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>The definition of tone,</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The dictionary meaning of tone is &quot;the attitude that a writer or speaker conveys.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you read an article about how to set up a home office, for example, you might feel that it&#39;s written in a friendly tone if the author seems happy and enthusiastic about setting up your new workspace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suppose you visit your local coffee shop and order one of their specialty drinks, say an iced caramel latte with two pumps of vanilla syrup and whipped cream drizzled on top. In that case, you&#39;d probably expect something different from the barista than if they were handing over change at the register after buying some gum at the gas station across town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In both cases, the friendly home office post and the welcoming coffee shop interaction, you know what kind of person wrote/said these things just by reading them because they represent different attitudes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One is helpful, while another can be snarky. One wants success, while the other wishes they could take off their shoes and get comfortable before being served dessert.</p>', '2023-04-19 04:11:37', '2023-04-19 04:11:37'),
(106, 54, 'What Is Tone in Writing?', '1', 'what-is-tone-in-writing', '<h2><strong>What Is Tone in Writing?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Tone is the attitude or feeling you convey in your writing. It&rsquo;s the way you sound when you write.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, if I were to say, &ldquo;I saw a movie last night,&rdquo; my tone would be casual and conversational. In contrast, if I wrote something like, &ldquo;Last night I saw a movie that was very entertaining!&rdquo; my tone would be more formal and enthusiastic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tone is an important part of good business writing because it helps establish a connection with readers by understanding how they should feel about what they are reading.</p>', '2023-04-19 04:11:56', '2023-04-19 04:11:56'),
(107, 54, 'Writing Tone vs. Writing Voice', '1', 'writing-tone-vs-writing-voice', '<h2><strong>Writing Tone vs. Writing Voice</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Sometimes, there is confusion between tone and voice, and newbie writers may use both terms interchangeably.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tone is different from voice. Voice refers to the writing style itself; who you are as a person comes through in your choice of words, sentence structure and diction (vocabulary).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Voice is also influenced by your experiences growing up, such as where you grew up, what language was spoken around you at home (if any), and what books were read aloud during childhood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But it doesn&#39;t depend on those factors alone. You can choose how educated or uneducated you want to sound. A word choice like &ldquo;antiquated&rdquo; might make sense for an academic paper on Shakespeare but would seem out of place in an email promoting a sale at a clothing store.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your voice and, therefore, your writing style will change depending on the content or message you share.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, your tone should remain consistent throughout all pieces of content that share the same purpose (for example, if all blog posts are meant to be helpful).</p>', '2023-04-19 04:12:17', '2023-04-19 04:12:17'),
(108, 54, 'How to Choose the Right Tone', '1', 'how-to-choose-the-right-tone', '<h2><strong>How to Choose the Right Tone</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To choose the right tone, you need to know who you&#39;re writing for and what message you want to convey:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Are your readers familiar with the brand you&rsquo;re writing for? If not, do they know about it at all?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>What is the purpose of this piece? Is it informative or persuasive?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Are the readers likely to share it with others after reading it, or are they more likely just read for themselves (as in a blog post)?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2023-04-19 04:12:41', '2023-04-19 04:12:41'),
(109, 54, 'Think About Your Audience', '1', 'think-about-your-audience', '<h2><strong>Think About Your Audience</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The starting point for any piece of creative writing is knowing your audience. Your tone should reflect the expectations and needs of your audience, as well as their interests and values.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get started, you need to consider the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Demographics: Gender, age range, location (city/country), education level etc.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Language: Are they native English speakers or non-native? How is their grammar? What about spelling?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Culture: Do they prefer direct communication versus indirect? Are politics viewed as a conversational taboo, or are they passionate about current events?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2023-04-19 04:13:02', '2023-04-19 04:13:02'),
(110, 54, 'Tailor Tone for Specific Content', '1', 'tailor-tone-for-specific-content', '<h2><strong>Tailor Tone for Specific Content</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You should tailor the tone to the content and audience. The tone can be formal or casual, highbrow or lowbrow, bold or quiet.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s why you might hear an NPR host say something like &ldquo;Hey guys!&rdquo; and then turn around and hear another say, &ldquo;This is NPR News.&rdquo; The first example is more informal, while the second is more formal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regarding what your audience prefers, that depends on who they are (business people might like more professionalism than teenagers).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And remember, it&rsquo;s not just what they want from us. It&rsquo;s also about how much information we want them to digest concerning our goals for the writing we create together.</p>', '2023-04-19 04:13:36', '2023-04-19 04:13:36'),
(111, 54, 'How do I know when I\'ve got the wrong tone?', '1', 'how-do-i-know-when-ive-got-the-wrong-tone', '<h2><strong>How do I know when I&#39;ve got the wrong tone?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There&#39;s no right or wrong when it comes to tone, as the tone of your writing will depend on the piece&#39;s content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re unsure about the tone of your work, try testing out different sentences or paragraphs on friends and family first and ask them to be honest with you. They&rsquo;ll let you know if the tone seems slightly &ldquo;off.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A great way to avoid hitting the wrong tone is to find an emotion that matches the tone of your work. For example, try conveying happiness in your word choice if you&#39;re writing about a happy event.</p>', '2023-04-19 04:13:57', '2023-04-19 04:13:57'),
(112, 54, 'What should I avoid when trying to find the correct tone?', '1', 'what-should-i-avoid-when-trying-to-find-the-correct-tone', '<h2><strong>What should I avoid when trying to find the correct tone?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your audience will connect with you more if they feel like you&#39;re actually talking to them. That means avoiding words and phrases that might make you look arrogant or cocky - this will only make you look bad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead, try to use words and phrases that convey the emotions you feel while writing. For example, if you are writing about someone struggling, try to show their feelings through your writing instead of putting them into perfect words.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lastly, avoid sounding preachy, condescending, or pedantic - these tones will put people off instead of drawing them in.</p>', '2023-04-19 04:14:28', '2023-04-19 04:14:28'),
(113, 54, 'Don\'t get too caught up in trying to find the \"right\" voice or tone', '1', 'dont-get-too-caught-up-in-trying-to-find-the-right-voice-or-tone', '<h2><strong>Don&#39;t get too caught up in trying to find the &quot;right&quot; voice or tone</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Although finding the right tone is important, don&#39;t get too caught up in it. It&#39;s more important to focus on what you want to say and how you want your audience will respond.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Just be yourself.&nbsp; Write with your own voice, use your own words, and be authentic and honest in what you say.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In other words, just write how you would normally talk if someone asked you a question about the topic at hand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And then listen intently for feedback from the audience. That&rsquo;s how you truly learn whether your tone was spot on or off the mark.</p>', '2023-04-19 04:14:39', '2023-04-19 04:14:39'),
(114, 54, 'Use a Consistent Style Guide', '1', 'use-a-consistent-style-guide', '<h2><strong>Use a Consistent Style Guide</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Although not strictly a part of writing tone, a sloppy style can certainly affect tone.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s important to be consistent in how you use punctuation, capitalization, and other elements of grammar.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, don&#39;t capitalize a word unless it&#39;s a proper noun (like &quot;New York City&quot;) or if it is at the beginning of a sentence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You should also avoid using different style guides throughout your work. Instead, choose one and stick with it throughout your writing so that readers can easily follow along from start to finish.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many style guides are available for free online, and some even include samples for inspiration.</p>', '2023-04-19 04:15:11', '2023-04-19 04:15:11'),
(115, 54, 'The copy is a reflection of the brand', '1', 'the-copy-is-a-reflection-of-the-brand', '<h2><strong>The copy is a reflection of the brand</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The tone of your copy should be consistent with what you want your company to look like, sound like, and feel like. Your tone needs to match how people perceive your brand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s also important that all communications align with one another in tone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have an upbeat and fun personality as a business but then write in an overly formal tone in some places, it would confuse people who aren&rsquo;t familiar with your business or industry.</p>', '2023-04-19 04:15:30', '2023-04-19 04:15:30'),
(116, 54, 'Conclusion', '1', 'conclusion-2', '<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The tone in creative writing can be tricky to nail down, but by understanding the different aspects of tone, you&#39;ll find the correct tone for your writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The tone of your writing will reflect the brand&#39;s personality, so it&#39;s important to choose the right one. The best way to find the correct tone is by practicing and getting feedback from your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, remember that all writing has a tone, so don&#39;t get too caught up in trying to find the &quot;right&quot; voice or tone - there isn&#39;t one.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By understanding tone and how to choose the right one for your content, you&#39;ll be well on your way to writing with authority and style.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keep the blog posts coming, and let us know how you go!</p>', '2023-04-19 04:15:52', '2023-04-19 04:15:52'),
(117, 61, 'How to Develop a Proofreading Checklist for Copywriting Projects', '1', 'how-to-develop-a-proofreading-checklist-for-copywriting-projects', '<p>Keen to boost your proofreading game - but need help figuring out where to start? Then this article will discuss the essential features of good proofreading, with a comprehensive checklist, ensuring that your copywriting projects are always accurate and professional.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading is vital for successful marketing and advertising campaigns, and having a comprehensive proofreading checklist to hand ensures accuracy in copywriting projects by double-checking for errors, typos, and grammatical mistakes before publication.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keen to get started? Then read on to learn all you need for the ultimate proofreading checklist.</p>', '2023-04-19 04:28:52', '2023-04-19 04:28:52'),
(118, 61, 'Why Is Proofreading So Important For Copywriting Projects?', '1', 'why-is-proofreading-so-important-for-copywriting-projects', '<h2>Why Is Proofreading So Important For Copywriting Projects?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading is an essential step in copywriting to ensure accuracy in your work, and eliminate errors that could impact the perception of your business or brand. It also helps to ensure that the final product meets the brief requirements and effectively communicates all key messages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading also plays an important role in ensuring that the quality of the writing is consistently high, and that any errors or typos have been identified and rectified.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Having a proofreading checklist can help you to maintain quality control, and ensure that no mistakes slip through the cracks. It also helps to build trust with your clients or employer, as they can be confident that the copy you are providing is accurate and of a high quality.</p>', '2023-04-19 04:30:29', '2023-04-19 04:30:29'),
(119, 61, 'The Ultimate Proofreading Checklist and Key Facts', '1', 'the-ultimate-proofreading-checklist', '<h2>The Ultimate Proofreading Checklist</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We all know how important good proofreading is to the overall success and quality of a piece of copywriting - but how do you know you have covered all your bases? Well, we have put together the ultimate proofreading <a href=\"https://demo91.co.in/dev/affiliatecontent/public/\">checklist </a>for you to use on all your copywriting projects:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1.&nbsp; Read The Piece</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It may sound obvious, but the first step in any proofreading checklist should always be to read the copy through. When reading, make sure to check for any obvious errors in grammar and punctuation, typos, factual inaccuracies or discrepancies, as well as make sure all key messages are communicated correctly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It can be helpful to read out loud - this will allow you to easily pick up on any errors that your eyes may have missed and will let you hear the sentences and phrasing to make sure that it reads well and makes sense. Remember that copywriting isn&#39;t just about accuracy, but also about making sure the copy is engaging and effective.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2.&nbsp; Check for Consistency</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The next step in your proofreading checklist should be to check for consistency throughout the piece. This means checking that all brand names, company titles, dates and numbers are consistent throughout the text and that any images used in the piece are of a good quality.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3.&nbsp; Check For Spelling and Grammar Errors</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have read the piece and checked for consistency, it&#39;s time to double-check for any spelling or grammar errors. This means using a reliable spell-checker such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly </a>or <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor to </a>pick up on any mistakes that you may have missed, as this can make a huge difference to the overall quality of the piece.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also use tools such as UK vs US Spelling to ensure that you are writing in the preferred language, or the Guardian and Observer Style Guide if your work requires a certain, specific style.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4.&nbsp; Check The Copy Against The Brief</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Another important step during the copywriting process is to check the copy against the brief. This means making sure that all key messages are communicated correctly, and that the copy meets all the requirements set out in the brief. If there are any discrepancies or changes needed, these should be noted and highlighted prior to submitting the copy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>5.&nbsp; Check Your Links</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The next step is to check your links - this means ensuring that all links in the copy are functioning correctly and are taking readers to the correct page. It&#39;s important to double-check this before submitting, as any broken or incorrect links can have a negative impact on the overall effectiveness of the piece.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You should also check that the anchor text you have chosen for your link is accurate, relevant, and flows well with the rest of the piece.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>6.&nbsp; Check Your Formatting</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The next step in your proofreading checklist should be to check the formatting. This means making sure that all headings, fonts, margins and spacing are consistent throughout the piece, as this can have a huge impact on the readability of the copy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As mentioned, return to the brief at this point and check whether there are any specific formatting requirements or guidelines that you need to adhere to - you can also use tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/titlecase\">TitleCase</a> to double-check the titles and headings.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>7.&nbsp; Read with Fresh Eyes</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Even after reading the piece multiple times, our eyes can become accustomed to seeing errors, typos or discrepancies that we may have missed the first time around. The best way to ensure accuracy is to read through the copy again with fresh eyes, preferably at least one day later. This will allow you to check it from a different perspective and pick up on any errors you may have overlooked.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 07:58:52', '2023-05-08 07:58:52'),
(120, 60, 'The Impact of Content Strategy on SEO Copywriting', '1', 'the-impact-of-content-strategy-on-seo-copywriting', '<p>Content strategy and SEO copywriting are two of the most important aspects of digital marketing success; they are the foundation upon which any successful online marketing campaign is built.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But just why are these so important, and what difference can a good content strategy have on the effectiveness of SEO copywriting? We took a look at some of the key points to consider and give you a better understanding of the importance of content strategy, what it includes, and just why your business needs it.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-19 05:36:58', '2023-04-19 05:36:58'),
(121, 60, 'Content Strategy – What Is It?', '1', 'content-strategy-what-is-it', '<h2>Content Strategy &ndash; What Is It?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Content strategy is essentially the process of planning, creating, and managing content in order to achieve specific goals. This content can be anything from blog posts, articles, images, videos, webinars and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In short, content strategy involves researching and understanding your target audience, their preferences and how they interact with content. This enables you to create content that is tailored to their needs and interests, thus making it more engaging. A good content strategy also ensures that your content is aligned with your overall business objectives and goals so that it contributes to the success of your marketing campaign.</p>', '2023-04-19 05:37:25', '2023-04-19 05:37:25'),
(122, 60, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact-4', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>73% of B2B marketers and 70% of B2C marketers use content marketing as part of their overall marketing strategy - if you want to be successful in SEO, your content strategy needs to be effective.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 08:22:57', '2023-05-08 08:22:57'),
(123, 60, 'Key elements of a successful content strategy', '1', 'key-elements-of-a-successful-content-strategy', '<h2>Key elements of a successful content strategy</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the key elements of a successful content strategy include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Identifying Your Audience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Understanding who you are targeting is key to creating content that resonates with them. What interests and motivates your target audience? What type of content do they prefer? Answering these questions helps you create content tailored to their needs and interests.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Make the most of tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/google-trends\">Google Trends</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/ubersuggest\">UberSuggest</a> and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/also-asked\">Also Asked</a> to attain an up-to-date overview of just what people are searching for within your industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating Engaging Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you understand your target audience, you can start creating engaging content. This includes original blog posts, videos, images, podcasts and more. You should also ensure your content is accessible and easy to consume &ndash; for example, by making use of short paragraphs and lists.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Optimising for SEO</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating content is just the start; you must ensure it gets seen. SEO stands for Search Engine Optimization, and it is an essential part of any successful digital marketing campaign. The goal of SEO is to increase your website&rsquo;s visibility and rankings in major search engines such as Google and Bing. This can be achieved by optimising various aspects of your website, including content, links and page load times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SEO copywriting involves writing content with the intention of getting it to rank higher in search engine results pages. The process involves conducting research to identify relevant keywords, optimising titles and meta descriptions for each post, and adhering to established SEO guidelines. Tools like <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/semrush\">SEMRush</a> and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/surfer-seo\">Surfer SEO</a> are useful for this - they can take care of the process and ensure that you have the best chance of ranking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Incorporating a content strategy into your SEO copywriting can result in content that is customised to your intended audience and optimised for search engine rankings. With these elements in place, you have a better chance of standing out from the competition, driving more traffic to your website, and ultimately helping your business reach its goals.</p>', '2023-04-19 05:41:40', '2023-04-19 05:41:40');
INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(124, 60, 'The Impact of Content Strategy on SEO Copywriting', '1', 'the-impact-of-content-strategy-on-seo-copywriting-2', '<h2>The Impact of Content Strategy on SEO Copywriting</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Content strategy is an important factor in creating effective SEO copywriting, and it can make significant differences in the outcome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By utilising a content strategy when creating your SEO copy, you can maximise the effectiveness of your efforts and improve your rankings in search engine results pages. Here are some of the key benefits:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating Quality Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A well-developed content strategy involves producing high-quality content that captures the attention of your intended audience. This makes it more likely for your content to be shared and for people to link back to it, which helps boost your SEO rankings.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Finding Your Niche</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A content strategy can be helpful in identifying gaps in the market when creating content. By creating content to fill in these gaps, your posts can become more appealing to search engines and enhance your rankings.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Optimising for Keywords</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As we mentioned, identifying relevant keywords to include in your content is essential for SEO success. Content strategy helps you research which keywords are most popular and effective, thus enabling you to focus on using them in your copywriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A good content strategy should also include finding ways to incorporate keywords into your content to make them more natural and less obvious.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Analysing and Tracking Results</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To ensure effective digital marketing, it is necessary to not only produce high-quality content and optimise for search engines but also evaluate and monitor the outcomes of your endeavours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This process assists in determining the effectiveness of content and identifying areas for potential improvement. You can use analytics tools such as Google Analytics to measure the success of your SEO copywriting campaigns and make adjustments accordingly.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Increased Visibility</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Content that is created with an effective strategy has a higher chance of being seen by both users and search engines. This results in increased website visitors, leading to improved visibility and rankings.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Higher Rankings</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Content that is strategically created and optimised for SEO has a higher chance of being noticed by search engines and ranking well in search results pages. As a result, there is a rise in exposure and footfall, ultimately contributing to the expansion of your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Better Engagement</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Content created with an effective content strategy is more likely to be interesting and engaging to readers, which leads to better user engagement. This can lead to more shares and comments, which can help further boost your SEO rankings.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating a Solid Strategy</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To create a successful content strategy, you need to research, analyse, and plan. Researching popular topics with your target audience can help you create resonating content while analysing the competition and their keywords can determine which terms to focus on. In addition, identifying your target audience and keywords is a crucial element of your strategy, and can help you plan your content creation and optimise it for SEO.</p>', '2023-05-08 11:57:06', '2023-05-08 11:57:06'),
(125, 60, 'Case Study', '3', 'case-study-2', '<h2>Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A case study involving a retail clothing store was conducted to analyze the impact of content strategy on SEO copywriting. The store aimed to enhance their website rankings and boost traffic to their online store.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As part of their content strategy, they began by researching and analyzing popular trends and competitors to identify relevant keywords for their SEO copywriting. Several keywords related to their clothing items were identified from this research.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They formulated a content plan that involved producing high-quality blog articles and product descriptions incorporating the targeted keywords in a seamless manner and worked to integrate keyword-rich meta descriptions and title tags into their web pages. Finally, they set up tracking tools such as Google Analytics to monitor the progress of their efforts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Within a few months, the store noticed a significant increase in their website rankings and more traffic to their online store. After six months, they had achieved a 30% increase in organic search traffic, which translated into increased sales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This case study demonstrates the impact that an effective content strategy can have on SEO copywriting. By understanding their target audience and leveraging keywords correctly, this retail store was able to improve their website rankings and attract more customers.</p>', '2023-05-08 11:57:55', '2023-05-08 11:57:55'),
(126, 60, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact-5', '<h2>Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>54% of businesses will increase their content marketing budgets in 2023 - it is crucial that businesses continue to invest in their content strategies if they want to rank higher in the search engine results pages.</p>', '2023-05-08 08:24:22', '2023-05-08 08:24:22'),
(127, 60, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-2', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Overall, an effective content strategy is essential for successful SEO copywriting. By understanding what makes good SEO copy, you can create content that is tailored to your target audience and optimised for search engine rankings. Implementing this strategy can potentially increase visibility, generate more website visits, and ultimately aid in achieving both short and long-term business objectives.</p>', '2023-04-19 05:52:19', '2023-04-19 05:52:19'),
(128, 58, 'The Ultimate Guide to Productivity Tools for Copywriting', '1', 'the-ultimate-guide-to-productivity-tools-for-copywriting', '<p>Are you a copywriter looking for ways to increase your productivity? Are you feeling overwhelmed by trying to find the right tools to make your job easier? Look no further!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This guide provides an in-depth look at the best <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool\">productivity tools</a> available for any copywriter. From task-management apps to content libraries, you&#39;ll find everything you need to become a more efficient and successful copywriter.</p>', '2023-04-19 05:54:14', '2023-04-19 05:54:14'),
(129, 58, 'What Is Copywriting?', '1', 'what-is-copywriting', '<h2>What Is Copywriting?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting involves creating written content that aims to persuade readers to take a certain action; this could be buying a product, or trying a service. It is commonly utilised in marketing and advertising campaigns and requires the use of storytelling techniques to be effective. In many cases, copywriters may also produce content for various mediums such as websites, blogs, and printed materials.</p>', '2023-04-19 05:54:34', '2023-04-19 05:54:34'),
(130, 58, 'What Skills Do Copywriters Need?', '1', 'what-skills-do-copywriters-need', '<h2>What Skills Do Copywriters Need?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to excel as a copywriter, you may find it helpful to possess a variety of skills, including:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Excellent Writing Skills</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriters require strong writing and editing abilities to allow them to effectively communicate with their intended audience, and produce compelling and engaging content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creative Thinking</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriters need to be creative and possess a skill set that enables them to generate fresh ideas and develop concepts, ensuring that their work remains unique, engaging and exciting for readers and audiences.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Research Skills</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Effective copywriters will be able to make the most of research techniques to identify their target audience, and be able to then source and reference credible information accurately, and in the correct format where necessary. Making the most of tools such as Google Scholar and Lexis Nexis can aid in locating relevant articles, books, and studies for use as references in writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Time Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Efficient management of resources is crucial for meeting deadlines in copywriting, which can be a time-consuming process. Time-tracking tools like <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/stayfocused\" target=\"_blank\">Stay Focused</a> and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/rescuetime\" target=\"_blank\">RescueTime</a> can aid in monitoring task-specific time allocation, allowing you to stay on top of your workload and meet all your deadlines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Proofreading</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading is an important step in the copywriting process, and tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\" target=\"_blank\">Grammarly</a> and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\" target=\"_blank\">Hemingway Edito</a><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\" target=\"_blank\">r</a> can help you identify any mistakes or typos before submitting your work - this will ensure that your copy is error-free.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Analytical Skills</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriters are required to analyse data, interpret trends, and provide recommendations based on their findings, in order to develop copy that is more impactful and resonates with the target audience. This means that you not only need to be able to find information but also to analyse and interpret it accurately to use in your work.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Marketing Knowledge</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Having a fundamental grasp of marketing principles and strategies is crucial for copywriters to create optimised copy for SEO and other marketing objectives.</p>', '2023-04-19 05:55:18', '2023-04-19 05:55:18'),
(131, 58, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact-6', '<h2>Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Studies show that 74% of all readers will notice any spelling or grammatical errors that are left in your copy after it is published - avoid embarrassment by investing in the best proofreading tools.</p>', '2023-05-08 12:10:10', '2023-05-08 12:10:10'),
(132, 58, 'What Are Copywriting Tools?', '1', 'what-are-copywriting-tools', '<h2>What Are Copywriting Tools?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/blog/category/copywriting-skills/productivity-tools\">Copywriting tools</a> are valuable resources that can enhance a copywriter&#39;s work by providing task tracking, document organisation, content library creation, client collaboration, and other helpful features. Making the most of these tools can increase efficiency and productivity, allowing more time to be devoted to producing persuasive copy that resonates with the intended audience.</p>', '2023-04-19 05:56:13', '2023-04-19 05:56:13'),
(133, 58, 'The Best Tools For Copywriters', '1', 'the-best-tools-for-copywriters', '<h2>The Best Tools For Copywriters</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating an organised and efficient work environment can enhance productivity for copywriters. Various productivity tools are available to manage tasks, store documents, and collaborate with others. To ensure that your work is of the highest quality, here are some recommended tools to consider.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/evernote\" target=\"_blank\">Evernote</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The task-management app allows for the efficient organisation of tasks, notes, and ideas across multiple devices through synchronisation. You can work from anywhere in the world, and ensure that projects are always up-to-date and ready for collaboration.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Google Docs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This word-processing program operates in the cloud, and enables real-time collaboration with colleagues and clients, making it easier to share notes and updates wherever you are in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/trello\" target=\"_blank\">Trello</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This popular project management tool enables the division of key tasks into smaller units, as well as allowing users to monitor progress, making it easier to keep track of and manage projects.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Grammarly</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Grammarly is a comprehensive spelling and grammar checker that will ensure all your pieces are accurate and well-written, allowing your work to appear professional and accurate.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Content Libraries</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To save time when writing copy, many copywriters make use of content libraries like Unsplash, Pexels, or <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/canva\" target=\"_blank\">Canva</a>. These libraries provide free images and graphics that can be used in your projects.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/titlecase\" target=\"_blank\">TitleCase</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In some cases, you may have a project which requires very specific formatting. Title Case is a useful tool that helps you convert sentences into the correct capitalization format.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/semrush-writing-assistant\" target=\"_blank\">SEMrush Writing Assistant</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This AI-powered tool can help you optimise your copy for SEO and make sure that it&#39;s keyword-rich - a very important consideration if you are looking to rank highly in search engine results pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/readable\" target=\"_blank\">Readable</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This readability testing tool allows you to quickly check if your text is easy to comprehend. You can even set specific goals such as grade level or target audience to tailor your writing to a specific audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/reedsy\" target=\"_blank\">Reedsy</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a great resource that can help you to find rhymes, quotations and homophones to use in your work - perfect for poets and lyricists.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/seo-powersuite\" target=\"_blank\">SEO Powersuite</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This comprehensive SEO tool helps you to track your rankings, optimise content for keywords, and identify weak spots on your website. It&#39;s an invaluable asset for any copywriter looking to rank highly in search engine results pages.</p>', '2023-04-19 06:03:22', '2023-04-19 06:03:22'),
(134, 58, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact-7', '<h2>Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>According to experts, most readers only consume around 20% of all information that is included on a page - if your article or post is not easy to read and scan, you are more likely to lose the attention of your reader.</p>', '2023-05-08 12:13:18', '2023-05-08 12:13:18'),
(135, 58, 'What Are The Benefits of Using These Tools?', '1', 'what-are-the-benefits-of-using-these-tools', '<h2>What Are The Benefits of Using These Tools?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are a number of benefits to using copywriting tools, and these include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Organise Projects</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Project management tools like Trello and Asana enable users to divide tasks into smaller components and monitor their progress, promoting organisation and productivity during the copywriting process. This allows work to be completed promptly and effectively, making it easier to meet deadlines and manage projects.</p>', '2023-04-19 06:12:40', '2023-04-19 06:12:40'),
(136, 58, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-3', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>During a significant project which incorporated multiple participants working from every corner of the planet, it became clear to the project manager that things were slowly spiralling out of control. Documents were being mislabelled and misplaced, deadlines were being ignored, and key elements of briefs and important information were being missed - and all directly due to poor communication.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By adding Trello to the team, things changed overnight. Projects could be organised in tables, deadlines set and highlighted, and files shared and stored in a single, secure location that was accessible to each and every team member. Peace was restored, stress levels returned to something approaching normal, and a calm victory settled over the writers. At long last, the project was at peace.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 12:15:09', '2023-05-08 12:15:09'),
(137, 57, 'How to Use the 8-Step Writing Process', '1', 'how-to-use-the-8-step-writing-process', '<p>Sometimes, writing can feel like a chore. But there&#39;s no reason for it to be.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The reason writing can feel like a chore is that you don&#39;t have a step-by-step process. When there is no logical order to your own writing, it can feel like waiting for inspiration to strike - disconcerting when you have deadlines to meet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, what trips many people up is they have no structure or process. They subconsciously attempt two or more steps of the writing process simultaneously - a recipe for disaster.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this guide, I&#39;ll walk you through the eight stages of the writing process and how to separate them from each other for optimal results. This is guaranteed to make your writing more effective and enjoyable!</p>', '2023-04-19 06:48:16', '2023-04-19 06:48:16'),
(138, 57, 'Make your writing more effective and enjoyable', '1', 'make-your-writing-more-effective-and-enjoyable', '<h2>Make your writing more effective and enjoyable with these steps!</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Step 1: Start with brainstorming</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The first step in the writing process is brainstorming. Start writing down any ideas that come to you. It&#39;s very important not to edit or censor your thoughts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may have heard the phrase, &quot;The only stupid question is the question that is never asked.&quot; This attitude is used in brainstorming sessions in forward-thinking businesses because self-censoring or self-editing could mean great questions or ideas are left unsaid.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fostering an environment where nothing is wrong and everyone feels encouraged to say whatever is on their mind means these businesses get the best ideas for products, services, improvements, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You need to adopt the same approach. There is no stupid idea, thought, or question at this stage of the writing process. Make a note of whatever comes to mind.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you find your mind is quicker than you can type or write (it often is) and you&#39;re worried you&#39;ll lose some thoughts before jotting down, use voice-activated note-taking apps or transcription apps, such as&nbsp;<a href=\"http://otter.ai/\" target=\"_blank\">Otter.ai</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Step 2: Organize the topics your brainstormed (pre-writing)</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The next step in the writing process is about organizing your ideas into a logical order. The human brain does not think linearly. It tends to &#39;spark&#39; in different directions. It&#39;s why mind mapping was invented, as it mimics how a human brain thinks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, when it comes to writing, no matter how short or long a piece is, you need to organize it sequentially so it&#39;s easy for readers to follow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Go through your list of brainstormed topics and work out the order they would naturally come in your piece.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Step 3: Research your topics</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This step in the writing process is about gathering information from various sources. This information-gathering stage is sometimes called pre-writing, and it helps you narrow down the list of topics you brainstormed before moving forward with drafting your writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be successful at this stage, consider these questions: What exactly do I want my readers to know? Who are my intended audience members? How can I best communicate my ideas in my writing so they&#39;re understandable and helpful?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If there&#39;s a specific question at hand (e.g., &quot;Why do people use social media?&quot;), it may also be helpful to find out where other writers have looked into similar topics so they can give their take on them (e.g., &quot;What does Sally say about Facebook?&quot;).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This type of research is called secondary research because it involves looking into other people&rsquo;s work instead of primary sources such as original documents or interviews with experts who have knowledge about what we&rsquo;re studying.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s also important not to forget the breadth of sources available. Some helpful examples are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>academic journals (which contain peer-reviewed articles written by experts)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>websites maintained by organizations dedicated specifically to scientific inquiry (like NASA)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>newspaper articles written by journalists working at respected news outlets like The New York Times, Wall Street Journal, etc.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The point is there&#39;s no shortage of information at your fingertips. The opposite is true. With super fast internet, we have a world of information, almost too much information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trick is to allot a certain amount of time to research. Otherwise, you risk &#39;going down the rabbit hole,&#39; losing hours (very easily done) without you accomplishing much writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Spend a few minutes researching each topic you brainstormed to see if it&#39;s worthwhile to include, and if so, gather information about that topic.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Step 4: Plan your structure and outline</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Not that you&#39;ve removed irrelevant topics and fleshed out the remaining topics, the next step in the writing process is to create an outline of your content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An outline lets readers follow along with what you&#39;re saying while they read, which makes your writing easier to read and more enjoyable for them (and keeps them from getting lost).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It also gives you a clear idea of what topics need more explanation or support so that later on, you know where improvements are needed when it&#39;s time for revision.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A great structure for any length of writing to follow is:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Introduction</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Introduce your &#39;why&#39; of your piece. Why are you here? What are you going to talk about? For example, &quot;As Gen Z spends up to 6 hours a day on TikTok, is this video-sharing site a creative outlet or damaging mental health?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s all about &#39;setting out your stall&#39; - grabbing your readers&#39; attention by telling them exactly what you&#39;ll be discussing and why (and perhaps even the benefits for them)- important if you&#39;re writing something that may induce a sale).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Arguements/sup-topics</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You&#39;ve already organized your topics previously. This is where you list these topics into discrete categories.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, in our Tiktok piece, the first category could be TikTok usage statistics, TikTok history, TikTok revenue, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The second category could be stories and quotes from people who use TikTok and love it for allowing a creative outlet, finding new friends and a sense of community, learning new ideas, positive statistics, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The third category could be mental health statistics regarding social media and young people, stories and quotes from people adversely affected by TikTok, etc. And so on.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Conclusion</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There&#39;s nothing worse than a piece of writing that ends abruptly (think about how you feel when a film ends like this).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Summarise the main points of your writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Depending on the topic and who you&#39;re writing for, you may write the conclusion with a neutral tone so the reader can make up their mind.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Or you could write a conclusion that leaves no doubt about which side you&#39;re on. Follow your client or publisher&#39;s guideline. Sometimes strong opinions are welcome. Other times, neutrality is key.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keep in mind that even though an outline seems set in stone at this point, it will probably change throughout the writing process as new ideas occur or as one topic becomes irrelevant after another develops further during drafting or revision (which we&#39;ll cover later).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This can be frustrating if it means going back and changing everything again&mdash;but don&#39;t worry! If necessary, we&#39;ll show how easy it is once everything you&rsquo;ve written everything out. Just keep going until then.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use numbers/bullets instead of long sentences when describing each paragraph. This makes it easier for readers to scan quickly since they don&#39;t need all those details immediately but want some sense of what topics you&rsquo;re discussing within each section before diving deeper into reading specific paragraphs themselves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This can also help with keeping track of what you&#39;ve said in the outline if you need to look back on it later (which we highly recommend doing). Finally, using numbers/bullets instead of long sentences will keep your paragraphs shorter and easier for readers to understand.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Step 5: Write the first draft first (don&#39;t stop to edit)</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The next step in the writing process is to begin writing your first draft. This means you don&rsquo;t stop for editing or proofreading during this process. Instead, you should write as quickly as possible without stopping for a set period (sometimes called free writing)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The good news is that because you&#39;ve followed the above steps, you won&#39;t experience what many amateur writers experience, which is racing to get down their ideas and thoughts before they slip away!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Because you&rsquo;ve brainstormed, organized, researched and outlined, you&#39;re at a stage where ideas won&#39;t escape you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, you still want to write the first draft quickly. If it helps, consider it a &lsquo;rough draft,&rsquo; not the final version you will submit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You don&#39;t want to edit because it slows down the writing process. Avoiding editing will help keep your mind focused on what matters most - developing an argument and conveying it effectively through language use (i.e., word choice). Editing is a step further down the line. Keep the different stages separate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At this drafting stage, focus on getting your main idea across clearly rather than worrying about spelling or grammatical errors or ensuring every detail is correct.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s also important not to worry about the quality of your writing when beginning the first draft. This will only slow progress toward completing the assignment in time for submission requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Focus instead on developing one strong idea per paragraph that relates directly back to your overall topic sentence (which should come right after introductions).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Step 6: Take a break, redraft and revise</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Congratulations! You&#39;ve written your first draft. The next step in the writing process? Set your document aside and let your brain rest for a bit. You&#39;ll be re-reading it with fresh eyes later, so don&#39;t worry if you can&#39;t think of anything else to add at this point.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You&#39;ll also want to reread your first draft with an eye toward larger issues, such as structure and argument (does your writing make sense?) or style (is any of your writing unclear?). Once you&#39;ve done that, check in with yourself.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Does it feel like a strong and cohesive piece? Is there any additional evidence that you could add for support? If so, write those down before adding them to your writing later in this process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, go through each paragraph individually and make revisions based on what needs improvement from an organizational standpoint, stylistic clarity and other problems identified during the editing tasks above.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You might also want to start thinking about what else you could add to your writing, such as figures, tables and other visual aids.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While these can certainly be useful for some readers, they aren&#39;t necessary for all audiences&mdash;especially if the point you are trying to make doesn&#39;t rely on any data presented visually or otherwise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So only use them if they add something to your writing or make your writing clearer and more readily understood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re unsure whether your writing needs figures and tables, try reading it aloud. If it sounds choppy or confusing (or if you have to pause during the reading), then you may need to add some visual aids.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Step 7: Edit for sentence structure and clarity</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The next step of the writing process is editing. This is the process of making sure that your assignment has all the necessary parts:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have you included all the information required for your assignment?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Does a separate title page, abstract, and reference sheet follow a format acceptable to your client or publisher?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have citations been used correctly?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Editing looks at sentence structure and clarity. Proofreading focuses on grammar errors, removing typos and adherence to a style guide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We recommend editing first, then proofreading last because this allows for more flexibility when going through the editing process &ndash; if something needs changing after careful proofreading, you can do it without having to re-edit the whole thing again!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The proofreading stage is a final check that your essay is ready to be handed in. You can do this yourself or ask someone else to look at it.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Step 8: Proofread your final draft</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Now that you&#39;ve made the big changes (editing), we need to focus on proofreading. In this section, we&#39;ll talk about what small errors to look for and how software can help with proofreading.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you send your work out into the world, it&#39;s important to check for those pesky little errors that can make your readers cringe. These include things like sentence fragments and sentence structure issues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Small mistakes like these are easy enough to fix by hand, but if they pile up or are too numerous, they will impede readability and make people question whether they can trust your writing as a whole.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Luckily there are plenty of tools out there that can help with proofreading edits. Grammarly is one option that works well on both web browsers and word-processing software like Google Docs. It does a great job of editing and proofreading and making sure your writing is grammatically correct.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pro Writing Aid also does a good job of flagging common mistakes. Microsoft Office lets you automatically underline spelling mistakes in red so that no one has any excuse not to fix them immediately before hitting publish.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most important thing when proofreading is to read your work out loud. This helps you catch any errors that might not be obvious when reading silently in your head.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you get stuck on a sentence or paragraph, try reading it backward or changing the tense of verbs. This can often help you access new meaning in old text.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you&#39;ve completed this final step, you have your final draft ready to submit.</p>', '2023-04-19 06:55:23', '2023-04-19 06:55:23'),
(140, 57, 'Conclusion', '1', 'conclusion-3', '<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You have your eight steps! Make sure you follow them whether you&#39;re writing a shorts social media post or a huge dissertation. These steps work, period. Let us know how you get on!</p>', '2023-04-19 06:57:31', '2023-04-19 06:57:31'),
(141, 56, 'Top 16 Copywriting Trends for 2023', '1', 'top-16-copywriting-trends-for-2023', '<p>Being ahead of the game when it comes to copywriting will give you an edge over the competition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So here are 16 copywriting trends and content marketing trends for 2023. Once you&rsquo;ve gone through this article, make sure you use this knowledge to your advantage.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you already have particular skills mentioned below, make sure to &lsquo;play them up&rsquo; with potential clients, as you know these will be aspects they&rsquo;re looking for in their next copywriter.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And if you lack certain skills, forewarned is forearmed! Make sure you take steps to upskill so you can meet the copywriting demands in 2023.</p>', '2023-04-19 06:59:16', '2023-04-19 06:59:16'),
(142, 56, 'Steps to upskill to meet the copywriting demands', '1', 'steps-to-upskill-to-meet-the-copywriting-demands', '<h2>Steps to upskill to meet the copywriting demands</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. AI copywriting</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>AI copywriting has been gathering pace in the last few years, and 2023 will be the year when it becomes mainstream. However, there is no need for concern. You&rsquo;re not about to be replaced by super-intelligent cyborgs!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The use of artificial intelligence in copywriting is more for time and energy-saving. While the technology is impressive, it still lacks the &lsquo;human touch.&rsquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Savvy copywriters are using AI copywriting tools to assist them rather than seeing them as something that will replace them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, AI copywriting is fantastic for creating rough drafts, which a writer can polish and add personal touches and flair.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>AI copywriting can also show writers where they can improve copy at a glance. AI copywriting tools to check out&nbsp;<a href=\"http://copy.ai/\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Copy.ai</u></a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://jasper.ai/\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Jasper.ai</u></a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. From copywriter to copywriting consultant</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This trend is a follow-on from the AI copywriting trend. As artificial intelligence becomes smarter and creates a realistic copy, human copywriters will be seen in a more consultative role.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead of &lsquo;doing&rsquo; the copywriting, you will become someone who gives advice and creates frameworks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use knowledge of this trend to your advantage by helping your customers. Ask them what difficulties they have and how copy can solve those problems. How can you help them with their overall content marketing strategy?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Start demonstrating that &lsquo;consultant&rsquo; side of you now to stay ahead.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The &lsquo;doing&rsquo; copywriters will fall by the wayside as AI becomes even more intelligent, but you&rsquo;ll have nothing to worry about as a copywriting consultant.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Interactive content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Chatbots have become the norm as interactive content in the last few years, and in 2023, they&rsquo;re set to become even more popular with advancements such as natural language processing and machine learning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then there&#39;s augmented reality which sounded so futuristic just two to three years ago but is already becoming normal for forward-thinking businesses.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How do you fit into this as a copywriter? It&rsquo;s simple. Interactive content still requires intelligent, well-thought-out content.&nbsp;In fact, tailoring content can require&nbsp;<em>more&nbsp;</em>content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, we&rsquo;re sure you&rsquo;ve had a bad chatbot experience. Yes, some of that experience may be to do with software issues, but a lot of it has to do with bad or no copywriting. &lsquo;Canned&rsquo; responses that don&rsquo;t help a customer or lead them to a dead end are not only a lost opportunity but can also lead to complaints.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Make sure you demonstrate the need for great copy, no matter how futuristic-sounding the technology is. Great content is great content and will always be necessary, no matter the form it comes in.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Copywriting for video</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Video is the most consumed content online and has been for several years., It will be no different in 2023 as it continues to dominate copywriting trends.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Offer video copywriting in the form of scripts and video strategy will become a key tool in your arsenal to attract and keep customers going forward.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scriptwriting for videos will also change depending on the platform. For example, TikTok is known for short-form videos, while YouTube is the king of longer videos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Demonstrating your knowledge of best practices and what converts best on different platforms will earmark you as the copywriter to hire.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you already have skills in this department, let your current clients know by demonstrating your knowledge of whatever platform they use to generate leads.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you don&rsquo;t have video copywriting skills, now is the time to upskill.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Consistent brand tone on all channels</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Another trend gathering pace for a few years is the need for a brand to sound uniform across all channels and platforms.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is great news for you as you can use this knowledge to negotiate bigger projects.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Educate them on why having different writers for blog posts, LinkedIn, web copy, adverts, etc., hurts their conversions and sales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It makes far more sense for one copywriter to handle all the content (or, if that&rsquo;s too much, be the copywriting consultant that manages and delegates to others) to ensure a consistent brand tone.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Webinars</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Webinars continue to be a key content marketing trend that shows no sign of stopping in 2023, and it&rsquo;s understandable why.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Webinars are a great place for businesses to showcase their products and allow their customer to engage with the brand fully.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, many brands don&rsquo;t use webinars because of the time and effort spent on content creation, such as scripts, presentation slides, handouts, promo copy, etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Demonstrate your knowledge in this area to current and prospective customers (and if you don&rsquo;t know, learn it!) They&rsquo;re likely leaving money on the table by not utilizing webinars in their content marketing, and your copywriting could be the key to unlocking these profits.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. Using FAQs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Did you know that 14% of all searches on Google searches start with the word &lsquo;how?&rsquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This means millions of people every day look for answers to their questions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We all know that the aim of all content marketing is to answer those questions. But online attention spans continue to drop, so the average person makes snap judgments about whether your content will give them the answer they&rsquo;re looking for.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is what FAQs are one of the biggest copywriting trends. If someone spots a question that is identical (or almost identical) to the one they&rsquo;ve searched on Google, they&rsquo;re more likely to click on your content than a competitor&rsquo;s.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sadly, a lot of businesses either don&rsquo;t have an FAQ section or see it as somewhere to dump a few general questions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Intelligent business owners keep tabs on what their ideal customers are typing into Google and other search engines and use this to create FAQs that customers actually ask.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And now that you have this vital information, you can also wow your customers by creating FAQs that get them noticed by their potential customers.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>8. Case study-based storytelling</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We don&rsquo;t need to tell you that storytelling is one of the most important things you&rsquo;ll learn to create high-quality content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This trend is all about marrying storytelling with data. Stories are the key to grabbing and keeping the attention from a target audience. However, it&rsquo;s hard facts we want to see when making a buying decision.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Using both is the key to gaining attention that converts into sales.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Create stories based on case studies. Start with the problem a particular customer had and how they tried to find a solution without success.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now enters the product or service in your story. Demonstrate with hard facts and figures how the problem was solved. How did the product or service save or make money, and how much? Or how much time did the product or service save, etc.?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your current clients are not using case study-based storytelling, now is the time to tell them they&rsquo;re missing out!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>9. Repurposing as a content marketing strategy</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Repurposing content is not new, but 2023 will be the year more businesses realize how much content they already have, and it&rsquo;s a more efficient content strategy to repurpose than keep generating new content all the time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The problem? Repurposing does not mean just taking content wholesale from one platform and dumping it into another.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, you wouldn&rsquo;t take a 2,000-word article and send that as an email.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The problem for businesses is that repurposing takes time and effort. That&rsquo;s where you come in.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Demonstrate your understanding of different platforms and best practices for repurposing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, you could tell a client that a 2,000-word article is best summarized into two to three &lsquo;teaser&rsquo; paragraphs for an email and then a link to the original article.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Or you can rewrite the article into &lsquo;episodes&rsquo; to go out via email sequentially.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The benefit for you is that you are creating work for yourself, and the work is relatively easy as there&rsquo;s no research or content creation from scratch involved - just rewriting.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>10. Voice search</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>More and more people have smart speakers, which will change the content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As we go into 2023, how your copy looks will be less important. Instead, how you use words and how they&nbsp;<em>sound&nbsp;</em>in voice search will become more important.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There will likely be a move away from keyword-focused titles and headings. Instead, it would make sense for titles and headings to be framed as sentences that a user would use to ask for something in voice searches.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>11. Copy that works when English is a foreign language</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As we become a global neighborhood, the need for copy that is understood and resonates has become a key content marketing trend.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even within English-speaking countries, there can be huge differences in the context of certain words and phrases.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As more and more companies cater to global audiences, as a copywriter, you need to ensure you write copy that works whether someone speaks British English, US English, or even English as a foreign language.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>12. Long-form copy</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This may be surprising, given the trend for video content. But there appears to be an opposite reaction happening here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As people prefer watching videos, when they do want to read, they prefer well-researched, intelligently-written long-form content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, for social media marketing, the content is getting shorter, but outside of the social media world, it&#39;s getting longer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>13. Podcasts will become even more popular</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>More and more businesses realize how podcasts can generate highly qualified leads from their target audience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When people listen to podcasts, they usually give them their undivided attention. Compare that to social media platforms, where we&rsquo;re constantly distracted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s why leads that come from podcasts are of a higher quality.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So how does this affect you as a copywriter?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many brands and businesses would love to start a podcast but are scared of the time and effort it will take to create content ideas and scripts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That&rsquo;s where you come in! You can help write scripts and episode plans.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not many copywriters have these skills, so make sure you learn to stay ahead of the game.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>14. Email marketing remains king of the digital marketing trends</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Every year, someone will herald the death of emails. And each year, the evidence points to email marketing as the digital marketing trend that generates the highest ROI.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This trend will continue in 2023. If you&rsquo;re a skilled email copywriter, push those skills to the forefront when speaking to potential customers and encourage them to increase their email marketing efforts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And if email copywriting is something you&rsquo;ve never done before, consider upskilling yourself - it will be worth it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>15. Doubling up content as a content marketing strategy</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Many businesses miss opportunities to add other content formats to already existing content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Previous content could be made more attractive, understandable, and even more search-friendly by adding, for example, infographics, custom graphics, or videos.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The more content formats you use, the more chances you have to grab attention.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As with content repurposing, this doubling-up content strategy is a great way to create new projects for your customers that are relatively easy to do as you&rsquo;re using existing content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>16. Updating old content as a content marketing strategy</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Like repurposing content and doubling up content, most business owners forget content they&#39;ve previously posted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regarding Google, the age of a website is very important. The older a website, the more credibility and authority it has.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, it also needs to see that the website is being updated regularly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most business owners assume this means pumping out new content regularly. While they need to do this, they&rsquo;re missing an easier content strategy option right under their noses - updating their old content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Look at expert content marketers such as Hubspot, for example. Many of their articles will have a note saying the original article is from several years ago, but it&rsquo;s been updated for this year.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They do this because they know Google and other search engines will notice the update and boost their articles to higher search results.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use this knowledge when speaking to your customers. As them about previous blog posts, articles, and other content. Tell them you can easily update them with new, relevant information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You could find you&rsquo;ve created a huge, lucrative project if they have an extensive library of previous content!</p>', '2023-04-19 07:02:57', '2023-04-19 07:02:57'),
(143, 56, 'Use these content marketing trends to make 2023 your best year', '1', 'use-these-content-marketing-trends-to-make-2023-your-best-year', '<h2>Use these content marketing trends to make 2023 your best year</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As we said before, forewarned is forearmed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use the above copywriting trends and content marketing trends to inform how you speak to current and potential clients and coordinate their marketing strategies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They will also inform you of any skills gaps you have that you need to plug.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get in touch with us, and let us know how you get on!</p>', '2023-04-19 07:03:25', '2023-04-19 07:03:25'),
(144, 55, 'How to Find Copywriting Clients on Instagram', '1', 'how-to-find-copywriting-clients-on-instagram', '<p>Depending on who you listen to, your Instagram account is either the holy grail for client generation or a complete time suck.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Social media platforms dominate marketing strategies. So it&#39;s understandable if you think you might miss out on ideal clients for your copywriting business by not posting regularly on Instagram.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The truth is, you are!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, that does not mean you stop whatever you&#39;re doing and start making a ton of Instagram stories.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Strategy is everything. Blindly posting on your Instagram account will just take up all your time and energy, with no new freelance clients to show for your efforts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ve put together the ultimate Instagram strategy guaranteed to find clients for your freelance copywriting business.</p>', '2023-04-19 07:08:35', '2023-04-19 07:08:35');
INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(145, 55, 'Your Instagram social media marketing strategy', '1', 'your-instagram-social-media-marketing-strategy', '<h2><strong>Your Instagram social media marketing strategy</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Here is your step-by-step Instagram marketing strategy designed to turn your Instagram account into a magnet for prospective clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>&#39;Brand&#39; your Instagram account</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Instagram does not allow you to change background colors or add customizations. However, you can use your posts to give a &#39;feel&#39; of who you are and what you do.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember, Instagram is a visual social media service. When someone arrives on your profile, they will see a grid of your most recent posts. This differs from the &#39;feed&#39; style of recent posts you see on Facebook or LinkedIn.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Professional Instagram marketers use this to their advantage by setting a &#39;brand voice&#39; early on. This means all posts have the same colors, fonts, etc., so there is a harmonious and professional feel when someone lands on the Instagram profile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Start to see your Instagram profile page as the homepage of a website. Would you think it was professional if you stumbled across a website with no discernable branding and all kinds of colors and fonts?</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Create Instagram content that meets your audience&#39;s needs</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You&#39;d think this would be a given for copywriters, as we spend a lot of time determining audience needs when writing content for our clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And yet, we often miss this when it comes to our own marketing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your ideal client is a small business, creating content about copywriting tips or your copywriting services won&#39;t work. Most small business owners aren&#39;t aware of how a copywriter can solve their problems, such as low sales, stiff competition, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead, focus your content on business growth. All business owners want to grow, no matter how big or small. Educate them on how good copywriting can grow their business.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Create regular content to find clients</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>While each social networking service has differing algorithms, they all agree on one aspect. The more you post, the more the platform will show your posts to others. The Instagram algorithm is no different.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Writing a few posts for a week and then dropping off the radar is a waste of your time and effort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to generate leads from Instagram, you need to dedicate some time to posting regularly, ideally once per day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The good news is as Instagram is a visual social media platform, you don&#39;t have to write much. It&#39;s all about creating eye-catching visuals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have fun with content creation!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you love funny memes and jokes? Do you have some favorite motivating quotes? Your Instagram account is where you can share them as it shows off your personality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, don&#39;t be afraid to &#39;re-use&#39; content elsewhere (make sure you attribute it, so you&#39;re not accused of repurposing other people&#39;s content as your own). This is called content curation, and it&#39;s a great way to save time on creating your own content while still showing off who you are.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Just remember to use your brand voice throughout all your posts.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Use hashtags intelligently</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;ve written SEO content for clients as a copywriter, you&#39;ll know that trying to rank for the highest searched keywords on Google is not a great strategy. There&#39;s usually far too much competition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A more intelligent approach is to use high-intent longtail keywords with lower search volumes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And yet, many writers forget about this when it comes to Instagram.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Using ultra-popular hashtags with millions of mentions will mean your posts get lost in a sea of noise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead, focus on hashtags with a few thousand to under 400k mentions. They&#39;re still popular, but not so crazy popular that you get lost.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Use hashtags that represent you</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is similar to brand voice. There&#39;s more to you than &#39;just&#39; copywriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Perhaps you focus on clients who have sustainable or green goals? Maybe you&#39;re proud of owning a woman-owned business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Find hashtags that represent these aspects of your business. Yes, you need to use hashtags focused on what you do, but it pays to add hashtags that go beyond this and show prospective clients who you are.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The key to long term clients is people resonating with who you are and not just your great copywriting skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Social media marketing is a two-way street</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As copywriters, we&#39;re guilty of seeing social media marketing as a one-way avenue. We create content for our clients, who broadcast it to their audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, social media marketing works in both directions. Savvy copywriters know this as well as savvy business owners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Spend time looking at other people&#39;s Instagram posts, particularly those who could be future copywriting clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Like their posts and, even better, write meaningful comments. It&#39;s easy to hit the like button, but a comment takes time, and your prospective clients will notice the effort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most people&#39;s guards are down on social media, especially somewhere like Instagram.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whereas cold emailing or cold calling puts people in a defensive mode, a comment on an Instagram post by a stranger rarely causes negativity, especially if the comment is positive and meaningful.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Think in terms of friends first and freelance clients second</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you&#39;ve got a potential client&#39;s attention, sending them a direct message is acceptable. Remember, this is not like cold emails or cold calling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, don&#39;t abuse this. As their guard will be down, you don&#39;t want to go directly into &quot;sell, sell, sell!&quot; Doing this will be even worse than getting the brush off when cold calling - at least they were expecting the pitch.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead, think in terms of being a friend, not a salesperson.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get to know your prospective client. How are they doing? Who are they? What&#39;s important to them? Let your conversation flow naturally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trust us. If they enjoy the conversion, you can bet they&#39;ve checked out your Instagram profile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you follow the first and second steps in this Instagram social media marketing strategy, your brand voice and posts will tell them everything they need to know about what you do and how they can benefit.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Show off your writing prowess</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, Instagram is a visual social media platform, so do not write long blog posts or huge press release-style posts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, you&#39;re a copywriter. You can bet your potential clients will judge your words on your Instagram posts. After all, if you knew someone was a photographer, you&#39;d check out the quality of their photos, correct?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Think of your Instagram posts as a mini portfolio of your work. Yes, you can&rsquo;t show off long-form writing style, but you can certainly show off short-form and medium-form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use your posts to show how intelligently you can write captions and how engaging you can make your posts. Your potential clients will notice and want the same for their marketing.</p>', '2023-04-19 07:14:52', '2023-04-19 07:14:52'),
(146, 55, 'Finding copywriting clients on Instagram', '1', 'finding-copywriting-clients-on-instagram', '<h2><strong>Finding copywriting clients on Instagram</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There&#39;s no quick fix when it comes to finding clients on Instagram. However, there&#39;s no quick fix for finding copywriting clients anywhere!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The key is to pick one or two lead-generating strategies and spend time nurturing them. This will yield far better results than trying all kinds of strategies and spreading yourself thin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;ve chosen Instagram as one of your main lead-generating strategies, following the above steps over a few months is guaranteed to get you clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please do let us know your Instagram client-generating success stories!</p>', '2023-04-19 07:15:15', '2023-04-19 07:15:15'),
(147, 51, 'What is the AIDA Copywriting Formula?', '1', 'what-is-the-aida-copywriting-formula', '<p>Have you ever tried to bake a delicious cake to impress your guests without a specific recipe?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s the same with copywriting. It&#39;s difficult without a tried and tested formula at hand. AIDA is a well-known formula that has been used repeatedly with proven success.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What is AIDA?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>AIDA is a century-old copywriting formula widely used by writers to convert visitors into paying customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>AIDA stands for Attention, Interest, Desire, and Action, the four stages of the customer purchase process. Think of these stages as the different stages of interaction customers have with a product or service before they finally become buyers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>The four stages of the AIDA formula are:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Attention - Create attention by creating awareness about your product or service.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Interest - Foster interest in your product or service by connecting with the reader.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Desire - Create desire for your product by highlighting the benefits of the product or service.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Action - Compel your audience to take buying action.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>AIDA is one of the most simple copywriting formulas used by marketers, salespeople, and advertisers, to engage, attract and convert leads into clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The AIDA model can be easily adapted to suit different marketing channels, such as email marketing, sales letter, digital marketing, and social media platforms.</p>', '2023-04-19 07:19:56', '2023-04-19 07:19:56'),
(148, 51, 'Why is AIDA important as a marketing formula?', '1', 'why-is-aida-important-as-a-marketing-formula', '<h2><strong>Why is AIDA important as a marketing formula?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>AIDA is an elegant formula. It forces you to understand the prospect or potential customer and their motivation for buying. When you know the prospect&#39;s desires, needs and wants, you can successfully encourage them to buy your product or service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It also goes through the natural process we all go through when we want to purchase something. We all become aware of a product or service (attention) but have little interest because we&#39;re unsure whether it&#39;s for &#39;people like me.&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then become interested in the product or service when we see or hear marketing that talks to our desires, needs and wants, which makes us feel that this is something for us (the interest stage).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We start to want the product or service (desire) when we see or hear anything that highlights the benefits of having it in our lives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, we become buyers when we receive a compelling call to action that asks us to buy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you write using the AIDA model, you write copy that hits all stages of the customer purchase process. Missing just one stage completely damages the journey.</p>', '2023-04-19 07:21:01', '2023-04-19 07:21:01'),
(149, 51, 'AIDA copywriting formula best practices', '1', 'aida-copywriting-formula-best-practices', '<h2><strong>AIDA copywriting formula best practices</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are some tips for success in your marketing efforts using the AIDA formula.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1) Write a compelling headline&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>What do you see first when you see an ad? The headline, of course! Creating a great headline hooks your reader into reading through your blog post (the attention stage of AIDA).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If nobody reads your copy, nobody buys your product. It&#39;s as simple as that. 80% of readers don&#39;t move past the headline, so you can&#39;t get to generate their interest, create desire and then compel them to take action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some strategies to craft a great headline are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Make it urgent</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>When your headline conveys a sense of urgency, it implies that if the reader does not take action immediately, they will lose out on something special.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This can improve the click-through rate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Example: 5 amazing makeup trends you are not aware of!</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Quote specific numbers</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A specific headline grabs more attention. Imagine a headline that is &#39;How to lose weight!&#39; Now, compare that to How to lose 8kg in 30 days!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Adding &#39;8kg&#39; and &#39;30 days&#39; is more attention-grabbing as it arouses curiosity. A reader will think, &quot;Is it possible to lose that weight in just 30 days? How?&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It also adds credibility. Facts are specific. Lies are vague.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Example: How I made $10,000 per month from writing sales copy.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Speak directly to your audience</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Know who your audience is and target it precisely. Mention the people you are writing for directly in the headline. Make them think, &quot;This is for me!&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Example: Become a content marketing manager in just 6 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Bring on the emotion</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Supercharge your copy with emotion. Remember, the buying process is an emotional one. Get people&rsquo;s attention by using emotion-filled words and phrases.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Example: Powerful stress-busting tips you need to know</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>2) Speak directly to your buyer persona</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your target audience should feel that you are speaking directly to them throughout the copy, especially in the opening paragraph. You should use &lsquo;you&rsquo; and &lsquo;your&rsquo; in your marketing language.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This makes your prospects feel that you are paying special attention to them. For example, if your target buyer persona is a marketing manager, address your title to them personally.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>3) Use style elements</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Style elements like underlining, italics, and bold help certain ideas in your marketing copy to stand out. It&#39;s important to remember that prospects are not just attracted by how a copy reads but also how it looks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Styling it with different style elements helps it to stand out and drive the message home. But at the same time, don&#39;t overwhelm your viewer with over-styling. Use style elements only when it is appropriate. Ideally, you want to use them when mentioning anything that makes a reader think, &quot;That&#39;s me!&quot; (the interest stage of AIDA) or how the product or service will benefit them (the desire stage of AIDA).</p>', '2023-04-19 07:21:40', '2023-04-19 07:21:40'),
(150, 51, 'The AIDA copywriting formula broken down', '1', 'the-aida-copywriting-formula-broken-down', '<h2><strong>The AIDA copywriting formula broken down</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The above best practices are a quickstart guide. If you want to perfect your AIDA understanding to write the absolute best copy, stick around to get step-by-step instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Attract attention</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>It is just like wooing a partner. You need to have a great pickup line, or a hook, to reel your prospect in. Remember, you&#39;re competing with hundreds of similar sites.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For blogs and articles, the hook is the headline. For emails, they are the subject lines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you write a headline, you first need to understand the buyer&#39;s needs. Research your customer&#39;s background, motivation, demographics, job profiles, etc. Understand why they will be interested in buying the product or service.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Do:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Direct, actionable language is the best policy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use emotional words to create powerful copy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A great idea is to encourage a response by asking questions.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Make your copy relevant to your target market.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Don&rsquo;t:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Don&rsquo;t fake your expertise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Avoid capslocks or using too many style settings. Let your content speak for itself.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Don&rsquo;t use spammy words and cliches like &lsquo;free&rsquo; or &lsquo;urgent.&rsquo;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Create Interest</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have caught your audience&#39;s attention, the more difficult task is to inspire their interest in your product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The longer they stick around, the more they&#39;re likely to move to the desire stage and then the action stage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another advantage is that the longer a reader sticks around, it signals to Google that your content is interesting and relevant, which means the content ranks higher on Google search results.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Do:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Personalize your content to connect with readers so they think, &quot;This is for me.&quot;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Promise a solution to their problem.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Show them that you understand their needs and wants.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use industry terms and speak their language.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Don&rsquo;t:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Don&rsquo;t overwhelm viewers with a lengthy, complicated copy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Don&rsquo;t add irrelevant content (this can only happen if you don&#39;t know your audience).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Don&rsquo;t focus on your own goals and benefits. Focus on the reader&#39;s goals and benefits.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Create Desire</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you create interest in your customer for your content, you can generate the desire to buy your service or product. Generating desire is the cornerstone of effective copywriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Do:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tell them your offer (no one likes &#39;blind&#39; copy).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pitch the benefits of your offer (not just the features).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Show them how you are unique from others.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Increase your credibility by highlighting demonstrative examples or testimonials.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Don&rsquo;t:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Don&#39;t go overboard with promotion.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Don&#39;t bury your offer by writing too much content.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Call to Action (CTA)</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the final stage! Your call to action should be clear and concise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tell your potential lead exactly what they need to do. Anything wishy-washy, and you&#39;ll lose momentum and lose the sale.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Do:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clearly outline the CTA steps.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reduce &#39;buyer&#39;s remorse&#39; friction by using encouraging language.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Make their job of taking action as easy as possible (i.e., don&#39;t have lots of hoops they need to jump through just to buy).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Don&#39;t:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Don&rsquo;t use vague directions (&#39;click on the button directly below&#39; will convert far more than &#39;click&#39; - what should they click?)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Don&#39;t pile on too many call-to-action options as you risk choice paralysis.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>', '2023-04-19 07:24:10', '2023-04-19 07:24:10'),
(151, 51, 'Case Studies', '1', 'case-study-4', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Studies</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p><strong>AIDA writing formula case study - Casper</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s go through the AIDA formula step-by-step to see why this is a successful copy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Attention:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The headline, &#39;How to get pee out of a mattress: 6 easy steps&#39; grabs attention and arouses a ton of curiosity for parents and pet parents.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Casper knows its target market and, therefore, its pain points, needs, wants, etc. This is a common problem with children.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And using a specific number with &#39;6 steps&#39; arouses further curiosity and credibility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Interest:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>They swiftly move on to the task of keeping the reader&#39;s interest by making them feel like this content is just for them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They talk about &#39;hours of scrubbing&#39; and &#39;lingering scent&#39; because they know that&#39;s what their target audience experiences. Notice how they use emotional words and phrases, such as &#39;sinking feeling.&#39; You can only write effective copy like this when you know your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Desire:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>They announce that they will deliver on their promise of six steps to get pee out of a mattress. But just before they do, they also mention that prevention is better than cure - a mattress protector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a clever way to place a marketing message. They&#39;ve just given you the solution to prevent this problem from happening again.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Action:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is no vague call to action. There&#39;s no confusion about what a reader should do next to buy a mattress protector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is a clear button inviting them to &#39;Shop Waterproof Mattress Protector) - what else would you press a button for on this page?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>AIDA writing formula case study - Coca-Cola</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Coca-Cola has been around for almost as long as AIDA. And like AIDA, it&#39;s still going strong!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether advertising Coke Zero, Diet Coke, or any product, the AIDA formula stands.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Attention:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether in print, on TV, in digital ads, etc. Coca-Cola is great at grabbing attention because they understand its audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this example, they know their audience loves the hissing sound that comes from removing a bottle cap.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Interest:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In most Coco-Cola content marketing, there are images of people representing the typical Coca-Cola customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This helps potential customers think, &quot;This is me.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You&#39;ll also see content customized toward different events and holidays in the year. Again, this fosters a sense of &quot;this is for me&quot; when their target audience sees people doing things they are doing during that time of year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Desire</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Coca-Cola is very clever in positioning its products as the fun-creating solution to any day or event.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As far back as the 30s, Coca-Cola depicted Santa drinking Coke to help him muster up the energy for a night of delivering toys to children.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since then, Coca-Cola has been synonymous with Christmas, and sales of its products go through the roof during this time of year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Action</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Coca-Cola ensures in all its marketing messages that everyone knows they can get their product from most food stores and use language to entice people to go and buy now.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of their most successful call to action was &#39;Share a Coke.&#39; See how calls to action like this not only encourage consumers to buy but also evoke feel-good emotions by encouraging you to gift the experience of Coke to a friend or loved one.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 13:13:44', '2023-05-08 13:13:44'),
(152, 51, 'Why the AIDA method is timeless for digital marketing', '1', 'why-the-aida-method-is-timeless-for-digital-marketing', '<h2><strong>Why the AIDA method is timeless for digital marketing</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s timeless because Coca-Cola spends millions using the formula. They&#39;ve been doing so since its inception. Tech giant Apple also uses the AIDA formula in print and digital ads. Steve Jobs even used it when giving speeches.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether you&#39;re writing a blog post, paid digital ads, sales page or other marketing materials, the AIDA model works because the journey is the same. You need to grab the reader&#39;s attention, keep their interest, build desire for what you&#39;re selling, and then give them the pish to buy.</p>', '2023-04-19 07:29:43', '2023-04-19 07:29:43'),
(153, 50, 'What Are Content Mills and Should You Write for Them?', '1', 'what-are-content-mills-and-should-you-write-for-them', '<p>When starting out in your freelance writing career, you may hear about content mills. New freelancers may even start writing for a content mill without realizing they&#39;re writing for one.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Content mills are also known as content farms. These companies depend upon volume sales of mass-produced content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The content produced is in the form of articles and blog posts. However, the writers who write this content are paid very low rates. This is because these content farms sell content at very low rates themselves and are looking to make a profit through publishing a ton of content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Content mills are generally on the lowest rung of quality in the writing industry. They care only about the quantity of the content and not about the quality.</p>', '2023-04-19 07:31:14', '2023-04-19 07:31:14'),
(154, 50, 'What are the two different types of content mills?', '1', 'what-are-the-two-different-types-of-content-mills', '<h2>What are the two different types of content mills?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Content mills or content farms come in two forms:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.&nbsp; Individual websites</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These types of content mills produce a large volume from multiple freelance content writers. They work like a writers mill disguised as a job board. Their main goal is to rank their content high on Google and other search engines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>2.&nbsp; Freelance marketplaces</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These content marketplaces connect writers who create cheap, low-quality content with independent online publishers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many content mills give themselves the cloak of legitimacy by disguising themselves as freelance marketplace. But, in reality, they exploit writers by paying very low rates for their writing work (as low as 2 cents per word).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additionally, most of the writing work is published anonymously. A writer is considered a ghostwriter for these websites.</p>', '2023-04-19 07:33:10', '2023-04-19 07:33:10'),
(155, 50, 'The journey of the content mill', '1', 'the-journey-of-the-content-mill', '<h2>The journey of the content mill</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We started to see content mills about 15 years ago. At first, there were the likes of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://guru.com/\" target=\"_blank\">guru.com</a>&nbsp;that paid a pittance to writers in lieu of cheap quality content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then, around 10 years ago, the site Content Media was launched by a former MySpace executive. It, too, offered a bare-bones pay rate to writers in return for very cheap quality content. They then stuffed the content with keywords to get high rankings on Google.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This strategy worked, and content mills clocked in huge returns. But then several crucial updates made by Google to its algorithm put a stop to their dream run.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now you have content mills in their new avatar as mass writer platforms. Thankfully, a handful of these upgraded content mills offer pro rates to writers for good quality writing work.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The best content mills</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a beginner and just starting out as a freelance content writer, here are some of the best content writing sites to look into:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Upwork&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>You set your own rates.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Hires worldwide.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Pays through various payment gateways, including PayPal and direct bank transfers. Once payment is made by the client, you have to wait for 6 days before you can withdraw money.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>You can find high-paying gigs of freelance writing work through this website. Upwork allows freelance writers to work directly with clients and apply for the jobs of their choice. The fees charged by Upwork are high initially, but as the volume of work increases, the percentage fee comes down to only 5%.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Constant Content</h3>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>You can set your own pricing for articles.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Hires worldwide.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Pays through PayPal on the first week of every month.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Only articles can be listed for sale on this content website. Clients can post orders which can then be fulfilled by the writers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>This site focuses solely on selling articles. The writers keep 65% of the sale price. However, there is no guarantee that your writing work will sell. So first post a few articles and then wait and see. If they&#39;re not picked up, you can post them elsewhere. The best part about Constant Content is that a writer can set their own rate per article.&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Crowd content</h3>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Pay is $0.012 cents per word for blogs and articles and $1.75 cents per social media post.&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Hires from any country where English is the native language.&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Pays through PayPal every Tuesday and Friday.&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>On Crowd Content, the quality of your application determines your rating. If your rating is high, you get access to higher-paying gigs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>This content writing site offers varied work, such as blogs, articles, technical writing, copywriting, etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Textbroker</h3>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Pays up to 5 cents per word.&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Hires from native English-speaking countries.&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Payment is through PayPal, but you should have at least $10 in your account.&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>To write for this site, you need to have US citizenship or permanent residency. You will be asked for a writing sample. Based on the quality of your sample, you&#39;re allotted a rating. The higher the rating, the more pay-per-word you&#39;ll receive.&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2023-04-19 07:34:03', '2023-04-19 07:34:03'),
(156, 50, 'Problems with content mills as a freelance writer', '1', 'problems-with-content-mills-as-a-freelance-writer', '<h2>Problems with content mills&nbsp;as a freelance writer</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Most content mills are full of problems that are not easily spotted by new freelance writers until too late. Here are the problems of getting involved with content mills.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Low-quality content</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The only goal of many content mills is to get their content ranked high on Google.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Content mills generally source writers working at very low pay rates. Because these writers need to write in bulk to make money, there is less focus on quality control, and many will publish badly written copy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most writers of this type of content don&#39;t do any research and don&#39;t add their original viewpoint. They just change the order of words or phrases around as they don&#39;t have time to do a good job.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This can also lead to plagiarism, which is taking someone else&#39;s ideas and passing them off as one&#39;s own.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Plagiarism is a serious offense. College students can get kicked out of college and many writers out of their job. If you publish plagiarized content on your own website, Google can penalize your ranking. The original content publisher may even sue you as you copied their content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Poorly paid freelance writers who become &#39;stuck&#39;</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Because of the volume of writing required to make money, writers working for content mills are caught in a vicious cycle. They are barely paid a living wage, so they churn out low-quality content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This, in turn, results in a sorry-looking portfolio. High-end clients on the lookout for quality content won&#39;t bother with hiring these writers. So they&#39;re stuck working for these content mills as they can&#39;t find clients independently.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many writers are then frustrated, give up on writing and look at other income streams.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have a decent income goal of earning $4,000/month, and you are being paid only 2 cents per word by a content mill, you&#39;ll have to write 200,000 words per month (or 200 blog posts of 1,000 words each).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Can you write that much? Not if you want to preserve your health and your sanity!</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Stunted freelance writing career</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If your goal is to become a freelance writer with a thriving freelance business, then working for a content mill is not for you. You can only work as a ghostwriter and remain anonymous. Your content will be considered as mere ghostwritten content. All the credits and the profits from your labor will go to the content mill you&#39;re working for.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A freelance writer has to first work at building their portfolio and reputation. Even if you are an experienced writer of 200 articles, you don&rsquo;t have ownership of those articles. And when you sit down to write an author bio, you&#39;ll have nothing to show.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to earn good bucks as a legitimate freelance writer, you have to build authority and show evidence of your expertise as a professional writer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you write for a content mill, you&#39;re writing purely for SEO, which means you are basically writing for an algorithm. You&#39;re not writing to inspire people or to showcase your creative skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Later on, when you make your career as an independent freelance writer, you will have difficulty finding connections who recognize you for your writing skills. You will have to start as a freelance writer from scratch.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Creates a terrible market for other high-quality writers and content</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>There are experienced writers who can write amazing pieces of content but are starving. Why?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inexperienced clients don&#39;t realize the low-quality of content churned out by a content farm. They see that 2 cents per word is the going rate and think that&#39;s what they should pay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Who wants to $100 per blog post when they think $30 is the market average?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you&#39;re stuck with content mill writing, you&#39;re not only hampering your own freelance writing business, you&#39;re hampering other writers&#39; businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Little or no code of ethics</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>When you write for a content mill, you may find you take on unethical work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, can you write an honest review for a baby food product when you don&#39;t have young kids? How fair is it to the readers?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may write a fully SEO optimized 2,500+ word review on a baby food brand without knowing if it&#39;s good or even safe.</p>', '2023-04-19 07:44:31', '2023-04-19 07:44:31'),
(157, 50, 'Conclusion', '1', 'conclusion-4', '<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You can start an online writing freelance career writing for content mills. It can be a good move for writers wanting to gain experience and make quick money or a supplemental income. Just make sure you pick one of the reputable ones under &#39;The best content mills&#39; above.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But, if you&#39;re looking for more money and want to make a serious career out of freelance writing, forget about writing articles for content mills and focus on building your own portfolio by writing for one or two reputable publications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you&#39;ve gained a reputation as a freelance writer who writes quality content, you&#39;ll earn a lot more, and you&#39;ll attract satisfying freelance writing projects.</p>', '2023-04-19 07:44:47', '2023-04-19 07:44:47'),
(158, 49, 'What Content Could be Used for a Structured Snippet Extension', '1', 'what-content-could-be-used-for-a-structured-snippet-extension', '<h2>What are snippet extensions?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Structured snippet extensions help to relay basic information about your client&#39;s product or service offerings to browser search queries. They help search engines to find potential online customers. There are a huge variety of categories that can benefit from using a structured snippet extension as an effective advertising tool. It informs your audience about what your business provides at a glance without clicking on the site and is a good digital marketing strategy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to make your information more memorable for your users, then using ad extensions is a smart digital marketing move.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The snippets are made of two parts:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Header</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Values</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2023-04-19 07:47:11', '2023-04-19 07:47:11'),
(159, 49, 'What content could be used for a structured snippet extension header?', '1', 'what-content-could-be-used-for-a-structured-snippet-extension-header', '<h2>What content could be used for a structured snippet extension header?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The various types of structured snippet headers you can use in your digital marketing are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Types</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This is more of a general header, and if you are not sure of which header to use, you can use the &lsquo;types&rsquo; header. For example, the American Automobile Association uses different memberships in its types header.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Styles</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>When you want to list specific subtypes within a broader product category, you can use the styles header. However, you should take care that the items you list in the &lsquo;style&rsquo; header should be variations of the same category of product. For example, coffee mugs with different designs.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Shows</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>When advertisers want to list the names of TV shows or performances, they can use the show header. For example, Shows: Friends, Slumdog Millionaire, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Service catalogs</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You can list the services your business offers by using the structured snippet header of &lsquo;service catalog.&rsquo; This header can be used only for services and not for listing products. The users can get quotes for the services listed on the advertiser&#39;s website through structured snippet lists. For example, a handyman could list weatherproofing services, home decor services, plumbing services, etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Neighborhoods</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Official&nbsp;city tourism sites usually use this structured snippet to list the neighborhoods in the city. Only specific districts of a city can be listed in this neighborhood header. You cannot list the names of cities or apartment buildings.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Models</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You can only list models of a particular product like cars or personal electronics in this &lsquo;models&rsquo; structured snippet header. Only specific model names are allowed and do not include manufacturer or store names. Also, you can&#39;t add characteristics like a model number or a benefit. For example, Model: Prius, Camry, and Corolla are models of the Toyota company.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Insurance coverage</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The &lsquo;insurance coverage&rsquo; header highlights specific types of insurance coverage. Here&#39;s a structured snippet header example from an insurance comparison site. Insurance coverage: Auto, Home, Life, Renters, Two wheelers, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Featured hotels</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Advertisers can showcase specific hotels, which they can then book for their customers through the featured hotel header. This snippet header is used by hotel booking websites and travel agencies to help their customers find hotels and book rooms. The values in this header should be the specific names of hotels. For example, Featured Hotels: Hilton NY, The Park, NY, Marriot, NY, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Destinations</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The destinations header is generally used by airlines, rail companies, and bus operators. The &#39;destination&#39; snippet header lists specific places visitors can travel to. It can be cities, states, countries, continents, sites, or attractions. These companies list the destinations the passengers can travel to using their services.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Degree programs</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>An educational institution, like a college or school, uses the &#39;degree program&#39; snippet header to promote specific programs that the institution offers. The list should contain specific degrees like MA or BA. It should not contain any additional information about the degree programs. For example, Degree programs: Accounting, Marketing, Advertising, Taxation, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Courses&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In this &#39;course&#39; snippet header, you can list specific classes or courses, such as &lsquo;creative writing&rsquo; or &lsquo;public speaking.&rsquo;. You cannot list degrees like MBA or BA as you should use the degree program snippet header instead.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Brands</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Under the &#39;brand&#39; snippet header, you can list specific brands you offer without any additional information or description of the brands and products. You also cant include the number of brands you offer or any defining phrases.&nbsp; For example, if you want to advertise various Dell laptop brands, your header will read, Brands: Inspiron, Alienware, XPS, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong>Amenities</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The snippet header &lsquo;amenities&rsquo; is usually used to highlight the features and facilities a place offers. This header enables hotels, Airbnb, or real estate agents to showcase the amenities they have to offer. This is how Airbnb uses this header, Amenities: WiFi, pet friendly. Laundry facility, etc.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-19 07:51:27', '2023-04-19 07:51:27'),
(160, 49, 'How do I optimize structured snippets and boost ad performance?', '1', 'how-do-i-optimize-structured-snippets-and-boost-ad-performance', '<h2>How do I optimize structured snippets and boost ad performance?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You can optimize structured snippets for your digital marketing strategy with these few tips and tricks:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>To get the best results and make structured snippets work, focus on matching the search and query intent to the target audience.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Add structured snippets to an ad campaign or ad group by pairing them with search queries the snippets will appear for. This will make it easy for them to be found by the search engine.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use the correct format. Complete the list and highlight specific aspects to make it easy for the visitor to understand what products and services your company offers. Double-check to make sure you have compiled everything with the most relevant structured snippet you need.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>List at least four values per header. This helps to widen the choice base for the visitor and keeps them engaged on your site. This is a crucial part of online advertising.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consider the smartphone or mobile user who uses mobile and tablet devices and is an on-the-go type of customer. More individuals search using mobile devices than desktops or laptops.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A crucial step in the SEO process is to capture the attention of potential customers by using an ad extension. You can do this if you create shorter snippets. Optimization of snippets is a must for engaging customers on the go.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It&#39;s a good strategy to have several header value options available. It gives the client more choices, and you may have a more relevant extension to pair with the ad.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2023-04-19 07:52:00', '2023-04-19 07:52:00'),
(161, 49, 'What are dynamic structured snippet extensions?', '1', 'what-are-dynamic-structured-snippet-extensions', '<h2>What are dynamic structured snippet extensions?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are multiple structured snippet extensions available. Dynamic structured snippet extensions are extensions that are automatically added to your ad campaigns by Google. Based on the information that google has about your products and services, it will decide which snippets to show and which values to add to your campaign.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The drawback to this is that Google does not reveal to you the actual snippets they have created. You can only find out what snippets have been created by a chance encounter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For this reason, most people turn off dynamic structured snippets extensions.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-19 07:52:21', '2023-04-19 07:52:21'),
(162, 49, 'How do I turn off dynamic structured snippet extensions?', '1', 'how-do-i-turn-off-dynamic-structured-snippet-extensions', '<h2>How do I turn off dynamic structured snippet extensions?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You can turn off structured snippet extensions by following these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Log into your account.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Go to the &lsquo;ads and extension&rsquo; menu.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Navigate to the section called &#39;automated extensions.&#39;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Click &lsquo;more&rsquo; in the top right-hand corner of the page.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Choose advanced options.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pick the option, &lsquo;turn off specific automated extensions.&rsquo;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Select &lsquo;dynamic structured snippets&rsquo; from the list.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Specify the reason for disabling the dynamic structured extension.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Click on the &lsquo;turn off&rsquo; button to complete the process of turning off structured snippet extensions.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>', '2023-04-19 07:52:45', '2023-04-19 07:52:45');
INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(163, 49, 'How do I use Google ad structured extensions?', '1', 'how-do-i-use-google-ad-structured-extensions', '<h2>How do I use Google ad structured extensions?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Ads structured snippets are used to help people advertise certain aspects of their products and services. They are a type of ad extension.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The heading of an ad should be below 30 characters, and its description should not be more than 90 characters. To use this feature, follow this process:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Go to Google ads.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Click on &#39;search campaigns&#39; and find &#39;ads.&#39;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Click on &#39;extensions&#39;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Find &#39;add structured snippet extension&#39;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Once on this page, choose your desired header.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>When you add structured snippets to your search ads,&nbsp; you are providing valuable information to your viewers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Follow these simple steps on Google and make your ad stand out to your target audience and attract more qualified leads.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By using the right information in your headers, you can do away with the problem of unnecessary clicks. It will help your target audience find you more quickly on Google - a win for you and your readers/customers.</p>', '2023-04-19 07:53:14', '2023-04-19 07:53:14'),
(164, 48, 'How to Write the Perfect Blog Post Title (including examples)', '1', 'how-to-write-the-perfect-blog-post-title-including-examples', '<p>Blog posts remain popular even though blogging has been around for over two decades. Many content marketers spend considerable time working on the blog content as it remains an important aspect of their content marketing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, many blog writers don&#39;t spend enough time on creating the best blog post titles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a huge mistake for two reasons.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The blog title or blog headline is the very beginning of a content piece. Therefore it&#39;s the first thing that draw readers in to read your blog article. If it&#39;s not a great title, there&#39;s no point in writing the rest of the blog article as nobody is going to go beyond the blog post title to read it.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>A reader may never even get to your article if your title is bad. They&#39;ll see the title in their Google search, ignore it, and click on another article. You need compelling headlines with trigger words that make a reader feel, &quot;I need to read this&quot; to get a high click through rate.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Search engines use your blog post title as an indicator of relevancy. The best blog post titles, perhaps with a trigger word, lets Google and other search engines know that your content is relevant. Great blog titles will help a site rank well on search engine results pages.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>So let&#39;s look at a few ideas on how to create the best and most catchy blog post titles to increase your click-through rates.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-19 07:54:56', '2023-04-19 07:54:56'),
(165, 48, 'The beginner\'s guide to catchy blog post titles', '1', 'the-beginners-guide-to-catchy-blog-post-titles', '<h2>The beginner&#39;s guide to catchy blog post titles</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&#39;s our step-by-step guide to creating the best blog post titles for your content marketing, that grab the attention of both your target audience and search engines.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Curiosity-based headlines</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Make sure your blog title includes a sense of need or want for your target readers. They should be eager to learn more.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, the blog post title for this blog post is How to Write the Perfect Blog Post Title (including examples).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Writers know they need to write great blog titles or blog headlines for their blog posts to have a great click-through rate. Anything that shows them how to do it well will make them want to read further. Even experienced writers will want to check that there are no new tips that they&#39;ve missed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, using &#39;including examples&#39; raises curiosity further as it implies that the &#39;good stuff&#39; is right there inside the article or blog post.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Deliver your promise</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>There&#39;s nothing worse than raising curiosity only to not deliver on the promise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Writers who focus solely on click through rate (i.e. making an article look great enough to click on when someone searches on Google) without delivering can be penalized by Google as it measures how long people stay on a site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If most of your visitors click to read your article but then disappear fast, it signifies to Google that your content is either irrelevant or poor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Imagine how you would feel after reading &#39;How to Write the Perfect Blog Post Title (including examples)&#39; and then there are no examples or tips.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People tend to scan content instead of reading from top to bottom. They need to see that the blog content delivers on the promise made by the blog title.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Add emotions to your blog/article title</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Emotions sell, whether they are positive or negative and therefore make intriguing blog post titles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, instead of writing &ldquo;7 Things I Do Not Like About Work From Home&rdquo; you can write &ldquo;7 Things I Hate About Work From Home and What To Do About Them!&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By using &#39;hate,&#39; you evoke far more emotion than &#39;do not like.&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Notice how the second headline also uses an element of curiosity too by using &#39;what to do about them,&#39; implying that the answers are right there inside the blog post or article.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Give priority to keyword research &amp; search engine optimization</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s prudent to do keyword research and check the number of monthly searches. You can then use this knowledge to strategically place the best keyword into your blog title.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If someone is likely to type in a particular keyword to see the type of content you write about, seeing those same keywords in your blog title will prove to the that your article is highly relevant to their needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keep in mind search intent. A short-tail keyword may have higher monthly search numbers, but a long-tail keyword could be more relevant and have lower competition, so your article can rank well on Google and other search engines.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Keep your blog headlines under 60 characters</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Search engines like Google tend to only show the first 60 characters. Longer blog titles will be cut off - problematic if your main keyword is at the end of your blog title, or the shortened blog title does not make sense.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stick to under 60 characters for your blog title, and you can be sure a searcher will see the entire thing.</p>', '2023-04-19 07:56:49', '2023-04-19 07:56:49'),
(166, 48, '13 Blog Post Title Templates To Increase Your Click Through Rates', '1', '13-blog-post-title-templates-to-increase-your-click-through-rates', '<h2>13 Blog Post Title Templates To Increase Your Click Through Rates</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s take a look at some tried-and-tested headline examples that grab attention and arouse curiosity.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. &#39;How to&hellip;.&#39; blog titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a popular way to create a blog title (we used it here in this article title).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These blog post titles attract the reader to learn something valuable, mostly a skill they haven&#39;t yet mastered and need or want to learn.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of &#39;How to...&#39; headlines:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>How to download YouTube videos&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>How to write a resume&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. &#39;X ways to solve Y&#39; blog titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These blog titles are great for list posts. Using specific numbers in blog titles is a great way to arouse curiosity and grab attention.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, &quot;3 ways to solve anxiety&quot; is a better blog title than &quot;one way to solve anxiety&quot; because it gives someone a choice. If there&#39;s only one solution, it may not be a fit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, this kind of blog headline would arouse the curiosity of someone who&#39;s solved the issue to see what the &#39;other two&#39; ways are to solve this problem. Here are some other headlines using this great title template:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of&nbsp;</strong>&#39;X ways to solve Y&#39; titles</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>5 ways to solve sibling rivalry issues</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>7 ways to solve dry rot in your home</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. &#39;X things about Y&#39; blog titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These blog post titles are similar to the &ldquo;X ways to solve Y&rdquo; blog title template as it uses a specific number. But instead of solving a problem or issue, it&#39;s used for list posts that provide valuable information about a topic.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of&nbsp;</strong>&#39;X things about Y&#39; headlines</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>5 things you need to know about Covid</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>10 things you should know about anti-virus software before you buy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. &#39;Why, what &amp; where&#39; blog titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These blog post titles grab attention because they promise that the answers to a question are right inside the article.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of &#39;Why, what &amp; where&#39;</strong>&nbsp;titles</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Why is earth called the blue planet?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>What is artificial intelligence?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. X&hellip;.you should&hellip;.&#39; blog titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These blog post titles arouse curiosity as the word &#39;should&#39; makes a reader feel like they could be missing out on vital information that everyone else knows. No one likes to be the last to know!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of &#39;X&hellip;.you should&hellip;.&#39;</strong>&nbsp;headlines</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>7 amazing places you should visit once in your lifetime</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>18 books you should read before you turn 18</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. &#39;Who&hellip;&#39; blog titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to include examples/testimonials or client experiences in your article, these blog post titles let your readers know who these people are.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is important as a reader wants to &#39;qualify&#39; that they&#39;re getting advice from the &#39;right&#39; people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of &#39;Who&hellip;&#39;&nbsp;</strong>titles</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>24 influential travel bloggers of 2022 who fuel our wanderlust&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>5 Twitch streamers who have been banned from the platform in the past</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. &#39;What no one will tell you about&hellip;.&#39; blog titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These types of blog post titles insinuate to the reader that there&#39;s a secret inside the article, something others don&#39;t want to tell you. You can see why this kind of blog title would make someone eager to get &#39;insider&#39; information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course, you need to remember to deliver on your promise, as detailed in the steps above under &#39;The beginner&#39;s guide to a killer blog post title.&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of &#39;What no one will tell you about&hellip;.&#39;&nbsp;</strong>headlines</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>10 things no one will tell you about being an entrepreneur&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>5 things no one will tell you about computer science engineering</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>8. &#39;X&hellip;.mistakes I wish I knew earlier!&#39; blog post titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We try to learn from our mistakes, but wouldn&#39;t it be better to avoid making painful mistakes altogether? This kind of blog title grabs attention because no one likes being wrong and they offer a way to avoid pain - a powerful motivator.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of &#39;X&hellip;.mistakes I wish I knew earlier!&#39;&nbsp;</strong>titles</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>4 skincare mistakes I wish I knew earlier</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>10 income tax mistakes I wish I knew earlier (and how you can avoid)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>9. &#39;An in-depth guide to&hellip;.&#39; blog post titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These blog titles grab attention because some searchers want to know they don&#39;t need to read different content from different sources to understand a topic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you use &#39;an in-depth guide to&#39; in your blog title, you signify to your reader that this is it. This is all they need. They don&#39;t need to look elsewhere.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Why would a reader click on another article when yours has it all?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of &#39;An in-depth guide to&hellip;.&#39;&nbsp;</strong>headlines</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>An in-depth guide to how Google Search works</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>An in-depth guide to finding a perfect warehouse</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>10. &#39;Better than&hellip;.&#39; blog post titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These blog titles pinpoint a comparison between two subjects, usually referring to something being better than the other.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This grabs attention because we all want the perceived best. We don&#39;t want to make the mistake of choosing second best or worse.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Examples of &#39;Better than&hellip;.&#39;&nbsp;titles</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>10 reasons why Android is better than iPhone</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Is Microsoft still better than Google in 2022?&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>11. &#39;Vs&#39; blog post titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These blog titles are similar to &#39;better than&#39; blog titles with a key difference. They are used to make compare two or more things without saying one is better than the other outright.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Just like &#39;better than&rdquo; blog titles, these blog headlines grab attention because we want to make the best choices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of &#39;vs&#39;&nbsp;</strong>headlines</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer engineering Vs software engineering: which is right for you</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mauritius Vs Bali: Which one should you choose next in 2022?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>12. (&#39;negative statement) &#39;Here&rsquo;s why&#39; blog post titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There&#39;s a reason why newspapers are full of bad news and hardly any good. Bad news sells.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With this type of blog headline, you grab eyeballs for your article by using a bad statement, and then you arouse curiosity by telling the reader why this is the case.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of (negative statement) &#39;Here&rsquo;s why&#39;&nbsp;</strong>titles</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You&#39;re using the wrong tips to lose weight, here&#39;s why</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Your content strategy is all wrong, here&#39;s why</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>13. &#39;Stop&#39; blog post titles</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the perfect headline to grab a reader&#39;s attention because readers feel alarmed that they&#39;re making mistakes unwittingly, and the contents of the article will help them stop making these mistakes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of &#39;stop&#39;&nbsp;</strong>headlines</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>7 health warnings you should stop ignoring right away</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scientists explain 22 reasons why you should stop using plastic&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2023-04-19 07:59:16', '2023-04-19 07:59:16'),
(167, 48, 'Conclusion', '1', 'conclusion-5', '<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We wrote this article as a valuable resource to help a content creator craft great headlines that catch visitors attention.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a writer, you&#39;re paid more money when you create successful content that has a great click-through rate. The best way to guarantee a great click-through rate is by crafting headlines telling readers and search engines that your article is the best and most relevant information online.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some pro writers will spend more time just writing titles than they do creating content because they know that a killer blog post will fail without a great title. With the above templates, crafting a great title will become second nature.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, keep in mind that you can come up with new templates that are a mix of two or even a few titles to create a new title template. This tactic could win even more attention from both readers and search engine</p>', '2023-04-19 07:59:55', '2023-04-19 07:59:55'),
(168, 47, 'What Are The Best Tablets For Writers? Our Choice', '1', 'what-are-the-best-tablets-for-writers-our-choice', '<p>When you&#39;re in the middle of your creative flow and inspired to write, a great writing tablet to hand is a must.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re a professional writer and on the lookout for a writing tablet, we&#39;ve done the hard work and picked some of the best writing tablets so you can decide which is best for you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The best tablets for writers</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Key characteristics of a great writing tablet are portability and long battery life. These features make the writing process for a writer easier and stress-free as you can write wherever inspiration hits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A writing tablet is positioned somewhere between a PC and a smartphone. Consider your particular needs as a professional writer when choosing a writing tablet device.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A writer would look for some of these key features in their writing tablet:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Screen size</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Display quality</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Good refresh rate</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Good and easy connectivity</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Long battery life</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sufficient cloud storage</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compatible, external keyboard (on screen keyboards are cumbersome when writing for long periods)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>All weather compatible (inspiration can strike anywhere!)&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s move on to our choice of the best tablets for writers currently on the tablet market.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Microsoft Surface Pro 7</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re looking for the perfect portable device for your writing needs, the Microsoft Surface Pro offers a top-of-the-line writing tablet.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s widely regarded as one of the best tablets for writers currently available on the market. This does mean that the Microsoft Surface Pro is also on the expensive side.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Pros</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It operates on Windows 10 home.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It&#39;s a thin, light computer with a comfortable 12.3 inch screen size</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It has storage of up to 2TB.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It&#39;s versatile (write, touch, draw, play, etc.)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Has USB-C and USB-A ports&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The Microsoft Surface Pro 7 has two modes. A laptop mode where you can use it like a laptop, and a studio mode where you can angle it perfectly for drawing with a surface pen</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A comfortable keyboard for hours of use as a writer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A stylus pen with pressure sensitivity and minimum lag for natural handwriting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It works fluidly with Microsoft Word with Windows 10 and Microsoft pre-installed</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cons</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>does not have long battery life (if you write for a long period, you&#39;ll have to carry a charger)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Some users feel the design could be more elegant (it can look a little industrial and clunk)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Expect to pay extra for the keyboard cover and stylus pen</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Pricing</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Microsoft Surface Pro retails at $749. If you want to buy the keyboard cover, it will come at $129, and a Surface pen will set you back by $99.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Samsung Galaxy Tab S8 Ultra</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Samsung Galaxy S8 Ultra is an upgrade on the S7 series and is considered one of the best android tablets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re looking for a premium writing tablet to streamline your content creation, and speed up your writing process, then this is one of the best tablets for writers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s larger screen enables comfortable writing and composing for long periods.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Pros</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A big 14.6 inch screen size.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Integrated responsive AMOLED display.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bright and responsive LCD display panel.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Qualcomm Snapdragon processing power</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>16GB RAM to efficiently power up its functioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Android 12 OS gives makes the latest applications easily accessible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>DeX mode allows the writing tablet to have PC-level multitasking.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Cons</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The S Pen that comes with this writing tablet can be a bit iffy and erratic.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>DeX mode fails to work sometimes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Apps have scaling issues.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The keyboard case becomes very expensive after some time.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It&#39;s big and heavy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It&#39;s on the expensive side for a tablet in this category.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Samsung Galaxy Pad S8 Ultra base model starts at $1,099. This has a storage of 8GB RAM/128GB storage and Wi-Fi connectivity only. The top model can be up to $1,380.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Apple iPad Pro</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re looking for multi-functionality in your writing tablet, then the Apple iPad Pro will meet all your needs as a professional writer, as well as aspects like graphic design, videography, or even gaming or watching movies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This portable device lives up to Steve Jobs&#39;s promise - it just works!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pros&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The M1 chip in this iPad makes it one of the fastest writing tablets of its kind.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enhance your writing experience with an Apple Magic Keyboard or Smart Keyboard Folio. Magic Keyboard has an inbuilt trackpad, while Smart Keyboard Folio has backlit keys to make it easier to write in poorly lit spaces.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Along with Apple Pencil, the iPad Pro offers speed and convenience of note-taking in documents, notes, and text fields.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Get rid of your storage problems with a big 2TB of storage.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Get 10 hours of battery life on a single charge.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>XDR display offers an immersive experience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>8GB/26GB RAM.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Battery life of up to 10 hours</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sharp and bright liquid retina display.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cons</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You have to purchase the Apple Pencil as an extra as it does not come with the iPad, unlike some other writing tablets.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Its operating system is pushed to the limits, and it discourages multitasking.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You can&#39;t install third-party work-specific apps not supported by Apple iOS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The Smart Keyboard doesn&rsquo;t feel real.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>There are no function keys and light for the Caps Lock.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You can&rsquo;t use a cursor with your iPad Pro.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Apple iPad Pro starts from $799 for the 11 inch screen size. For the 12.9 inch screen size, the price is $1099.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Apple Pencil costs $129. The Magic Keyboard costs $299. And the Smart Keyboard Folio is $179.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HP Pavilion 14</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The HP Pavilion 14 is the best writing tablet for writers who are on a budget. They&#39;re considerably cheaper than most tablets for writers</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Pros&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It&#39;s a hybrid tablet and is considered the most reliable on the market.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Despite a larger screen size of 14 inches, it&#39;s portable and lighter than a laptop.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Display has excellent FSD resolution.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Long battery life of more than 11 hours.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Superfast charging technology.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>360 degree&nbsp; hinge movement.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Its low price makes it the best budget tablet for writers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Cons</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>With low RAM storage and little cloud storage, it makes multitasking impossible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Its performance can be sluggish and not up to the mark of some of the more expensive tablets on this list.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Pricing</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The HP Pavillion 14 ranges from $ 299 to $369.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Lenovo Flex</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nThe Lenovo Flex is more of a 2-in-1 laptop. It&#39;s a best in class laptop that converts into a tablet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Writers who need the flexibility of both a laptop and writing tablet will love this portable device.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Pros</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Full HD touch screen display.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>AMD Ryzen mobile processing power, so that you can write for hours (as well as stream, game, etc.).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Has HDMI, USB - C, and USB - 3.1 inouts.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Built-in cyber protection with Windows 10 to protect you against viruses and malware.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You can physically close your webcam with an in-built shutter for privacy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Quick recharge technology (charge your device in one hour).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Great battery life.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cons</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lenovo Flex is a bit clunkier and heavier than similar writing tablets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The keyboard is not detachable, so a writer has to use it mainly in laptop mode.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lenovo 14 Flex comes at a price of $719.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:03:55', '2023-04-19 08:03:55'),
(169, 47, 'Conclusion - writing tablets for professional writers', '1', 'conclusion-writing-tablets-for-professional-writers', '<h2>Conclusion - writing tablets for professional writers</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We know that writing is fun, but it can also be stressful for writers to produce great content again and again. Having the right tools can help immensely, which is why we compiled this list of the best tablets for writers. In our opinion, a great tablet will not only help you to write efficiently but also do multiple tasks related to writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finding the best writing tablet to fulfill your needs is not a difficult task if you know what your needs are.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>A familiar operating system</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Why spend time learning how to use Microsoft Surface tablets or a Samsung Galaxy Tab if you&#39;re used to using an Apple iPad Pro or vice versa?</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Screen size versus portability</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The smaller the screen size, the more portable the device. But too small a screen size, and it becomes difficult to work on for long periods, even with great screen quality.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Battery life</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is important depending on your lifestyle. If you plan on writing mainly when you&#39;re out and about, it can be infuriating if you run out of power. The best writing tablet for you would be one with longer battery life.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Storage space</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re likely to have a lot of Apple or Android apps, you need a good tablet with a decent storage</p>', '2023-04-19 08:04:19', '2023-04-19 08:04:19'),
(170, 45, 'What is SEO Copywriting?', '1', 'what-is-seo-copywriting', '<p>As a writer, are you tasked with helping a client&#39;s website appear at the top of search engine rankings? Are you confused about what is a short tail or long tail keyword? Are you bored to death with the long, drawn-out lectures about SEO or search engine optimization?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ve put together this easy guide to get you up to speed.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is SEO copywriting?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>SEO copywriting is a part of search engine optimization, which utilizes different ways to make a site rank higher and make web pages search engine friendly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SEO copywriting is the process of writing that enables content to be found by search engines easily. It is useful for your viewers and gives them the answers to the questions they are searching for in their search results.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SEO copywriting can boost page rankings and keep the target audience satisfied.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In short, SEO or search engine optimization copywriting incorporates keyword-optimized content that is appealing to search engine algorithms and, at the same time, useful to human users.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Then what is SEO copyrighting?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is just a typo. Many people accidentally misspell copywriting as copyrighting when searching on Google.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Copyrighting is the right of an individual over their original piece of work. It&#39;s a completely different subject and is not related to SEO copywriting.</p>', '2023-05-08 13:04:42', '2023-05-08 13:04:42'),
(171, 45, 'What are some great SEO copywriting tips?', '1', 'what-are-some-great-seo-copywriting-tips', '<h2><strong>What are some great SEO copywriting tips?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are a number of SEO copywriting tools and SEO copywriting tips employed by SEO copywriters to improve the authority and relevance of their content and get their web page easily found by a search engine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They do this by using specific target keywords so that search engine users will readily find the content. When Google sees its relevancy, it ranks that site higher.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&#39;s some SEO best practices to rank content in the top 10 of Google and increase traffic to a site.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.&nbsp; Site speed for web pages, landing pages, and category pages</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Studies have revealed that nearly half the people who click on a page in their Google search will abandon it if it takes more than 3 seconds to load.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the last decade, website loading times have made a huge impact on site ranking. Even if you have labored for hours to produce useful, interesting content, if the site loading time is more than 3 seconds, you&#39;ll find people will quickly leave. These days, the attention span of users is very short.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>First, analyze the site&rsquo;s speed by utilizing standard speed tests and Google Analytics tools. Then take action to decrease loading time below 3 seconds. Next, check the speed history again to see if the loading time of the web page has improved.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>2.&nbsp; Attention-grabbing headline or title tag</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Only one in five people will read past the headline of a piece of content. The rest will coast away if they find a headline boring. Around 80% of a blog post&rsquo;s success depends on an attention-grabbing headline.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The key element of SEO copywriting is, therefore, its headline. Keep these factors in mind while crafting one:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>In today&rsquo;s marketing world, the headline should prompt the viewers to click and read further.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It should be clickable and attractive. The headline should have the relevant keywords that people search for.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>If you want to be a successful SEO copywriter, create the headline first and then move on to the body of the blog post. This will help the content to be found by search engines faster.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Convey a specific message to the target audience in the headline.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Include a number or figure if possible</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Keep your title under 72 characters to increase click-through rates.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Following the above tips will attract organic visitors to your client&#39;s site.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>3. Quality Content&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Content is an essential element of SEO copywriting success. Instead of focusing just on keyword stuffing, a copywriter should focus on the quality of the content of their SEO writing. You can improve the content for content marketing by paying attention to the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Content should be fresh and useful for humans (and not just geared towards search engines).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use competitive keywords and keyword phrases (and don&rsquo;t stuff keywords).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Put the relevant keywords in your headline.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Make your headline readable from an SEO perspective.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Understand the user intent of your readers and target them.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Blog posts should be longer than 1000 words.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Write content that understands and solves the problem of your readers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Write a compelling introduction that draws the reader in and makes them want to stay on the page.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Optimize your SEO copy by downloading a WordPress plugin called Yoast SEO. It will help you to get a site ranked higher on Google if you follow its prompts.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Meta Title and Meta Description</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The role of meta description is to help search engines understand the content. A meta description is used by Google as a snippet. The snippet copy will help search engine users to see if the page is relevant to their search query.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The role of meta description is to help search engines understand the content. A meta description is used by Google as a snippet. The snippet copy will help search engine users to see if the page is relevant to their search query.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to rank high on Google and catch people&rsquo;s attention, follow this checklist for writing a meta description:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Make sure the keyword intent behind your keywords is correct. The intent of your client&#39;s business should be clear in the keywords.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Keep your meta description under 150 characters (including spaces).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For mobiles, keep it under 113 characters (remember, more searches are done on mobile than any other device, so it&#39;s best to optimize for mobile over anything else).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Along with a short description, include a call to action.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Target keywords should be included (they will be bolded in a query and help the page rank).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Your meta description should be unique to the page.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Frequency of targeted keywords</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The number of times specific keywords appear on the page determines the keyword frequency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In recent times keyword frequency has lost a lot of its importance due to changes in the Google algorithm, but it still stands in the top 200 ranking factors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s best to avoid having a keyword density of more than 5.5%. Doing so will flag your blog posts as &#39;spammy&#39; to Google and other search engines, which means they could penalise it.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Links</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The building blocks of a web page are links. Link building will help a website rank higher in Google searches and increase search volume. Here are the types of links useful for SEO copy:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Internal page links that link to more useful, relevant content.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Links to social media platforms to give Google relevancy and social clues (google pays attention to social media marketing)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>External page links show you value other people&rsquo;s content.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The primary mission of search engines like Google is to organize all the online information in the world. Links help search engines understand the content marketing strategy so they can send the best visitors to your site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, to be successful in link building, you need to make sure your content creation is focused on human users first and search engines second.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, internal links to other existing content on the site are a great idea, but only if they&#39;re relevant. Don&#39;t just link to any page for the sake of it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Linking to external sites is a great way to show Google the intent of your content. However, you should not link to any site you find.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some sites are &#39;low value&#39; in Google&#39;s eyes as they&#39;re spammy or &#39;thin&#39; on content that humans want to read. Linking to sites like these will not help you&#39;re standing with Google. In fact, it could even harm your Google ranking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stick to well-established, authority sites. Ideal sites to link to are those that end with .gov, .edu, or .edu.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:07:51', '2023-04-19 08:07:51'),
(172, 45, 'What are the different approaches to SEO copywriting?', '1', 'what-are-the-different-approaches-to-seo-copywriting', '<h2><strong>What are the different approaches to SEO copywriting?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Write useful content</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the best SEO copywriting tips is to write useful content for human that is also great SEO content. There is no other way around it. People love good and useful content that flows naturally and are likelier to stick to your blog post if they find it interesting.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rather than mere keyword stuffing, this is the best way to generate leads for your brand. Studies have proven that along with being useful, content should have these four features:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Write high-quality content that is fresh (don&#39;t regurgitate information that&#39;s already out there, give it a fresh spin).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Optimize your content with well-researched keywords where you&#39;ve studied keyword intent.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Gain sufficient, relevant backlinks (this is where other sites link to your site).&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Use keyword research and search intent.</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Keyword research is an important aspect of the approach to SEO copywriting. Along with keyword research, you should also be aware of its intent. Before you solve your target audience&#39;s problems, you should know what the keyword used stands for and whether it fulfils the search intent of viewers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pay attention to the classification of keywords also. There are generally two types of keywords:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Informational keywords are used by people who want to search for useful information for free without paying for it. They are generally how-to words. People using these keywords are generally not buyers. It&#39;s best to use these keywords in your title tags to cultivate an audience, guide them to your brand, and encourage them to buy a product or service.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Commercial keywords are used by people when they intend to buy something. They are used by the searcher when they are desperate to take action to buy a product. Some examples of commercial intent keywords are review, buy, order, free, comparison, best, fast, etc. The person who is searching with a commercial keyword usually wants to buy a product, or they may sign up for an email that will lead them to convert as buyers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Here are the three steps to using a target keyword in your copy:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use the target keyword in the title.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use alternative keywords in the meta description as well as in your introduction.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Write the content naturally for human readers and keep an eye on keyword density (don&#39;t stuff keywords)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Write the conclusion with the primary keyword inside.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Use long-tail keywords and short-tail keywords</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Short-tail keywords are three words or less, while long-tail keywords are more than three words. SEO firms use long-tail keywords to get your page to the top of search engine results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The advantage of using long-tail keywords is that as they grow longer, the search volume gets lower but more specific or relevant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, if someone searches for &#39;Ford Ka,&#39; they could be looking to buy a car, or they are just looking for information. If you&#39;re writing for a car dealership, someone just searching for &#39;Ford Ka&#39; does not mean they want to buy a car. Even if they do, they could be hundreds of miles away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, if someone searches for &#39;Ford Ka in Birmingham, UK,&#39; that&#39;s far more relevant. Yes, there will be far fewer searches than &#39;Ford Ka,&#39; but those searchers will be far more relevant to your car dealership client. Quality of searches trump quantity from a commercial point of view.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Therefore, long-tail keywords have higher conversion rates than short-tail keywords. They are highly recommended by WordPress plugins like Yoast SEO.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Use storytelling</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stories have eternally been loved by humans. As an SEO copywriter, if you can weave your client&#39;s brand story into your content, viewers will find it more appealing. They are more likely to stick through to the end of the blog post and more likely to push the call-to-action button.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use the element of storytelling in a natural way and use high-quality content to make the maximum impact on your reader. The Lego Movie is a successful brand story. It does not just sell Lego bricks. It sells possibilities.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 13:12:32', '2023-05-08 13:12:32'),
(173, 45, 'Case Studies', '1', 'benefits-of-seo-copywriting', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Studies</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Case studies help to explain your products and services. They help to drive more organic traffic to your site, and are therefore highly useful. Studies have shown that B2B buyers prefer research-based content and case studies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The different types of case studies are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Research reports and studies.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Technical spec sheets and data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Analyst intelligence and insight.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>White papers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Articles on trade publishing.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Your main long tail keywords will start showing up on the top Google rankings once you start writing consistent and detailed case studies consistently.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 13:09:31', '2023-05-08 13:09:31'),
(174, 45, '​​​​​​​Benefits of SEO copywriting', '1', 'conclusion-6', '<h2>&nbsp;<strong>Benefits of SEO copywriting</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>What are the benefits of great SEO content and SEO copywriting?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Most people only click on the first two to three search results when searching on Google. Good SEO content that is pleasing to both humans and Google will mean your client&#39;s website will rank higher than a competitor&#39;s website, and hopefully get into those top search results.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Great content creation that&#39;s based on good SEO copywriting principles and search intent will gain valuable and qualified traffic to your target site. Remember to use focus keywords in title tags and meta descriptions in your writing process.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>If you write content that provides useful information to your audience by answering their questions and providing a solution to their problems, you&#39;ll create trust which leads to sales and brand loyalty.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You can inspire your readers to take action, e.g., to buy your product, subscribe to the blog, listen to the podcast, etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You can gain authority over time through link building as other sites link to your content when relevant.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A great SEO strategy will not only benefit you in terms of search engine optimisation, but you&#39;ll find it benefits other digital marketing forms, such as social media marketing.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '2023-05-08 13:10:36', '2023-05-08 13:10:36'),
(175, 44, 'The 6 Best Writing Apps for iPad - Our Choice', '1', 'the-6-best-writing-apps-for-ipad-our-choice', '<p>In the past, writers and authors had to document their thoughts through pen and paper, styluses on clay pads, typewriters, and other writing tools. Computers allow us to write, edit, format, and rearrange content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With ongoing digitalization, we have modern writing apps, writing tools, and software that provide the writer hassle-free functionality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many writers love Apple iOS devices and use apps on the iPhone or iPad to help them write. Some of these writing apps have features that include distraction-free writing. It&#39;s worth mentioning apps like Final Draft and Scrivener, which are perfect for users who need an easy-to-use, simple text editor or word processor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a beginner writer, you can start with Pages (free) or Word ($70 per year subscription) as a beginner. But, if you take your writing seriously, you&#39;ll want to graduate from this. So, let&#39;s look at some great writing apps you can use on your Apple iPad device to support your writing and help you create your next article, blog, or even novel.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:20:33', '2023-04-19 08:20:33'),
(176, 44, 'What you should know about writing tools', '1', 'what-you-should-know-about-writing-tools', '<h2><strong>What you should know about writing tools</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you begin with any of the suggested apps, consider the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>What do you plan to write?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There are five aspects to consider:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fiction or nonfiction</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prose or Poetry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Long-form or short form</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Writing platform (print or web)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Leisure writing or professional writing</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The types of writing you plan to do influence your choice of app.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:21:02', '2023-04-19 08:21:02');
INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(177, 44, 'The 5 different stages involved in writing', '1', 'the-5-different-stages-involved-in-writing', '<h2><strong>The 5 different stages involved in writing</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Most writing projects involve five distinct steps. While some apps target some of these steps, others focus on all five stages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1.&nbsp; Prewriting</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This includes topic selection, research, brainstorming, and planning what you need to write. This crucial first step allows you to collect and arrange your thoughts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.&nbsp; First Draft</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first draft of your writing doesn&#39;t need to be perfect and will likely be different from your final write-up. Your primary focus here should be writing without distraction or being unsure about yourself.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.&nbsp; Revision</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This takes your first draft to the next level, where you add, remove, and rearrange content and structure. It involves improving the words, clarifying the vague content, and removing unnecessary text.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4.&nbsp; Editing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is fine-tuning your writing, including spelling, punctuation, and grammar corrections, checking for clarity and enhancing the text. This is an important step, especially with professional writing. A professional editor may use a separate app for tracking edits and making suggested changes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5.&nbsp; Publishing&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Publishing can be in two mediums, print or web. Some apps have settings that allow the writer to post on several web platforms directly, create ebooks, or develop and download fully-formatted PDFs.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:21:59', '2023-04-19 08:21:59'),
(178, 44, 'Word processors do not allow you to separate style from content', '1', 'word-processors-do-not-allow-you-to-separate-style-from-content', '<h2><strong>Word processors do not allow you to separate style from content</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Many writers use word processors for their writing projects. But be aware that these are not the best tools for professional writing projects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Word processors are not designed for composition. Word processors were mainly intended for business use. As such, a lot of emphases is placed on presentational elements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s why Word or Google Docs start to format your work, typeset your text, etc., immediately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many of the features in a word processor cause distraction. They don&#39;t allow you to focus on ideas generation and the creation of words. Your mind is diverted to the final document. This is a big, time-wasting problem.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A writer&#39;s main purpose is to write. Anything else is a distraction. Though all the features provided may be useful later in the editing and publishing steps, initially, they will hinder your writing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pro writing apps are different and focus on helping the writer to write. Once the writing process starts, they allow formatting and style to get in the way. Any extra features that may be useful to writers at a later stage can stay out until needed.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now let&#39;s look at the six best writing apps we&#39;ve reviewed for the iPad. We&#39;ll list the pros, cons, and pricing for each. Remember to use the above points to help you decide which app is best for you.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:22:30', '2023-04-19 08:22:30'),
(179, 44, 'The 6 Best Writing Apps for the iPad ', '1', 'the-6-best-writing-apps-for-the-ipad', '<h2><strong>The 6 Best Writing Apps for the iPad&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>#1 Ulysses</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a simple text editor that hides a lot of power. Its strength lies in its simplicity as a basic word processor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ulysses treats everything that you write as one single document. No stylistic formatting and no distractions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Quick access to whatever you are writing</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A great feature set for optimized writing experience</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The ability to share in multiple formats</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Export files directly to publishing mediums</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Trial available only after subscription</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>New users are required to learn Markdown and keyboard shortcuts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ulysses is a subscription app and can be used across Mac, iPhone, and iPad at an annual cost of $50 per year.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>#2 Scrivener</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Many book writers recommend Scrivener as an enjoyable writing experience. It&#39;s designed for long-form content, such as books, academic papers, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As you progress, you can organize and rearrange your chapters, topics, etc. (very difficult to do in Word or Pages).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allows you to set writing targets for your entire book project or just for a current session</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Store research, e.g., drafts, notes, web links, images, PDFs, videos, audio files, etc., in your book</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Quick access to everything you need</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Built-in spelling and grammar checks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Polish your writing and prepare it for book printing or sending to publishers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Learning basics takes some time as a beginner</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Freezes at times, and takes a while to backup</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>For Mac, Scrivener costs $49 (one-time fee).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>#3 OmniOutliner</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As the name suggests, this is an &#39;outlining&#39; tool. Its main element is to help in expanding ideas. It&#39;s exceptional in outlining everything from novels to non-fiction books.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This app allows you to jot down thoughts and then helps you arrange, elaborate, manage, and grow them until your work is complete. It&#39;s ideal for bloggers, video creators, and freelance writers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Easy to learn and use</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Well-designed interface</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Variety of easy-to-use templates</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Keyword filtering</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mind mapping tool</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>No feature for internal PDF export</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Full-feature software is expensive compared to other apps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Available for both Mac and iOS, OmniOutliner is $99 on either platform (the stripped-down OmniOutliner Essentials costs $19.99).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>#4 Drafts 5</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the most basic note-taking apps, Drafts 5 allows you to speed up your composition and writing work. Whether you&#39;re a beginner or a seasoned writer, you can start composing and writing fast.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once the text is ready, the app can publish it as a blog post on your website, an email, or various other actions in just a tap.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Easy to use and cost-effective</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Transcribes from video and audio content</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Great user support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Regular updates</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Freezes when sharing large files</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Simplify feature can sometimes delete important information</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Drafts 5 is free to use, while Drafts Pro subscription is $20 per year.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>#5 iA Writer</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This helps you stay focused and clarify your message.&nbsp; Even before Mac introduced its Focus Mode, iA Writer already had this unique feature.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A unique feature is the ability to have all your writing fade to grey, except the sentence you are working on. This takes distraction-free writing to the next level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Inexpensive</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Next level distraction-free design</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Option to highlight superfluous adjectives, weak verbs, and repetitions for improving your writing</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Supports Markdown formatting with plain text commands right in the text</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>No templates available</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Limited tools for organizing and arranging files</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pricing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>For Mac, the cost is $29.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>#6 Final Draft</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Despite many new competitors, this screenwriting app remains the leading choice for television and film writers. Although Final Draft is a word processing app used for letters and prose, its strength lies in its ability to automate screenwriting formats.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The settings in Final Draft help you concentrate on your storyline, characters, and dialogues by automatically formatting as you write!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Crafted for screenwriters</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Easy to use</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Availability of extensive developmental tools</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Different types of writing templates are available</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Instant formatting as per industry standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Supports real-time collaboration with other writers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Expensive in comparison to other software</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaboration with other writers can only be done one person at a time</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Must sign in to the platform to work from there</p>', '2023-04-19 08:23:39', '2023-04-19 08:23:39'),
(180, 44, 'Conclusion', '1', 'conclusion-7', '<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A professional writing app is probably unnecessary if you&#39;re just starting your writing journey. Try using an app that serves your writing purpose and the one you&#39;re comfortable with. This will allow you to focus on your writing rather than getting to grips with an app.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A word processor like Microsoft Word, Google Docs, or Apple Pages can be all you need. If you have a device like a Mac or iPad, you can opt for a note-taking app like Apple Notes, Evernote, or your preferred text editor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But suppose you&#39;re a professional writer or serious about writing in a particular field. In that case, spending your valued time and money on an online app designed specifically for your purposes is wise. Most of the apps on our list have a trial version.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The money you spend and the time you invest getting to grips with a new online writing app will be returned many times as you learn to compose and write content fast and efficiently.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:23:57', '2023-04-19 08:23:57'),
(181, 42, 'Ultimate Guide to Tone of Voice Examples', '1', 'ultimate-guide-to-tone-of-voice-examples', '<p>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s not what you say, it&rsquo;s how you say it.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We all remember a time when we asked a loved one if something was wrong, to be given a curt, &ldquo;No!&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Their tone of voice means we know something is wrong and they know something is wrong. Also, they want you to know something is wrong. And yet their words convey the opposite of the truth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Humans have evolved to take in everything from body language and facial expressions to voice tones to help them understand others.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a writer, it&rsquo;s your job to put your clients in the best light possible in front of their target audience. In the absence of body language, facial expressions, and voice tones, your tone of voice through words alone must do the job of all these aspects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Does that sound daunting?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Don&rsquo;t worry. We&rsquo;ll show you how to find the perfect brand tone with tone of voice examples, for every client you write for.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You&#39;ll learn how to find a brand&#39;s personality by focusing on brand values and brand persona. Clients/customers expect brands to have a consistent tone, and you will be at the forefront of providing this - read on.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:26:01', '2023-04-19 08:26:01'),
(182, 42, 'Tone of voice definition', '1', 'tone-of-voice-definition', '<h2>Tone of voice definition</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s essentially about how your brand speaks to the audience and what they see and hear. Tone means how you communicate rather than what you communicate.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:26:26', '2023-04-19 08:26:26'),
(183, 42, 'Why do your clients need to get their brand voice right?', '1', 'why-do-your-clients-need-to-get-their-brand-voice-right', '<h2>Why do your clients need to get their brand voice right?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The perfect brand tone and brand voice creates an emotional connection with potential clients/customers. It makes people feel their core values are the same as the brand&#39;s core values.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It inspires potential customers/clients to make positive actions, whether that&#39;s buying a product/service, signing a contract, donating money/time, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember,&nbsp;<em>everything</em>&nbsp;you write for a client has a commercial aspect to it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may not be writing &lsquo;hard&rsquo; sales copy, such as sales letters, landing pages, etc. Perhaps you&rsquo;re tasked with &lsquo;soft&rsquo; content strategy, such as blog posts, social media posts, or relationship-building emails.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, all content is still geared towards profits. And that&rsquo;s why getting the right brand tone and brand voice is so crucial.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many amateur writers believe that they just need a wider vocabulary or the latest copywriting &lsquo;hack&rsquo; to become great writers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead, pro writers have a knack for hitting just the right tone of voice with a target market to inspire them to take action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Think about it. If you were a business owner paying someone to write content for you, who would you choose? The writer with a vast vocabulary and clever turns of phrases? Or the writer who hits the right tone of voice to trigger emotional responses in your potential customers/clients so they buy, sign up, etc.?</p>', '2023-04-19 08:26:52', '2023-04-19 08:26:52'),
(184, 42, 'How do I find the perfect brand tone for a client?', '1', 'how-do-i-find-the-perfect-brand-tone-for-a-client', '<h2>How do I find the perfect brand tone for a client?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If your client has worked extensively with freelancers and/or in-house writers, they&rsquo;re likely to have brand voice guidelines or style guides.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This certainly makes your job easier. The assumption is that your client has done their due diligence, knows their customers/clients inside out, and they know what tone of voice works.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, you may have a client who hasn&rsquo;t done any in-depth research on the correct tone of voice. Worse still, you may have a client who is making huge assumptions about their customers/clients that are wrong.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether you like it or not, this will impact how well your content performs. You could write the best content in the world, but if the tone of voice is off, it will fall flat as it won&rsquo;t resonate with the audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ask the following questions to your new client to build a style guide:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1.&nbsp; What business challenges do you currently have?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This question helps you understand if the current brand tone of voice is correct or not.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, if your client says they need more leads but have a high conversion rate, you know the issue is with reach and not tone. When people discover their products/services, they&rsquo;re &lsquo;sold.&rsquo; They resonate with the message and take positive action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, if your client says they need more leads but have a low conversion rate, it means something is off. They don&rsquo;t need more leads. They need to convert more of their existing leads. One reason could be an issue with the brand tone of voice with the existing content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2.&nbsp; Which businesses do you consider your competitors?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This question allows you to see what others are doing and the tone of voice they are using that could be working for them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Direct competitors are businesses that have the same target audience as your client. If you discover that a competitor has a lion&rsquo;s share of the market, it&rsquo;s common sense to analyze the tone of voice their content is taking. Success leaves clues!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3.&nbsp; If your target audience was one person, who are they? Describe them to me.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a clever way to get your client to focus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you asked, &ldquo;Who is your target audience,&rdquo; you may get generic answers, such as middle managers, which is too broad.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By asking your client to distill their audience down to one person, you will get specifics, such as age, gender, likes/dislikes, etc. The best writers will drill down much further, such as what publications/websites they read, what they do in their spare time, etc., to refine the tone of voice they should use when writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Think of how easy it is to write an email to your best friend. You know their personality, their likes and dislikes, and you know what offends them and what doesn&rsquo;t. If you&rsquo;re able to get to this level, that&rsquo;s when your writing will resonate deeply.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4.&nbsp; What do you want your potential customers/clients to do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember, even &lsquo;soft&rsquo; content that is not directly selling something still has a commercial aspect to it. No business is willing to spend money with zero return on investment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You need to find out what your client wants their audience to do overall (very likely to be a monetary transaction) and also the smaller action steps for different content pieces. E.g., signing up to get a free sample/report, upgrading product after initial purchase, etc.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:28:07', '2023-04-19 08:28:07'),
(185, 42, 'What are the main brand voice tones for businesses?', '1', 'what-are-the-main-brand-voice-tones-for-businesses', '<h2>What are the main brand voice tones for businesses?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are numerous words to describe tone. For example, passionate, dry, bold, down-to-earth, informative, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But ultimately, all business content falls into five tones of voice types:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Energetic</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dependable</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Elegant/Expensive</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Irreverent</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Innovative</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Understanding which of the five your client&rsquo;s audience falls into will make or break your content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s look at some examples using the five tone of voice types.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Energetic</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a good tone of voice to hit if your client&rsquo;s ideal customers/clients are in the youth market (e.g. teen clothes, &lsquo;young&rsquo; social media networks and apps, etc.)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It also works well in markets designed to utilize energy, such as gyms, sports clothing, exercise programs, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to hit an energetic brand tone</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An energetic style guide uses lots of bullet-pointed or numbered lists. Don&rsquo;t use long sentences with a ton of conjunctions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fragmented sentence structure with a motivating tone works well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, use short words for a brand voice that packs a punch.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s a great energetic tone of voice example:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take a look at the entire content piece at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.muscleandstrength.com/workouts/womens-3-day-glute-workout\" target=\"_blank\"><u>https://www.muscleandstrength.com/workouts/womens-3-day-glute-workout</u></a><u>.&nbsp;</u>Can you see how the brand&#39;s voice has a &#39;go-getter&#39; personality with a motivating tone throughout?</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Dependable</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the perfect tone of voice when your client&rsquo;s products/services are something that their clients/customers rely on.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The product or service may not be the most exciting, but people value these products or services for their dependability over excitement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Great examples are insurance companies, payment/merchant service providers, hosting companies, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This doesn&rsquo;t mean your words can&rsquo;t inject a little energy or humor. But keep in mind that the audience is ultimately looking for safety. &nbsp;Use a more formal tone of voice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to hit a dependable brand tone</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A dependable style guide uses words that are wholesome and feel comfortable and warm.&nbsp;At the same time, you want a slightly authoritative tone of voice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More so than any other tone type, avoid using any words that can offend, such as curse words. This will likely go against brand values. This is not the audience to be &lsquo;edgy&rsquo; with. Avoid using slang or colloquialisms for the same reason.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s a good dependable tone of voice example:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take a look at the entire content piece at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.aviva.co.uk/insurance/life-products/life-insurance/\" target=\"_blank\"><u>https://www.aviva.co.uk/insurance/life-products/life-insurance/</u></a>. Check out the respectful tone and writing style throughout.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Elegant/Expensive</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the must-use tone of voice for high-end items, boutiques, or any product or service that&rsquo;s targeted at the affluent. It&rsquo;s also an ideal tone of voice for salons, spas, and resorts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to hit an elegant and expensive brand tone</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An elegant and expensive style guide uses a longer sentence structure that flows well with conjunctions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use adjectives to create a world inside the reader&rsquo;s mind so they can imagine the pleasure. Keep content about the functional aspect of a product or service to a minimum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid using action-oriented words and short, punchy sentences. Nothing in your content should convey that there is a rush.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Look at this example of an elegant/expensive brand tone of voice:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take a look at the entire content piece at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.joali.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><u>https://www.joali.com/</u></a>&nbsp;to see the brand&#39;s tone and brand personality that oozes luxury and elegance.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Irreverent</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a humorous tone of voice for businesses and brands who want to be seen as &lsquo;out of the box&rsquo; thinkers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Therefore, it lends itself to apps and games targeted at the youth (especially males) as well as street brands.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, irreverent, offbeat humor can be used for all kinds of products and services - it&rsquo;s all about knowing your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to hit an irreverent brand tone</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to Merriam-Webster, irreverent means &ldquo;lacking proper respect or seriousness.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, you need to understand the audience to know what they like to disrespect - it&rsquo;s not a case of just disrespecting anything and everything! Therefore, hitting the right irreverent tone of voice is a bit harder than other tones.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your client needs to give you lots of tone of voice guidelines regarding their perfect customers/clients. so you can assess personality traits, word choice, and communication style.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s one of the best irreverent tone of voice examples for a &hellip; wait for it&hellip; life insurance company called Dead Happy!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check out the unique tone of the entire content piece at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://deadhappy.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><u>https://deadhappy.com/</u></a>. We&#39;re sure you&#39;ll agree. It&#39;s a very unique brand voice with a clear tone and very distinct personality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As you can see with this example, this flies against the earlier advice that insurance companies should go for a more dependable tone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, the reason why this content works so well is that the business knows its audience (young, upwardly mobile, and savvy, who love dark humor). They are able to show off the brand&#39;s personality with offbeat humor.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Innovative</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It will come as no surprise that this tone of voice is perfect for software companies, app firms, and any product/service which is cutting edge.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your client can succinctly tell you that &ldquo;no one is doing exactly what we&rsquo;re doing&rdquo; when you ask about their competitors, you know you have an innovative brand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That doesn&rsquo;t mean they don&rsquo;t have competitors at all. But they will have major differentiation points.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to hit an innovative brand tone</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Innovative people tend to use fewer words. So keep your content succinct.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, don&rsquo;t be overly formal. Think of how we became accustomed to seeing Steve Jobs in jeans. Innovative brands prefer conversational language with an informative tone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, don&rsquo;t go overboard and start using colloquial language that starts hitting an irreverent tone. Word choice is important.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, testimonials that &lsquo;prove&rsquo; how great a product/service is will work better than marketing messages. That&rsquo;s true for all brands, but more so for innovative brands.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s a good innovative tone of voice example:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check out the entire content piece at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://streamyard.com/%EF%BF%BC\" target=\"_blank\">https://streamyard.com/</a>&nbsp;where you can see the innovative brand personality and tone of voice, together with a powerful testimonial.</p>', '2023-04-19 08:31:38', '2023-04-19 08:31:38'),
(186, 42, 'Getting the brand\'s tone equals a highly effective (and highly paid) writer', '1', 'getting-the-brands-tone-equals-a-highly-effective-and-highly-paid-writer', '<h2>Getting the brand&#39;s tone equals a highly effective (and highly paid) writer</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Robert Cialdini introduced six persuasion principles in his international bestseller, the Psychology of Persuasion (a must-read for new and experienced writers).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of these principles is likability. The first step when we start any relationship, commercial or otherwise, is liking that person, business, etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The right tone of voice in your content creates likability immediately, which is the first step to the audience engaging with a business or brand. So you must take time to find the correct brand tone of voice for each client.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The more you hit the correct, consistent brand tone of voice, the more effective your content becomes. The more successes you have, the more you get paid!</p>', '2023-04-19 08:32:02', '2023-04-19 08:32:02'),
(187, 67, 'How to Build a Sustainable Copywriting Business with Client Value', '1', 'how-to-build-a-sustainable-copywriting-business-with-client-value', '<p>We already know what it takes to be a great copywriter: creating compelling, clear copy that can persuade readers to take action, engage in your content or learn from your writing!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So what does it take to run a copywriting business?</p>', '2023-04-20 02:51:03', '2023-04-20 02:51:03'),
(188, 67, 'How do I start a Copywriting Business?', '1', 'how-do-i-start-a-copywriting-business', '<h2>How do I start a Copywriting Business?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Focusing on the basics of copywriting is crucial in starting your own copywriting business. Planning and organisation will be your best friend in this new venture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you don&rsquo;t feel determination and passion, you may want to rethink this decision, as this isn&rsquo;t something that will come easy! But if done correctly, you will be left with a fantastic brand, a sustainable business and a client base that trusts you and your employees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you ask us, the preparation is well worth the reward.</p>', '2023-04-20 02:58:20', '2023-04-20 02:58:20'),
(189, 67, 'Case Study', '3', 'case-study-5', '<h2>Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Small businesses may be reluctant to create a yearly business plan due to the intangible aspects of being a start-up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating a quarterly business plan is a great way to improve your percentage of goals met and allows you to be more creative and adaptive as you move forward on this journey.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are a few ideas of goals you may plan during your first few months:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Earning an income of a specific amount.</li>\r\n	<li>Build your network and be in contact with X amount of people in the industry.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Create and optimise your portfolio with SEO in mind.</p>', '2023-05-08 07:53:42', '2023-05-08 07:53:42'),
(190, 67, '10 Steps to Building a Copywriting Business', '1', '10-steps-to-building-a-copywriting-business', '<h2>10 Steps to Building a Copywriting Business</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s get into the critical steps of building a copywriting business.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Each step is crucial, and we could bombard you with reels of information. Instead, we will hold back and summarise the most critical parts to get your brain cogs turning!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1.&nbsp; Conduct Market Research</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Market research is the foundation of any copywriting business, the copywriter&#39;s content and the inspiration for ideas and progression.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Understanding the broader landscape of copywriting marketing gives you insights into industry trends, modern customer preferences and any market shifts that will help you build an up-to-date and sustainable business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/convertkit\">CovertKit</a> is a great tool to help you grow and monetise your audience, and from only $9.00/month for a creator&rsquo;s account, it&rsquo;s a worthy investment in your future.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2.&nbsp; Choosing your Niche and Copywriting Specialities</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Starting a business from scratch is a challenging task. But gathering information on what you want your niche and specialities to be once you are up and running is a vital step.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One option is to open a business as a generalist copywriting business. This is an excellent option for start-ups to gain clients, credibility, social proof and experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your second option is to focus on subjects you are passionate about and knowledgeable about. For example, if you studied business and media, taking this approach with your services can be a great way to promise success.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thirdly, you can base your niche on those with high demand in the industry. Tools like <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/feedly\">Feedly</a> will help inform you about current viral topics and news.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3.&nbsp; Writing a Business Plan to Succeed</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Have you got a strategy in mind, goals you wish to achieve, and targets for the next three years? Get them all documented in a business plan!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thoughts and ideas may have gotten you this far, but constructing a solid business plan will take control from now on. Believe us when we say it is necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>4.&nbsp; A Strong Portfolio</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the essential parts of starting a copywriting business with client value is advertising and showcasing your capabilities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A strong portfolio that highlights your diversity and reliability will surely bring in clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not only will you reach a boarder audience through your online portfolio, but it is also an excellent way to show off those writing skills. Selling yourself to a potential client is a great way to show talent.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>5.&nbsp; Discussing Your Rates</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your rates will change over time, and depending on how experienced you are when starting your business, rates can range over vast numbers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may choose to charge per hour, per word, or project. Either way, the most important thing to remember is that you charge for skill, value and quality of work. <em>Don&rsquo;t sell yourself short.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>6.&nbsp; Building Your Network</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Network building is one of the often forgotten or skipped steps in creating a sustainable business, but its power can result in rapid success in expansion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can easily begin networking online. For example, a LinkedIn account is a great way to find connections to benefit your business.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>7.&nbsp; Accounting System</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Owning your own business will entail handling your own administrative work, so you&rsquo;re in luck if you have an accounting degree!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From spending to payments, your accounting system should be a top priority step on this list.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We advise keeping a Google spreadsheet to track income and expenses. A visual aid will help you crunch those numbers!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>8.&nbsp; Marketing and Social Presence</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You need to market yourself for the business to pick up. Let the world know you&rsquo;re ready to create awesome content!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Social media is a great way to do this. Creating a social presence on platforms such as LinkedIn, Instagram, Facebook, and Twitter is a great way to advertise your service in today&rsquo;s technology-driven society.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Look out for business start-up events, print creative and witty calling cards with your details and <em>sell</em>, <em>sell</em>, <em>sell</em>!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>9.&nbsp; Self-Development and Consistency</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Here at <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/\"><u>The Author&rsquo;s Pad</u></a>, we believe that self-development is a process that never ends once on the career path of a copywriter. That&rsquo;s why we have created a community that serves all copywriters, junior, senior or business owners alike.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Join our bank of copywriting knowledge and continue growing and improving your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>10.&nbsp; Rapport with Clients</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This last step in building a sustainable copywriting business with client value should go without saying, but building rapport with your clients is necessary.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your clients are your livelihood, so making sure that they are comfortable with your transaction, happy with the results and would recommend you to other potential clients is the only way to keep them on board!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Go the extra mile for clients, ask questions about the content they want you to create to appear attentive and interested, and, most importantly, follow through with deadlines, briefs and quality.</p>', '2023-04-20 03:05:18', '2023-04-20 03:05:18'),
(191, 67, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact-8', '<h2><strong>Key Fact</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>According to Indeed, senior copywriters can earn, on average, &pound;44,338 annually.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rates and average pay vary depending on the topic, style, location and experience, so it&rsquo;s important to do serious research before choosing yours!</p>', '2023-05-08 07:56:28', '2023-05-08 07:56:28'),
(192, 67, 'Frequently Asked Questions', '1', 'frequently-asked-questions-3', '<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Is the curious entrepreneur inside you asking for more information? Here are a few more FAQs on the topic of sustainable copywriting businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Is Copywriting a Profitable Business?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is a profitable business because the resources needed to succeed in this sector are limited. With copywriting mainly digital and online, starting a business and creating content can be completed relatively cheaper than other business models. For example, you don&rsquo;t need to rent office space, stock up a kitchen with ingredients or hire cleaners like other business models might require.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How much does it Cost to Start a Copywriting Business?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>According to <a href=\"https://www.starterstory.com/ideas/copywriting-business/startup-costs\"><em><u>Starter Story</u></em></a>, the average cost to start a copywriting business in 2023 is around &pound;5500. Apart from money, creating a copywriting business will also cost you time, focus, planning, and determination.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Is Copywriting a Good &lsquo;Side Hustle&rsquo;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is considered one of the best &lsquo;side hustles&rsquo; out there! The better your skills are, the higher quality of content you create as a copywriter will determine your prices and income. Copywriting is a gold mine for someone with a natural talent for writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-20 03:06:50', '2023-04-20 03:06:50'),
(193, 68, 'Why Portfolio Building Is Crucial for Every Aspiring Copywriter', '1', 'why-portfolio-building-is-crucial-for-every-aspiring-copywriter', '<p>In the US and UK, <a href=\"https://killercopywriting.online/how-many-copywriters-are-there-around-the-globe/\">17% of all freelancers</a> specialise in content services. It should be no surprise; content careers like copywriting let writers support themselves through their passion. However, getting started is a challenge. It&rsquo;s not easy to know where to begin or how specific tools can be beneficial.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A portfolio, for example, is a handy tool for copywriters, and most writers starting today don&rsquo;t have one.</p>', '2023-04-21 08:38:12', '2023-04-21 08:38:12'),
(194, 68, 'What is a portfolio for a copywriter?', '1', 'what-is-a-portfolio-for-a-copywriter', '<h2>What is a portfolio for a copywriter?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>For a copywriter, a portfolio is a selection of their past work highlighting their skills to clients. The writer aims to demonstrate their abilities and work history in hopes of gaining new contracts and customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Experienced copywriters can choose the best pieces they have written for their portfolio to attract the right clients. However, aspiring copywriters with no previous work must be innovative when creating a portfolio without experience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is possible to make a portfolio without doing any copywriting work. Starting a portfolio can be intimidating without the initial incentive of a client&rsquo;s brief. Perhaps because of this, some beginner writers wonder if having a portfolio will help them get work.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-21 08:38:51', '2023-04-21 08:38:51'),
(195, 68, 'Does a copywriter need a portfolio?', '1', 'does-a-copywriter-need-a-portfolio', '<h2>Does a copywriter need a portfolio?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In short, yes. Most potential clients will look elsewhere for a copywriter without proof that you can perform the task. You need to be able to demonstrate your writing skills through a variety of sample texts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The days of in-person meetings with physical portfolios are behind us, and remote working has flourished in the last four years. Being able to send a digital copy of your work puts you one step ahead of everyone without a portfolio to lean on.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-21 08:39:19', '2023-04-21 08:39:19'),
(196, 68, 'Why are portfolios important in copywriting?', '1', 'why-are-portfolios-important-in-copywriting', '<h2>Why are portfolios important in copywriting?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The main reason your copywriting portfolio is essential is that it proves you can do the job. Having samples from previous projects shows your versatility and talent. It could make all the difference between getting a job offer or a rejection email.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When clients look at your CV and maybe a cover letter, they get a decent idea of who you are. Providing them with a digital portfolio shows them you can use your personality to create a unique and characteristic copy sample.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What makes a good copywriter portfolio?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Good copywriters can adapt their style while maintaining what makes it their own. Their portfolios are eye-catching because of the range of copies they display. Samples like:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Blogs/articles</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Social media posts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Flyers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Email newsletters</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Product descriptions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Landing pages</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>These samples highlight the different copywriting skills required to be a successful copywriter. If you can show clients you can create content like this, they&rsquo;re more likely to hire you for their projects. They might consider you for other projects based on what you show in your portfolio.</p>', '2023-04-21 08:40:34', '2023-04-21 08:40:34'),
(197, 68, 'Why is it important to build your portfolio?', '1', 'why-is-it-important-to-build-your-portfolio', '<h2>Why is it important to build your portfolio?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Building your portfolio keeps it relevant to your current skill level. The work isn&rsquo;t over once you have your first portfolio &lsquo;finished&rsquo;. You should regularly maintain and update your portfolio throughout your career to accurately reflect the type of work you complete.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, as your career progresses, you might find a niche for your writing, like medical copywriting. Your portfolio, therefore, should display five - seven medical copywriting samples from your recent work. You can send this portfolio to prospective clients in the medical field and show off your knowledge within their area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating multiple portfolios for different specialities is also worth it as you develop your skills. It helps you market yourself to a broader range of clients, increasing your odds of receiving job offers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even from scratch with no experience, building a portfolio is crucial for aspiring copywriters. Clinching your first job is arguably the most challenging part of starting a career in this industry. Make it easier on yourself by building a sound copywriting portfolio. If you join The Author&rsquo;s Pad community, you&rsquo;ll find all the tools to make it easy.</p>', '2023-04-21 08:42:21', '2023-04-21 08:42:21'),
(198, 68, 'FAQs', '1', 'faqs-3', '<h2>FAQs</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Here, we cover a few frequently asked questions about building a portfolio as a copywriter.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What is the most important thing to become a copywriter?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Good copywriting is about thoroughly understanding written language. It would be best to have an excellent grasp of your spelling and grammar and an ability to communicate information and ideas effectively. Branching out to clients and maintaining good relationships is crucial to copywriting success. Start by building your portfolio and then grow from there.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What makes a copywriter stand out?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Originality and authenticity make your writing stand out from the competition. Rather than trying to write like someone else, try to write in a particular format in your own style. Good clients want writers that can keep any topic interesting and easy to digest, with some personality thrown in there too. Your copywriting portfolio allows you to set yourself apart from other applicants immediately.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What makes a good writing portfolio?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A good writing portfolio will include several writing samples covering various topics and styles. You&rsquo;ll also add more personal information about your history as an aspiring writer - anything that shows more of your character (whilst staying work-appropriate). It&rsquo;s also a good idea to include some links to your social media or blog if you have one.</p>', '2023-04-21 08:43:10', '2023-04-21 08:43:10'),
(199, 69, 'The Copywriter\'s Guide to Time Management and Workload Planning', '1', 'the-copywriters-guide-to-time-management-and-workload-planning', '<p>Time management and planning is the best way to ensure success in any business. This same principle applies to both aspiring and advanced copywriters.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Newcomers to the business that are beginning their business from fresh, building their clientele and have a little more time on their hands than they would like to admit, need to focus on organisation during this time and start as you mean to go on.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This does not mean that if you have a large workload, ten years of experience in copywriting and hardly any time to spare, you can skip this step! How do you expect to give every client your best when you are stretched thin, your diary is full of mistakes and Tipp-ex, and you&rsquo;re a little bit all over the place?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keeping to an efficient time management system and creating a plan to match your workload and its specific needs will clear up time you didn&rsquo;t know you had and allow you to plan to be your better self.</p>', '2023-04-22 07:07:13', '2023-04-22 07:07:13'),
(200, 69, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact-9', '<h2>Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>According to Dr Donalds E. Wetmore, 20% of the average workday is spent on crucial things, while the remaining 80% of the average workday is spent on things of little value.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not very time efficient at all! You want to distance yourself from this statistic as far as possible.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 08:20:34', '2023-05-08 08:20:34'),
(201, 69, 'Work Smarter, Not Harder', '1', 'work-smarter-not-harder', '<h2>Work Smarter, Not Harder</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Although it may not seem time-related, the work smarter philosophy is one of the most effective ways to improve your time/workload balance.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Feel like you&rsquo;ve been busy all day, answering a million emails and other administrative tasks, yet got no further on your copywriting project? We often spend more time than we realise in the planning stages of a project, and most of these can be made redundant.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/rescuetime\">Rescue Time</a> and the <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/todoist\">Todoist</a> are brilliant tools to help you plan efficiently and smarter. Saving you hours that would have gone to waste on a spreadsheet you&rsquo;d never return to! Using your time more wisely and utilising many of the great tools out there is just the first step in becoming a time-efficient copywriter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Knowing yourself and your capability at different times of the day can be a great way to manage your time. Not a morning person? Then don&rsquo;t force yourself to get up a 5 AM. You&rsquo;ll only waste more time proofreading and correcting the work that your half-asleep brain produced during this time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Plan your time to your schedule, optimise your productivity, and you&rsquo;ll see a positive difference in time-frames for progress in your workload.</p>', '2023-04-22 07:08:47', '2023-04-22 07:08:47'),
(202, 69, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact-10', '<h2>Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>On average, individuals use 13 different methods to try and improve and control their time management. How many do you use currently, or think you&rsquo;ve tried in the past?.</p>', '2023-05-08 08:21:01', '2023-05-08 08:21:01');
INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(203, 69, '3 Obvious, Yet Often Skipped Principles of Time Management', '1', '3-obvious-yet-often-skipped-principles-of-time-management', '<h2>3 Obvious, Yet Often Skipped Principles of Time Management</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>At first glance, these will seem like the usual tips and tricks that any Google search would tell you, but when put into practice, these can produce great results. Consistency is key, and planning one week of the year isn&rsquo;t going to cut it!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Being Self-Aware and Motivated</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We often lose ourselves in our workdays, and our brains can sometimes clock out when we clock in. Keeping self-aware of your goals, determination, and future is the only deterrent to this dissociation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keep yourself on track by reflecting on what you will complete in the day and how it is progressing in your career, which will motivate you to work better. Doing this will make your daily tasks more meaningful and your goals more reachable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Motivation is often forgotten when it comes to time management and planning, but studies show that it directly impacts how well your workday goes!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Knowing How to Prioritise</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Prioritising your workload can be difficult at first, but creating a system that works for your copywriting clients will bring to light the best and most efficient route to take weekly.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Using online tools crafted to increase productivity and time management skills is the first step in this process, and using Todoist will help you do just this. With Todoist, you can organise your tasks and projects and then share, collaborate and delegate these between you and your team.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Haven&rsquo;t you got a team to delegate? Todoist lets you set labels, filters and priorities to help you create a visual window into your workload. You can even create reminders and notifications for yourself to remind you of projects requiring more attention than others!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Try their <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/todoist\">free 30-day trial</a> today and learn the best practices for prioritising.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Plan For Your Day First, Then Your Week</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Workload planning when you are juggling 20 plus clients, 30 plus projects, and your everyday life can be daunting and is a task that is often shelved or abandoned. Taking a step back and looking at everything from a different perspective can make this task seem much more effortless.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/\">The Authors Pad</a>, we encourage self-enhancement, the refining of your skills, and efforts to make you stand out from the crowd, but these are hard to complete when you don&rsquo;t know your plan for Monday morning.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We understand that not everything always goes to plan, but even if 80% of your goals for the week are ticked off by Friday, it&#39;s better than 0%!&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-22 07:16:17', '2023-04-22 07:16:17'),
(204, 69, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact-11', '<h2>Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A Gallup study found that the average employee works 20% better when they are motivated about their workload.</p>', '2023-05-08 08:21:23', '2023-05-08 08:21:23'),
(205, 69, '5 Steps That Will Help Plan Your Week', '1', '5-steps-that-will-help-plan-your-week', '<h2>5 Steps That Will Help Plan Your Week</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Make that plan, write that checklist and set those goals for the week. Without them, you may as well be writing aimlessly. Here are five steps that will help plan your week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.&nbsp; Look at the timeline of your current projects, and list them in order of deadline. Be realistic with the time you allocate these tasks to ensure you don&rsquo;t overlap. Doing things quicker than originally planned is better than running out of time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2.&nbsp; Break these larger projects into smaller goals and tasks, this will help manage your time between each checkpoint within the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3.&nbsp; Avoid multitasking between projects, each client and their project deserves your full attention and effort.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4.&nbsp; Ticking off your successes towards the end of the day isn&rsquo;t the only benefit of a checklist. Tasks that are often incomplete at the end of the day, or even the week may not be necessary at all. Analyse your checklists monthly to see if you are wasting time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5.&nbsp; Regularly review your planning, changing time-frames or goals isn&rsquo;t cheating, copywriting is a flexible career and you need to be able to change your schedule to suit clients.</p>', '2023-04-22 07:19:13', '2023-04-22 07:19:13'),
(206, 70, 'How to Master Proofreading for Better Copywriting', '1', 'how-to-master-proofreading-for-better-copywriting', '<p>Proofreading is an essential step in the copywriting process, and this seemingly small step has the potential to make or break your work, taking you from &ldquo;okay&rdquo; to a total pro in no time. Proofreading offers the final chance to ensure that what you have written is accurate, correct, and error-free before you submit it for publication - but this is a skill that may not come naturally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mastering the proofreading process can be difficult, but with a few helpful <a href=\"https://demo91.co.in/dev/affiliatecontent/public/\">tips</a> and tricks, you can make sure that your copywriting is of the highest quality.</p>', '2023-04-23 07:00:16', '2023-04-23 07:00:16'),
(207, 70, 'What Is Proofreading?', '1', 'what-is-proofreading', '<h2>What Is Proofreading?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading is the process of carefully examining written material to identify and correct errors in grammar, spelling, punctuation, syntax, and formatting. It helps ensure that what you have written is accurate and error-free before you submit it for publication.</p>', '2023-04-23 07:10:58', '2023-04-23 07:10:58'),
(208, 70, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact-12', '<h2>Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you make an error on your page, experts claim that it will be seen by 74% of your readers. Do yourself a favor, and make sure that there is nothing to find.</p>', '2023-05-08 08:02:20', '2023-05-08 08:02:20'),
(209, 70, 'Top Tips To Master Proofreading', '1', 'top-tips-to-master-proofreading', '<h2>Top Tips To Master Proofreading</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>While it is a seemingly simple process, proofreading properly can be difficult. To help you perfect your skills, here are some tips and tricks for mastering proofreading.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Take Your Time and Read Carefully</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The most important part of proofreading is to read your work slowly and carefully. This helps you pay attention to details that you may have missed or overlooked before. Reading out loud can also be helpful, as it forces you to take your time and focus on errors that may have been overlooked when reading silently.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Check Your Spelling and Grammar</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When proofreading your work, always check for spelling and grammar mistakes. This can be done manually or with the help of a computer program such as Microsoft Word or a web-based grammar checker such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly</a>. As mentioned, make sure to read your work out loud when checking for errors, as this helps you identify mistakes that may have been missed when reading silently.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Check for Consistency</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Maintaining a consistent style and tone is essential when writing and good proofreading can help ensure that you have achieved this. You should also check that you have spelled names and titles correctly and consistently and that any abbreviations or acronyms are used correctly.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Check for Accuracy</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to catching typos and other grammar and spelling mistakes, it is also important to check for factual accuracy. Make sure that all information is correct and up-to-date, as providing incorrect information can negatively affect the credibility of your work.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Check for Clarity and Flow</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Before submitting your work, make sure to check for clarity and flow. This can be done by reading your work out loud and making sure that everything is clear and logically structured. If something doesn&rsquo;t make sense or seems unclear, take the time to rewrite it until it is perfect.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also check that your work is easy to understand by using tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a> to ensure that your content is readable and easy to follow.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Use a Fresh Set of Eyes</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are having trouble finding errors, try asking a friend or colleague to take a look at your work. This will give you a fresh set of eyes that can help you identify mistakes that you may have missed and can be a great final check/</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Check Formatting</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to checking your work for spelling and grammar mistakes, it is also important to check the formatting of your writing. Proper formatting includes elements such as font size, line spacing, margins, and page numbers. Attention to detail in these areas ensures a professional and polished appearance for your copy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Make Sure You Know The Language</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>English has subtle differences in usage across various countries, which can make proofreading challenging. It is important to have a strong understanding of the language and utilise resources, such as dictionaries or online tools, to clarify unfamiliar words or phrases, such as slang or colloquialisms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading tools like Grammarly and UK vs US Spelling can be useful for identifying and correcting errors in spelling, grammar, punctuation, and syntax, which can result in a more polished and error-free final product.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Take Breaks</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading can be tedious work, so it is important to take breaks when needed. Breaks will help you stay focused and alert while proofreading your work.</p>', '2023-04-23 07:05:53', '2023-04-23 07:05:53'),
(210, 70, 'Key Fact', '2', 'key-fact-13', '<h2>Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Missed punctuation is often considered to be the most common mistake that proofreaders fail to notice - using the right tools offers you a safety net, and reduces your risk of overlooking an obvious error.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 08:02:51', '2023-05-08 08:02:51'),
(211, 70, 'Why Is Proofreading So Important?', '1', 'why-is-proofreading-so-important', '<h2>Why Is Proofreading So Important?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading carefully and methodically offers several benefits, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>It Keeps Work Accurate</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading is an essential component of the copywriting process, as it guarantees that your work is precise, mistake-free, and refined. By dedicating time to meticulously reading and assessing your work prior to publication, you can assure that it meets the highest standards.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>It Strengthens Your Work</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading can enhance the structure of your writing and assist you in identifying any areas that require clarification or improvement, guaranteeing that your writing is coherent, rational, and comprehensible.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>It Ensures Professionalism</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The aim of any professional copywriter is to produce work that is error-free and polished. By taking the time to proofread your work, you can ensure that it reflects a level of professionalism and attention to detail that will be appreciated by clients or readers.</p>', '2023-04-23 07:07:05', '2023-04-23 07:07:05'),
(212, 70, 'CASE STUDY', '3', 'case-study-6', '<p>CASE STUDY:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDuring a significant project which incorporated multiple participants working from every corner of the planet, it became clear to the project manager that things were slowly spiralling out of control. Documents were being mislabelled and misplaced, deadlines were being ignored, and key elements of briefs and important information were being missed - and all directly due to poor communication.</p>', '2023-04-28 06:29:26', '2023-04-28 06:29:26'),
(213, 70, 'Tips To Become A Master At Proofreading', '1', 'tips-to-become-a-master-at-proofreading', '<h2>Tips To Become A Master At Proofreading</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you really want to up your game and become a master at proofreading, there are some tips that&nbsp;can help you on your way. These include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Take Your Time</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Tempting as it can be to rush through the proofreading process, it is important to take your time and read through your work carefully. This will help you identify any mistakes or areas that need clarification.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By adding Trello to the team, things changed overnight. Projects could be organised in tables, deadlines set and highlighted, and files shared and stored in a single, secure location that was accessible to each and every team member. Peace was restored, stress levels returned to something approaching normal, and a calm victory settled over the writers. At long last, the project was at peace.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Read Out Loud</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As we mentioned, reading out loud can help you identify errors in flow or clarity that may not be obvious when reading silently. It can also help you identify any words that sound awkward or out of place, and make sure that everything is clear and easy to understand.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Check References</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When writing about factual or numerical information, it is important to double-check the sources of your information. This will help you ensure accuracy and legitimacy in your work, and reduce the risk of any mistakes or inaccuracies.</p>', '2023-04-23 07:08:55', '2023-04-23 07:08:55'),
(214, 70, 'Case Study', '3', 'case-study-7', '<h2>Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>When one of our UK-based customers was given the opportunity to work with a client across the Atlantic, she jumped at the chance. The project was simple, in her area of expertise, and she assumed that she had nailed the project - until she received the feedback that all of the spelling had been proofed according to UK spelling conventions, as opposed to those typically used in the US.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a predominantly British client base, it was tricky for our client to automatically switch between the two languages - until she discovered Trysto UK vs USA spelling - a comprehensive guide that made switching from US to UK English a dream. Without excellent proofreading, however, she would never have spotted the error, underlining just how crucial this skill is for producing great work.</p>', '2023-05-08 08:03:26', '2023-05-08 08:03:26'),
(215, 70, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-3', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Proofreading is an important part of the copywriting process, and taking the time to read through your work carefully can help ensure that it is error-free and polished. By using the tips outlined in this article, you can become a master at proofreading, and produce professional copywriting that will be appreciated by clients or readers.</p>', '2023-04-23 07:10:01', '2023-04-23 07:10:01'),
(216, 71, 'How to Edit Your Way to Great Copywriting', '1', 'how-to-edit-your-way-to-great-copywriting', '<p>Are you looking for tips and tricks to take your copywriting to the next level? Do you want to learn how to craft compelling, engaging copy that captures your audience&#39;s attention and drives results? If so, then learning how to edit your way to great copywriting is a must. Editing is an essential part of the writing process, and knowing how&mdash;and when&mdash;to edit can help you create a copy that is not only engaging, but super effective as well.</p>', '2023-04-25 07:18:27', '2023-04-25 07:18:27'),
(217, 71, 'What Is Copywriting?', '1', 'what-is-copywriting-2', '<h2>What Is Copywriting?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is the art of writing persuasive, compelling copy to capture an audience&#39;s attention, and motivate them to take action. Copywriters work to produce written materials such as advertising copy, blog posts, sales copy, and web content that require skilful use of language, and a thorough understanding of the target audience, all with the goal of helping brands achieve their objectives.</p>', '2023-04-25 07:18:56', '2023-04-25 07:18:56'),
(219, 71, 'What is Editing?', '1', 'what-is-editing', '<h2>What is Editing?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As mentioned, editing is a necessary step in the writing process that involves checking for clarity, accuracy, and audience appropriateness to enhance the effectiveness and impact of the written piece.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Effective editing plays a crucial role in copywriting success, helping to eliminate choppy writing, run-on sentences, and unclear structure. Quality copy should be concise, direct, and engaging, achieving its goal while captivating the intended audience. Through editing, you can refine and improve your writing, ensuring that it effectively communicates your intended message in a manner that resonates with readers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Editing is also an important step in maintaining consistency in tone, style, and voice. It is recommended to approach editing with a critical and thorough mindset, focusing on elements such as grammar, punctuation, spelling, and sentence structure, and there is a wide range of <a href=\"https://demo91.co.in/dev/affiliatecontent/public/\">tools </a>available to help you ensure your work is of the highest quality.</p>', '2023-04-25 07:23:21', '2023-04-25 07:23:21'),
(220, 71, 'How to Edit Your Copywriting', '1', 'how-to-edit-your-copywriting', '<h2>How to Edit Your Copywriting</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you start editing your copy, it&#39;s important to understand just what actually makes good copy. In short, good writing is clear, concise, and engaging; it conveys a message in an easy-to-understand way and meets the needs of the target audience. <a href=\"https://demo91.co.in/dev/affiliatecontent/public/\">Focus </a>on clarity, flow, and readability when editing your copy - this will help ensure that your writing is effective and successful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As with any skill, editing is a learned process. Here are some tips and techniques to help you edit your copywriting for success:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1.&nbsp; Read Through Your Work Carefully</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Take the time to read through your writing carefully before you start making changes or edits. This allows you to get a sense of how the piece flows and identify any areas where it might need additional work.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2.&nbsp; Eliminate Any Unnecessary Words or Fluff</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Remove any words or phrases that don&rsquo;t add to the overall message of the piece - but remember to maintain clarity. While it&#39;s important to be concise, you also want to make sure that your copy is clear and easy to understand - excessive use of big words or overly long sentences can detract from the message.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3.&nbsp; Check For Spelling And Grammar Mistakes</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Mistakes in spelling and grammar can distract from your message, and they can also make you come across as unprofessional. Be sure to double-check for any errors before submitting your copy, and run your text through a checker such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly </a>to ensure that you catch any errors.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4.&nbsp; Check for Clarity and Flow</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Read through your writing to make sure that it&#39;s clear and easy to follow.; make sure that any transitions between topics are smooth and that each paragraph ties back to the message of the piece. You can also check that sentences make good sense and that the piece flows well and is pleasant and clear to read - tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/readable\">Readable </a>and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>5.&nbsp; Use Active Voice Whenever Possible</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Active voice helps to make your writing more engaging and direct, so use it whenever possible. Avoid passive voice as much as you can, as it can make your writing sound dull and disconnected.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>6.&nbsp; Give Your Writing A Purpose</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Make sure that your writing has a purpose, and that this purpose is clear throughout the piece. Every sentence should contribute to the overall message of the copy, so if something doesn&#39;t fit, it&#39;s best to delete it or rewrite it. When proofreading, ensure that each sentence has a clear purpose in the context of the piece.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every sentence should have a purpose, and each one should lead logically to the next. Make sure your writing is focused and that you&rsquo;re not straying from your main topic.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>7.&nbsp; Know Your Target Audience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Always remember to keep your target audience in mind when editing. When you understand who you&#39;re writing for and what they are looking for, it&#39;s easier to ensure that your copy is clear and engaging and to tailor your message accordingly to ensure maximum impact and effectiveness.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>8.&nbsp; Read Your Work Aloud</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Reading aloud is one of the best ways to catch any mistakes or awkward phrasing that may have slipped through the cracks when editing on paper. This helps ensure that your copy sounds natural and conversational, making it more engaging for the reader.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>9.&nbsp; Get Input from Others</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Getting feedback from other people is an important part of the editing process. Ask them to read through your copy and provide constructive criticism; this can help you identify any areas that need improvement, as well as any areas where you may have been unintentionally unclear or repetitive.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>10.&nbsp; Use Editing Tools</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Editing tools such as grammar checkers and spell checkers can be a great help when it comes to polishing your copy. While they won&#39;t necessarily identify any conceptual or structural issues, they can help you catch any typos or small mistakes that may have slipped through the cracks.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>11.&nbsp; Take a Break and Come Back to It Later</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It can be difficult to edit your own work, so don&#39;t be afraid to step away for a bit and come back to it with a fresh set of eyes. Taking some time away from the piece allows you to look at it with a more objective perspective, which can help you identify any areas where the copy may need additional work.</p>', '2023-04-25 07:25:35', '2023-04-25 07:25:35'),
(221, 71, 'Case Study', '3', 'case-study-8', '<h2>Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>When Jennifer&#39;s business started to take off, she realized very quickly that she was in need of extra help. What began life as a simple business creating and selling blog posts for customers soon became a headache-inducing nightmare of conflicting deadlines, contrasting briefs, multiple languages, and a lot of confusion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After a particularly taxing day, Jennifer finished a blog, gave it a cursory glance over, and sent it off to the client. The next morning her inbox was the recipient of an angry message, pointing out numerous spelling errors, missing links, deviations from the brief, and conflicting information that made the piece look sloppy, messy and unprofessional, In that moment, Jennifer realized: she needed a plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fortunately for her, she soon found herself at our door and received the wisdom she sought: a simple, straightforward proofreading checklist that could be easily adapted to each and every project that she found herself working on. This checklist formed the backbone of her editing process, streamlining the necessary tasks and ensuring that nothing was missed out. When she wrote and edited her next blog post, she felt the weight lift from her shoulders - and is pleased to report that she has never experienced an angry email from a client since.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>', '2023-05-08 08:00:54', '2023-05-08 08:00:54'),
(222, 71, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-4', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Editing is a necessary component of the copywriting procedure, and it is critical to devote sufficient time to guarantee the quality of your work prior to submission. By adhering to these guidelines, you can ensure that your writing is comprehensible, compelling, and impactful and that your message is effectively conveyed.</p>', '2023-04-25 07:26:50', '2023-04-25 07:26:50'),
(223, 72, 'The Importance of Editing in Copywriting for B2B and B2C', '1', 'the-importance-of-editing-in-copywriting-for-b2b-and-b2c', '<p>To communicate effectively with customers, businesses need many things - a great product, good customer service, and a quality reputation are all key, but excellent copywriting skills should be at the top of the list if you want to succeed - good editing goes hand in hand with this.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether you are working for B2B or B2C, editing is critical for any written message to succeed - and we have put together all you need to know about the significance of editing and the advantages that it can offer to both types of copywriting clients.</p>', '2023-04-26 11:22:00', '2023-04-26 11:22:00'),
(224, 72, 'What Is Copywriting?', '1', 'what-is-copywriting-3', '<h2>What Is Copywriting?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is a method used by businesses to effectively communicate their message and build relationships with their customers. It involves creating persuasive, engaging, and informative content that resonates with the target audience and can be utilised in various forms including emails, websites, blog posts, newsletters, and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Good copy requires creativity and a deep understanding of the target audience, an ability to really get into the minds of the consumer and coax them over to the business, and a final secret ingredient: good editing. Often overlooked, editing is just as important as writing and can make the difference between mediocre and great content.</p>', '2023-04-26 11:22:26', '2023-04-26 11:22:26'),
(225, 72, 'The Benefits of Editing in Copywriting', '1', 'the-benefits-of-editing-in-copywriting', '<h2>The Benefits of Editing in Copywriting</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are a number of ways in which editing can improve your writing, and these include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Improved Quality</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Editing is an important process for copywriters to enhance the quality of their work. Through careful review, they can detect any mistakes or areas that require improvement. This guarantees the communication is precise and direct without any extraneous words or phrases.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Increased Readability</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Editing can also improve the readability of content by simplifying language and formatting. <a href=\"https://demo91.co.in/dev/affiliatecontent/public/\">Tools </a>such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/readable\">Readable </a>and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a> can aid in creating fluid sentences, while <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/title-capitalization-tool\">Title Capitalization Tool</a> can ensure proper capitalization in titles. These actions can enhance the visual appeal of the content and encourage reader engagement.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Increased Credibility</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Proper editing can ensure that the copy is accurate, which will help to increase credibility. If a business&rsquo;s copywriting contains factual errors or typos, it can damage its reputation and make customers less likely to trust the brand.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>More Engaging Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of editing can be beneficial for copywriters in identifying areas for improvement and increasing engagement, and tools like<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/semrush-writing-assistant\"> SEMrush Writing Assistant</a> can aid in implementing effective SEO strategies and minimising unnecessary language.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Increased Efficiency</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Editing helps to streamline the copywriting process by eliminating any superfluous content and ensuring that all the information is relevant and on-point. This can help businesses to save time and resources, as they won&rsquo;t have to spend time revising or rewriting content that isn&rsquo;t necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Improved Consistency</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of editing is necessary for maintaining consistency in style, tone, and language, particularly for businesses seeking to establish a professional image and foster customer trust.</p>', '2023-04-26 11:22:58', '2023-04-26 11:22:58'),
(226, 72, 'What Is B2B?', '1', 'what-is-b2b', '<h2>What Is B2B?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>B2B copywriting is the creation of industry-specific content that caters to the needs of a particular company or industry, demanding a thorough understanding of the industry and its target audience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>B2B copywriting necessitates technical knowledge and research to generate compelling messages that prompt readers to take action, which differentiates it from B2B copywriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When copywriting for B2B projects, some of the main features to be aware of include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Tailor Copy To The Company</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>B2B copywriting should be tailored to the individual company, so it is important to understand their specific needs and requirements. This includes making sure that any instructions they provide are followed accurately.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Adhere To Industry Standards</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>B2B copywriters must possess a comprehensive knowledge of the industry they are writing for to allow them to produce content that aligns with the expectations of their intended audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Research</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Accurate, comprehensive research is necessary for B2B copywriting to produce content that is precise and enlightening. Examining the company, industry, target audience, and associated topics will guarantee that the copy is current and pertinent. Use tools such as Portents Content Idea Generator or <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hubspots-blog-topic-generator\">HubSpot&#39;s Blog Topic Generator</a> to craft new ideas, and find the latest stories in your industry with the <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/google-trends\">Google Trends</a> tool.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be Persuasive</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>B2B copywriters must possess the skill to create persuasive messages that encourage the reader to take action, as well as inform them.</p>', '2023-04-26 11:23:54', '2023-04-26 11:23:54'),
(227, 72, 'How Does Editing Help B2B Copywriting?', '1', 'how-does-editing-help-b2b-copywriting', '<h2>How Does Editing Help B2B Copywriting?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>When writing for a B2B audience, it&#39;s important to consider the interests and needs of the business as a priority. The copy should be informative and persuasive to convince potential customers or partners of the value of the company&#39;s services or products. Editing is crucial to ensure all of these elements are present and to correct any grammar or spelling errors, as well as ensure that consistency is maintained when it comes to brand names and details.</p>', '2023-04-26 11:24:39', '2023-04-26 11:24:39'),
(228, 72, 'What Is B2C?', '1', 'what-is-b2c', '<h2>What Is B2C?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>B2C, or business-to-consumer, is a type of copywriting that entails generating material for a broad audience of customers or consumers. B2C copywriters must have the ability to construct messages that will attract their intended audience and motivate them to act. This form of writing necessitates comprehension of the target audience&#39;s interests, necessities, and principles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When writing for B2C, keep the following tips in mind:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Focus On Benefits</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When creating content, it is important to prioritise the benefits that customers will receive from using the product or service, rather than solely highlighting its features.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Target Your Audience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Effective B2C copywriting involves customising the content to suit the preferences and requirements of the intended audience. The writing style should be engaging and persuasive, encouraging them to act.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Make It Concise</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Effective B2C copywriting is characterised by clarity and conciseness. The process of editing can aid in eliminating any fluff or overly complex language that may be perplexing or confusing to the reader. Take advantage of tools such as Hemingway and SEMrush Writing Assistant to ensure that content is concise and easy to read, and tools such as the Guardian and Observer Style Guide to ensure that words are correct and understandable.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be Engaging</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Effective B2C copywriting aims to capture the reader&#39;s attention through engaging and persuasive language, while editing can assist in ensuring the message is clear and concise.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-04-26 11:25:19', '2023-04-26 11:25:19'),
(229, 72, 'How Does Editing Help B2C Copywriting?', '1', 'how-does-editing-help-b2c-copywriting', '<h2>How Does Editing Help B2C Copywriting?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>For B2C writing, clarity and conciseness are crucial. Editing is a key step in ensuring that the content is error-free and easily comprehensible to the intended audience, and can play a key role in helping to ensure that copy helps to maintain the company&#39;s brand guidelines while also making the message compelling and engaging.</p>', '2023-04-26 11:25:37', '2023-04-26 11:25:37'),
(230, 72, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-5', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting for both B2B and B2C audiences requires good editing to ensure that the end result is well-written, accurate, and persuasive content. Editing also ensures that any grammar or spelling errors are removed, and ensures that text follows company instructions, brand requirements and formatting guidelines, while also ensuring that industry standards are met and that the audience is targeted effectively.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By making the most of the array of tools on offer, you can really master editing, and ensure that the output is right on the money - no matter which type of client you are producing content for.</p>', '2023-04-26 11:26:00', '2023-04-26 11:26:00'),
(231, 73, 'The Value of Consulting in Developing Your Copywriting Career', '1', 'the-value-of-consulting-in-developing-your-copywriting-career', '<p>Are you considering a career in copywriting?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Taking the plunge into a new career can be daunting, but understanding consulting is one of the best ways to start your journey as a copywriter. It allows you to gain experience and build relationships, while working with knowledgeable professionals in the field to gain valuable insights that can help jumpstart your career and get you on the path to success.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It seems clear that consulting can be helpful for developing and growing your career in copywriting. But just what does this entail, and how can it benefit you? For the answers to these questions, you are in the perfect place, and we have the information you are looking for. Continue reading to discover the advantages of consulting for copywriters.</p>', '2023-04-27 11:06:48', '2023-04-27 11:06:48'),
(232, 73, 'What Is Consulting In Copywriting?', '1', 'what-is-consulting-in-copywriting', '<h2>What Is Consulting In Copywriting?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>So, what is copywriting consulting? Consulting provides professional guidance for copywriters, including expert advice on marketing strategies, creating effective copy, and building a network of industry contacts. These services offer valuable insight into the copywriting industry, enabling individuals to make informed decisions about their career path.</p>', '2023-04-27 11:07:08', '2023-04-27 11:07:08'),
(233, 73, 'What Do Copywriting Consultants Do?', '1', 'what-do-copywriting-consultants-do', '<h2>What Do Copywriting Consultants Do?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A copywriting consultant provides a range of services, including:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Evaluating Writing Skills</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you work with a consultant, they will be able to evaluate your skills and abilities to determine the most suitable career path for each unique individual. This includes identifying suitable copywriting jobs for your skill set, as well as helping you refine your abilities to increase your value in the industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Developing Your Network</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Developing a strong professional network is essential for a successful career in copywriting. A consultant can offer guidance on building relationships with industry professionals and finding new work opportunities.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Providing Valuable Resources</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Consultants can provide access to industry contacts and insider information on copywriting trends and best practices, which can be valuable resources for staying current and gaining an advantage over other copywriters. They can also assist in keeping up with trends, improving skills as a copywriter, and potentially increasing chances of job opportunities.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Developing Your Writing Process</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Consultants can assist in improving writing skills for a successful copywriting career by providing guidance on research, audience analysis, and writing techniques to create effective copy.</p>', '2023-04-27 11:07:38', '2023-04-27 11:07:38'),
(234, 73, 'Benefits Of Copywriting Consulting', '1', 'benefits-of-copywriting-consulting', '<h2>Benefits Of Copywriting Consulting</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are advantages to seeking consulting services when starting a career as a copywriter, and these can include significant benefits such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Opportunity to Learn from Experience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>By working with a consultant, you can benefit from their years of expertise and experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Learning from both the successes and mistakes of others can be extremely beneficial in avoiding similar mistakes; use their wisdom and experience to move your career forward, rather than wasting time and energy repeating common mistakes or errors.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Strategic Advice</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Consulting also offers the chance to attain valuable strategic advice for approaching your copywriting business. Working with a consultant can provide valuable guidance on marketing and promoting yourself as a copywriter, as well as insights on optimising your career by building a business and making a reputable, reliable name for yourself within a crowded industry. The right consultant will consider your unique strengths, and be in an excellent position to help you market yourself effectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Expert Guidance</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Engaging the services of a consultant can offer valuable guidance and feedback, enabling your copywriting business to operate with optimal efficiency and effectiveness.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Making Connections</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting consultants can also help you make connections with the right people - both within and outside your industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Networking with established individuals in the industry can offer unique opportunities and valuable insights into current copywriting trends and developments.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Gaining Experience Of Your Own</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaborating with a copywriting consultant can provide valuable opportunities to enhance your skills in the field. By leveraging their expertise and guidance, you can expand your knowledge and gain experience that is beneficial for your career growth.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eventually, this experience can offer a comprehensive understanding of the industry and effective strategies for success - perfect for setting up as a business or copywriting consultant of your own in the future, or simply streamlining your current copywriting career.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Improving Efficiency</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Consulting services can assist in enhancing the efficiency of a copywriting business. Collaborating with a consultant provides an opportunity to learn how to effectively manage time and resources to increase productivity and profitability, resulting in meeting deadlines and expanding the business - all of which can be beneficial for a successful copywriting career.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overall, consulting can provide invaluable knowledge and guidance that is beneficial to furthering a copywriting career. Working with an experienced copywriting consultant can be a great way to gain the necessary advice and resources needed to build a lucrative, successful business in the industry.</p>', '2023-04-27 11:08:15', '2023-04-27 11:08:15'),
(235, 73, 'Can I Become A Copywriting Consultant?', '1', 'can-i-become-a-copywriting-consultant', '<h2>Can I Become A Copywriting Consultant?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Working with a copywriting consultant can be a great way to kickstart your career, but this is also a role that you can move into yourself down the line. Working as a copywriting consultant largely involves working with writers to <a href=\"https://demo91.co.in/dev/affiliatecontent/public/\">improve</a> their craft, or working with businesses to help them create better copy for their products and services. In either case, it&#39;s important to have a strong understanding of copywriting in order to be successful in this field.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This means understanding the fundamentals of writing and what techniques are most effective for creating engaging content that resonates with a target audience - tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/ubersuggest\">UberSuggest</a>, Auto Also Ask and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/answer-the-public\">Answer the Public</a> can be invaluable in performing keyword research and understanding what your audience wants to know.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You should also be familiar with the latest trends in copywriting and be able to apply these approaches to your own work, including understanding SEO and being able to use tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/surfer-seo\">Surfer SEO</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/page-optimizer\">Page Optimizer</a>, and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/keyword-surfer\">Keyword Surfer</a> to maximise SEO and ensure that your copy is seen by the right people. Finally, a good copywriting consultant should have excellent communication skills in order to effectively collaborate with clients.</p>', '2023-04-27 11:08:41', '2023-04-27 11:08:41'),
(236, 73, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-6', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Working with a consultant in copywriting can offer various advantages, including gaining experience, receiving professional advice, making industry connections, and improving business efficiency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Those who are interested in taking the next step into becoming a consultant should familiarise themselves with the basics of writing, understand the latest trends in copywriting, and have strong communication skills.</p>', '2023-04-27 11:09:05', '2023-04-27 11:09:05'),
(237, 74, 'The Benefits of Auditing Your Content for Improved Copywriting', '1', 'the-benefits-of-auditing-your-content-for-improved-copywriting', '<p>Writing effective and engaging copy is essential for any successful business. But how can you make sure that your copy is up to par? A content audit could be just the solution you need.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Conducting a content audit is a helpful way to improve your writing, as it can reveal areas for improvement, open opportunities to engage with your audience, and provide insights for creating stronger marketing messages. To learn more, read on to learn just what a content audit is, what you need to do, and how it can help your business.</p>', '2023-04-28 13:42:03', '2023-04-28 13:42:03'),
(238, 74, 'What Is A Content Audit?', '1', 'what-is-a-content-audit', '<h2>What Is A Content Audit?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A content audit involves conducting a thorough evaluation of your website, blog, or other written content. This assessment should consider the quality of existing content and its alignment with overall objectives, and also involves examining readability, optimization, the effectiveness of copy, and overall structure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Conducting a content audit can provide useful insights into the impact of your writing on readers and help identify areas for improvement - and tools like <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/readable\">Readable</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a> and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly </a>can be very useful in helping you achieve this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By auditing your content, you&rsquo;ll be able to identify weak points and make changes accordingly. This could include anything from improving the readability of your content, ensuring that it meets SEO standards, optimising your images and media, or even reworking the structure of a page to make it more engaging.</p>', '2023-04-28 13:42:40', '2023-04-28 13:42:40'),
(239, 74, 'Benefits Of Auditing Your Content', '1', 'benefits-of-auditing-your-content', '<h2>Benefits Of Auditing Your Content</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Auditing your content can provide a number of key benefits:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Identify Areas of Improvement</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the main benefits of conducting a content audit is that it can help you identify areas of improvement. By assessing your existing content, you can gain valuable insight into how well your writing is resonating with readers, and consider what needs to be improved in order to create more powerful, effective copy - this could include anything from ensuring that content is optimised for SEO to making sure that it&rsquo;s easy to understand.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Boost Your SEO Score</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>SEO optimization significantly affects the visibility and ranking of your website on search engine results pages. Conducting a content audit ensures that your content aligns with current SEO standards and allows for necessary improvements to increase your website&#39;s ranking - try using tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/surfer-seo\">SurferSeo</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/free-seo-optimization-tool\">Free SEO Optimization Tool</a>, or <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/seo-powersuite\">SEO Powersuite</a> to help enhance your results.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Engage Your Audience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A content audit can be useful in helping you to improve the effectiveness of your copy through boosted audience engagement. By analysing the structure and readability of your content, you can make necessary improvements to ensure your message is reaching your intended audience. This may involve breaking up large blocks of text or simplifying the language used.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Streamline Your Processes</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>By conducting a content audit, you can identify any areas or processes that are inefficient or need improvement. This could include anything from the time it takes to create and publish new content to the way you organise your existing assets. By streamlining these processes, you can save time and money while ensuring that your content is always up-to-date and relevant.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Gain Insight Into Your Audience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Conducting a content audit can also provide valuable information about your audience&#39;s preferences and interests, allowing you to create more effective content that directly addresses their needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Uncover Opportunities for Growth</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A content audit can help you uncover opportunities for growth. By analysing the effectiveness of your existing content, you can identify areas where you can make improvements or create new content to expand your reach. Additionally, auditing your content gives you a better understanding of what topics and formats are resonating with readers and how you can use this information to grow your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Save Time and Money</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A content audit can improve efficiency and reduce costs by simplifying the content creation and publication process. It involves identifying areas for improvement to update and optimise existing content for search engines. Furthermore, it can provide insight into reader interests in creating targeted and successful content.</p>', '2023-04-28 13:43:14', '2023-04-28 13:43:14');
INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(240, 74, 'How To Complete Your Content Audit', '1', 'how-to-complete-your-content-audit', '<h2>How To Complete Your Content Audit</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To complete a content audit, there are just a few steps to follow:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Compile A List of All Your Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>First, compile a list of all the content you have published on your website. This could include blog posts, product descriptions, landing pages, and any other type of content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know Your Goals</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The next step is to determine the goals you would like to achieve with your content. For example, are you looking to increase engagement or drive more traffic? This will help you identify areas where your existing content is falling short and what needs improvement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Common goals may include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Improve Your SEO results</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You may audit your content with the goal of improving your SEO results. This can be done by ensuring that all pages are optimised for relevant keywords and that the structure and formatting of the content are up to standard.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Increase Engagement</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Your content audit may also focus on increasing engagement. Analysing readability and understanding how readers interact with your content can help you make changes to improve engagement and ensure that your message is reaching its target audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Improve Your Conversion Rate</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you may audit your content to improve your conversion rate. This could include analysing the structure and readability of your copy to ensure that it is optimised for conversions, as well as making sure that all pages are up-to-date with the latest information about products and services.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Evaluate Your Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have a clear understanding of your goals, it&rsquo;s time to evaluate your content. This includes assessing factors such as readability, SEO optimization, relevance to your audience, and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Make Necessary Changes</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, make any necessary changes to ensure that your content is up-to-date and meets the latest standards for SEO. This could include anything from making sure your titles are optimised for search engines to rewriting sections of text that may be outdated or difficult to read.</p>', '2023-04-28 13:43:52', '2023-04-28 13:43:52'),
(241, 74, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-7', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A content audit is a great way to improve the effectiveness of your copywriting and ensure that your message is reaching its intended audience. By analysing the structure and readability of your content, you can make improvements to streamline processes and uncover growth opportunities - all of which is key to improving your overall success.</p>', '2023-04-28 13:44:18', '2023-04-28 13:44:18'),
(242, 75, 'How Google Maps Can Enhance Your Local Copywriting Strategy', '1', 'how-google-maps-can-enhance-your-local-copywriting-strategy', '<p>Are you looking for an effective way to enhance your local copywriting strategy? The answer may not be quite what you expect: Google Maps may be your secret weapon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With the help of Google Maps, you can tap into a powerful resource that will provide unique content ideas as well as insights into the target market in your local area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;From understanding local demographics to optimizing content for target audiences, Google Maps can be a valuable tool in improving your local copywriting strategy. In this article, we&rsquo;ll explore how you can use Google Maps to enhance your local copywriting efforts.</p>', '2023-05-01 05:38:03', '2023-05-01 05:38:03'),
(243, 75, 'What is Google Maps?', '1', 'what-is-google-maps', '<h2>What is Google Maps?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps is a web-based mapping service that offers satellite imagery, street maps, panoramic views, real-time traffic conditions, and route planning for different modes of transportation. It was launched on the internet in February 2005 and has achieved widespread popularity globally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps is a platform that provides directions and helps users discover nearby establishments. It also presents opportunities for effective local copywriting.</p>', '2023-05-01 05:38:29', '2023-05-01 05:38:29'),
(244, 75, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-facts', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>More than a billion people use Google Maps every month - this is an amazing resource that can really benefit your business - if you know how to use it properly.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 07:50:02', '2023-05-08 07:50:02'),
(245, 75, 'What Are The Benefits of Google Maps?', '1', 'what-are-the-benefits-of-google-maps', '<h2>What Are The Benefits of Google Maps?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps offers a range of benefits, and these include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Customizable Features</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>With Google Maps, you can customize features and information to suit your needs, including the ability to add labels and notes to maps, as well as filter map results by type of business or event. This makes it easy to find relevant content ideas for copywriting efforts.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Easy Accessibility</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps is compatible with any device that has an internet connection, allowing users to access it on their laptops, tablets, or smartphones. This feature provides convenient access to information when needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Reliable Source of Information</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps provides reliable information through regularly updated satellite imagery and local business/event information, ensuring accuracy and up-to-date content - good news for both business owners and customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Improved Local Marketing Strategies</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps can be used to improve local marketing strategies by helping you better understand local markets and target audiences. By using Google Maps to research local businesses and events, you can get an idea of the types of customers in a given area and tailor your copywriting efforts accordingly.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Enhanced SEO Efforts</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps can be used to optimize local search content, which can improve rankings and enhance reputation and presence in the local community, benefiting SEO efforts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-01 05:40:01', '2023-05-01 05:40:01'),
(246, 75, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-9', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Our team collaborated with a copywriter from the area to enhance the content for a real estate client. By utilizing Google Maps, we gained a better understanding of the local market and identified important demographics and competitors. This information helped us create tailored content that effectively engaged potential customers, leading to a rise in leads and website traffic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our clients reported that Google Maps provided valuable information about the local area, including search trends and keywords. This allowed us the opportunity for creating more relevant content for potential customers and improving our overall SEO performance. Our client expressed satisfaction with the results, including a significant increase in website traffic and leads.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 07:50:39', '2023-05-08 07:50:39'),
(247, 75, 'How You Can Use Google Maps For Copywriting', '1', 'how-you-can-use-google-maps-for-copywriting', '<h2>How You Can Use Google Maps For Copywriting</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps can provide valuable information to support the development of a copywriting strategy, with various options for utilization.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Get and Give Specific Directions</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps offers precise and comprehensive directions to nearby businesses, leading to enhanced customer satisfaction and demonstrating familiarity with the locality.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Understand the Target Audience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps provides demographic information about a given area, such as the types of businesses and establishments present. This information can be used to improve copywriting efforts and target specific audiences more effectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Find Local Events</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps can assist in locating local events that align with the target audience of your clients, making it easier to discover events that may appeal to potential customers, providing useful content ideas for copywriting endeavors.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Gain Insight Into Local Businesses</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps provides insight into local markets and businesses for copywriters. This helps create targeted content that speaks directly to a demographic. Detailed information on locations and businesses allows for campaigns tailored to a specific area or city. Understanding demographics allows for more effective targeting of potential customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Gain Insight Into Competitor Locations</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps offers useful insights for businesses seeking a competitive advantage. By identifying the locations of comparable businesses, you can evaluate their placement in the local market and use this data to inform your copywriting campaigns.</p>', '2023-05-01 05:41:13', '2023-05-01 05:41:13'),
(248, 75, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-facts-2', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>97% of users search online to find a local business - making the most of local SEO is a key element of ensuring that your business is a success.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 07:51:06', '2023-05-08 07:51:06'),
(249, 75, 'What Is Local SEO?', '1', 'what-is-local-seo', '<h2>What Is Local SEO?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Local SEO is a useful tool for businesses to enhance their appearance in search engine results within specific geographic locations. By optimizing digital assets such as websites and social media accounts, businesses can increase their visibility to potential customers seeking services or products in their area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Local SEO also helps businesses establish trust and credibility, as customers are more likely to trust a business that is located nearby.</p>', '2023-05-01 05:42:10', '2023-05-01 05:42:10'),
(250, 75, 'Other Tools For Local SEO', '1', 'other-tools-for-local-seo', '<h2>Other Tools For Local SEO</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Maps is a powerful tool for local copywriting, but it isn&#39;t the only tool available. Other local SEO tools that can help you with your copywriting efforts include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/moz-local\">Moz Local</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Moz Local is a software designed to assist businesses in enhancing their local listings on various platforms, including Google My Business and Apple Maps. It also provides comprehensive reports on listing performance and recommendations for enhancing local SEO outcomes.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/keywords-everywhere-seo-keyword-tool\">Keywords Everywhere</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Keywords Everywhere is a keyword research tool that offers insights into search terms used by local customers, providing information on location-related keywords to help businesses create content that targets potential customers in specific areas.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/wordstream-keywords\">Wordstream Keywords</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Wordstream Keywords is a keyword research tool that helps you find the most relevant keywords for your copywriting efforts. It provides data on local search volume and trends, so you can create content that is tailored to a specific area.</p>', '2023-05-01 05:42:33', '2023-05-01 05:42:33'),
(251, 75, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-8', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Utilizing Google Maps as a tool for local copywriting can provide valuable insights for targeting the intended audience, discovering local events, analyzing local businesses and competitors, and utilizing other local SEO tools to create successful campaigns.</p>', '2023-05-01 05:42:53', '2023-05-01 05:42:53'),
(252, 77, 'How to Use Google Drive to Streamline Your Copywriting Process', '1', 'how-to-use-google-drive-to-streamline-your-copywriting-process', '<p>Are you a copywriter looking for ways to streamline your workflow and make it more efficient? If so, Google Drive is an excellent choice. With its intuitive interface and a vast array of features, it can help you save time and be more productive. In this article, we&#39;ll discuss how to use Google Drive to organise your copywriting process, from planning content to storing research material. By the end, you&#39;ll be prepared to tackle any project with confidence.</p>', '2023-05-06 13:32:16', '2023-05-06 13:32:16'),
(253, 77, 'What is Google Drive?', '1', 'what-is-google-drive', '<h2>What is Google Drive?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Drive is a cloud storage and file-sharing platform developed by Google. It enables users to store, organise, and access files from any device with an Internet connection. With a single account, users can share documents and collaborate on projects in real-time. This makes it ideal for copywriters who need to stay connected with clients or co-workers while working remotely.</p>', '2023-05-06 13:32:41', '2023-05-06 13:32:41'),
(254, 77, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-14', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Google Drive hosts an average of two trillion files at any one time - if you are looking for a reputation that speaks for itself, this is a solid option.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 08:04:32', '2023-05-08 08:04:32'),
(255, 77, 'How to Use Google Drive for Copywriting', '1', 'how-to-use-google-drive-for-copywriting', '<h2>How to Use Google Drive for Copywriting</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>So, just how can you use Google Drive to make your copywriting easier? There are a number of benefits:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1.&nbsp; Create a Folder Structure</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The first step is to create a folder structure that will help you organise your copywriting project. To organise your files for a project, consider creating subfolders for various stages, like &quot;Planning&quot;, &quot;Writing&quot;, and &quot;Editing.&quot; This can aid in efficiently locating documents associated with each stage.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2.&nbsp; Upload Research Material</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Uploading research materials such as articles, videos, and images for the project can facilitate reference while writing or editing the copy - you will have all that you need immediately to hand, which can save you valuable time when working.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3.&nbsp; Create a Document Template</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To effectively serve multiple clients, it is recommended to establish a document template for each client, which includes their logo, brand guidelines, and other pertinent information - this will save you time when starting new projects, and ensure that you have all the data to hand.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4.&nbsp; Collaborate with Others</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To ensure easy accessibility for all members of a copywriting or editing team, it is recommended to share documents through Google Drive, as this can make it easy to make changes quickly and ensures everyone is on the same page.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>5.&nbsp; Keep Track of Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Drive enables users to manage and monitor all content created for a project, spanning from preliminary drafts to ultimate versions. Comparing and referencing various document versions is straightforward, guaranteeing precision and uniformity.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>6.&nbsp; Archive Projects</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Archiving completed copywriting projects in Google Drive allows for easy access, which can be crucial for client projects that require regular updates.</p>', '2023-05-06 13:34:07', '2023-05-06 13:34:07'),
(256, 77, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-10', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>When Ryan finally wrapped up a six-month project, he assumed that he would never hear from the client again. The project had been simple, if lengthy, deliverables had been approved, praised and signed off, and the business was thriving as it started down a new path. With a nod of approval, Ryan saved the files for the project in a far-off location on his laptop and went about his day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A few months later, he discovered an email in his inbox: the client wanted to get back in touch for further business, and was keen to use the same templates and formats as those established in the original project. Cue Ryan searched the endless files and sub-folders in the depth of his laptop, all while praying that he hadn&rsquo;t been foolish enough to delete the key item. Fortunately, his hard work paid off - but at the cost of his patience, stress levels and well-being!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the next project, Ryan decided to research some smarter ways to work: and discovered the ease and convenience of Google Drive, and the wider Google package. The rest, as they say, is history.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 08:05:02', '2023-05-08 08:05:02'),
(257, 77, 'What Are The Benefits of Using Google Drive?', '1', 'what-are-the-benefits-of-using-google-drive', '<h2>What Are The Benefits of Using Google Drive?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Drive offers a number of benefits for copywriters looking to streamline their workflow, from faster collaboration to better organisation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the main advantages of Google Drive include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Convenience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the main advantages of Google Drive is the ability to access and edit documents from anywhere - Google Drive allows you to work on projects wherever you are, as long as you have an Internet connection. This makes it easier to collaborate with remote teams or clients while still ensuring accuracy and quality.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Organisation</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Organising files into a folder structure on Google Drive can enhance accessibility and facilitate the location of relevant documents for each phase of a project, including planning, writing, and editing.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Cost-Effectiveness</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Drive is a free platform accessible to both individuals and businesses. With this technology, there is no need to purchase costly software or hardware. Additionally, it reduces the need for printing documents and simplifies the sharing of large files with colleagues or clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Businesses can choose to pay to access over 15 GB of storage, but with plans starting at just $6 per user per month, this is a cost-effective solution even if you decide to scale up.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Integration</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Drive has the capability to integrate with other Google products like Gmail and Google Docs, providing a convenient way to manage email correspondence and access all project-related documents in a single location.</p>', '2023-05-06 13:37:11', '2023-05-06 13:37:11'),
(258, 77, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-15', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Six million businesses pay for Google Drive - there must be something about it that keeps them coming back!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 08:05:31', '2023-05-08 08:05:31'),
(259, 77, 'What Other Tools Can I Use To Streamline The Copywriting Process?', '1', 'what-other-tools-can-i-use-to-streamline-the-copywriting-process', '<h2>What Other Tools Can I Use To Streamline The Copywriting Process?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to using Google Drive to streamline the copywriting process, there are a number of other tools that can help. Some of these include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Grammarly is an automated proofreading tool that helps identify spelling and grammar errors in written documents and suggests improvements to sentence structure and word choice.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The online editing tool allows users to detect and fix issues concerning the readability, clarity, and conciseness of their written work.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Google Docs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Docs is a word-processing tool that provides users with the ability to create and modify documents. In addition, it offers functionalities such as real-time collaboration and version control, all at no cost.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/surfer-seo\">SEO Surfer</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This tool can assist in optimising work with quality keywords for improved SEO results by automatically generating relevant keywords.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/google-trends\">Google Trends</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This tool provides analysis of the popularity of specific topics or keywords to assist in maintaining relevant and current content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Google Analytics</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics is an invaluable tool for monitoring how your website is performing and determining which pieces of content are resonating with readers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/trello\">Trello</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Trello is a project management and collaboration tool that helps you keep track of tasks, deadlines, and the overall progress of your copywriting projects. It enables you to create boards for different projects and assign tasks to team members. With Trello, you can also monitor each task&rsquo;s status, provide feedback on drafts, and create checklists, so no steps are missed during the writing process.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Time Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Time management is key for any copywriter to ensure projects are completed on schedule and to a high standard. To help manage your time more effectively, create a workflow plan and set realistic deadlines for each stage of the project. A great way to keep track of your progress is by setting up daily or weekly goals and breaking down large tasks into smaller ones. Tools like StayFocused can be very helpful here - they block time wasting websites and allow you to break down tasks to stay on track and avoid distractions.</p>', '2023-05-06 13:39:04', '2023-05-06 13:39:04'),
(260, 77, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-16', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Google Docs boasts over 25 million users across the world - this is a perfect platform that works hand in hand with Google Drive and allows you to smooth and streamline the entire copywriting process.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 08:06:02', '2023-05-08 08:06:02'),
(261, 77, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-9', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>By using Google Drive and the other tools mentioned above, copywriters can streamline their workflow and get their projects done more efficiently. By staying organised and taking advantage of the time-saving features of these tools, copywriters can ensure that they are producing quality work on time, and ensure that their clients are happy with the results of each and every article produced - all while making their own lives easier.</p>', '2023-05-06 13:40:09', '2023-05-06 13:40:09'),
(262, 78, 'The Importance of Visuals in Your Copywriting Portfolio', '1', 'the-importance-of-visuals-in-your-copywriting-portfolio', '<p>Copywriting portfolios are essential for any freelancer looking to showcase their skills and demonstrate their value to potential clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to written copy, including visuals in a portfolio is important for its success. Visuals have the ability to capture a reader&#39;s attention, convey information quickly, and offer an original approach to presenting ideas. Examples of visuals can range from drawings to screen captures, providing a variety of options for creating a distinctive portfolio. To help, we examined the ways in which visuals can enhance your copywriting portfolio and the resources available to assist you in your endeavour.</p>', '2023-05-06 14:01:15', '2023-05-06 14:01:15'),
(263, 78, 'What Are Visuals?', '1', 'what-are-visuals', '<h2>What Are Visuals?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Visuals, such as images, illustrations, screenshots, or videos, have the potential to enhance written work by making it more engaging and easier to understand for readers. When utilized effectively, visuals can provide a unique way to display ideas and concepts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are a number of benefits to using visuals in your copywriting portfolio, and these include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>They Help Break Up the Text</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When used effectively, visuals can break up long blocks of text and make it easier for readers to process. By including images and other visuals, you can draw in readers with interesting visual elements that capture their attention.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>They Can Help Illustrate Ideas</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Visuals can help illustrate complex concepts and ideas in a way that words alone cannot. From eye-catching screenshots to illustrations, visuals can help you communicate your ideas in a more engaging way.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>They Make Your Portfolio Stand Out</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Including visuals in your copywriting portfolio is a great way to make it stand out from the crowd. Visuals can draw in readers and showcase your skills in a unique and engaging way, helping you capture the attention of potential clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moreover, visuals are often shared more on social media platforms than plain text, which can be beneficial when you&rsquo;re trying to attract clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>They Improve The Experience For The Reader</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Incorporating visuals into a copywriting portfolio can enhance the reader&#39;s experience by providing context and simplifying complex concepts for easier comprehension. This allows for better information processing and understanding of the intended message.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>', '2023-05-06 14:07:54', '2023-05-06 14:07:54'),
(264, 78, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-17', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>60.8% of marketers agree visual content is absolutely necessary - if you are not including visuals, you are missing out on a lot of potential business.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 08:25:51', '2023-05-08 08:25:51'),
(266, 78, 'What Kinds of Visuals Can Be Included In My Copywriting Portfolio?', '1', 'what-kinds-of-visuals-can-be-included-in-my-copywriting-portfolio', '<h2>What Kinds of Visuals Can Be Included In My Copywriting Portfolio?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your copywriting portfolio can include various types of visuals, such as images, illustrations, screenshots, and other visuals that can display your skills and attract attention to your work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For instance, if you&rsquo;ve written a blog post about a particular topic, you could create an infographic or chart that summarises the key points. This would help readers quickly understand the content and will make your portfolio more interesting to look at. Additionally, you could also include screenshots of websites or other projects you&rsquo;ve worked on that demonstrate your skills.</p>', '2023-05-06 14:09:46', '2023-05-06 14:09:46'),
(267, 78, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-11', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>The client came to us with a copywriting portfolio that lacked visuals. They wanted to stand out from the competition, and they knew that adding visuals would help them do just that.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We took an in-depth look at their copywriting style and created visuals for several of their samples. We then sourced stock photography and illustrations that tied in with their work, as well as created screenshots of websites they had written content for. We also included a professional bio and client testimonials to add to the overall impact of their portfolio.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The end result was a portfolio that was visually engaging, easy to read and understand, and which showcased the client&#39;s work in the best possible light. The visuals we created allowed potential clients to get a better understanding of their copywriting skills, as well as boosting the client&#39;s confidence in their own work.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 08:26:53', '2023-05-08 08:26:53'),
(268, 78, 'Tools You Can Use to Create Visuals', '1', 'tools-you-can-use-to-create-visuals', '<h2>Tools You Can Use to Create Visuals</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are various tools available to assist with creating visuals for a copywriting portfolio, regardless of design expertise. The following are some of the most recommended tools in the industry:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/canva\">Canva</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Canva is an online design tool that makes it easy to create visuals, even if you don&rsquo;t have any design experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Adobe Photoshop&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Photoshop is the industry standard for image editing and illustration. It&rsquo;s a great tool for creating stunning visuals with ease.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Sketch</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Sketch is an illustration program designed for those who want to create vector graphics and illustrations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Including visuals in your copywriting portfolio is a great way to make it stand out from the competition. Visuals can enhance the reader&rsquo;s experience and make complex concepts easier to understand. From illustrations to screenshots, there is no shortage of ways to make your portfolio shine.</p>', '2023-05-06 14:11:09', '2023-05-06 14:11:09'),
(269, 78, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-18', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Readers spend an average of just 37 seconds on an article - use visuals to grab their attention, and keep them engaged.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 12:09:24', '2023-05-08 12:09:24'),
(270, 78, 'What Else Should Be Included In Your Copywriting Portfolio?', '1', 'what-else-should-be-included-in-your-copywriting-portfolio', '<h2>What Else Should Be Included In Your Copywriting Portfolio?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>While visuals are important, it should be noted that they are only one piece of the puzzle - there are other vital elements that should be included to show off to potential clients and reassure them that you can handle any project.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the main essentials to include are:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>High-Quality Samples of Your Best Work</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to including visuals, your copywriting portfolio should also include samples of your work that demonstrate the range of your skills. This could include blog posts, website content, and other pieces you&#39;ve written for clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When selecting samples, it is recommended to choose your highest quality work to ensure potential clients receive a favourable impression of your abilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Client Testimonials</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Including client testimonials in a copywriting portfolio can demonstrate experience and quality work to potential clients, providing insight into potential outcomes of working together, and showing that you have demonstrable experience and success.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Professional Bio</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Including a professional bio in your portfolio can help potential clients better understand your skills, writing style, and background, which may influence their decision to work with you - remember to double check all text with a spellchecker such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly</a>.</p>', '2023-05-06 14:13:38', '2023-05-06 14:13:38'),
(271, 78, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-10', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Including visuals in your copywriting portfolio is a great way to make it stand out from the competition and help potential clients gain a better understanding of the information you&rsquo;re presenting. By including high-quality samples, client testimonials and a professional bio, you can ensure that your portfolio is one of the most effective tools you have for attracting clients and showcasing your skills.</p>', '2023-05-06 14:13:59', '2023-05-06 14:13:59'),
(272, 79, 'Top Copywriting Strategies for an Effective Resume', '1', 'top-copywriting-strategies-for-an-effective-resume', '<p>Are you looking to write an effective resume that stands out from the competition? Writing a compelling and professional resume is key to landing an interview and getting your foot in the door. But how do you ensure that your resume stands out among the sea of other jobseekers? The answer lies in copywriting. Copywriting is the art of crafting persuasive words that draw attention, inspire action, and get results, and we have put together some top copywriting strategies to help you create a fantastic new effective resume:</p>', '2023-05-08 02:19:46', '2023-05-08 02:19:46'),
(273, 79, 'What Is A Resume?', '1', 'what-is-a-resume', '<h2>What Is A Resume?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A resume is a document that outlines your qualifications and experiences. It serves as an essential tool in the job search process, providing employers with an overview of your skills, achievements, and work history. A well-crafted resume can help you stand out among other applicants and increase the chances of landing an interview.</p>', '2023-05-08 02:20:27', '2023-05-08 02:20:27'),
(274, 79, 'What Should Be Included In Your Resume?', '1', 'what-should-be-included-in-your-resume', '<h2>What Should Be Included In Your Resume?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To create a professional and effective resume, it should include the following information:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Your Personal Information</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The first thing to include is your contact information. This should include your name, address, email, and phone number.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Education Information</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your resume should also include any educational qualifications you have achieved. List the schools you attended, degrees obtained, and certifications or awards received.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Experience/Employment History</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>List all of your previous jobs in chronological order, with a brief description of each role. Include details of the company, your job title and responsibilities, and any key achievements - remember to use specific examples.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Skills/Abilities</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your resume should also list any relevant skills or abilities that you possess. This could include any language abilities, computer skills, or other technical abilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>References</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you should include a few references at the end of your resume. It can be helpful to include a couple of references who can vouch for your skills and experiences.</p>', '2023-05-08 02:21:24', '2023-05-08 02:21:24'),
(275, 79, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-19', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>According to experts, recruiters spend just 6&ndash;8 seconds looking at each resume - so making sure that you make a sterling first impression is crucial to success.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 12:20:21', '2023-05-08 12:20:21'),
(276, 79, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-12', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Samantha was a recent college graduate who wanted to secure her dream job in marketing. She knew she had the skills and experience necessary, but wasn&#39;t sure how to showcase them properly in her resume.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to make her resume stand out, Samantha followed our top copywriting strategies for an effective resume. This included writing a compelling summary of her qualifications and accomplishments, tailoring her resume to the job, and including industry-specific keywords.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Samantha also used tools such as Grammarly and ProWritingAid to ensure that her resume was free from any errors. Additionally, she utilised Canva to create a visually pleasing resume that was sure to impress hiring managers. After making these changes, Samantha&rsquo;s resume reflected her qualifications and accomplishments in the best light possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The results spoke for themselves &ndash; with a well-written, optimised resume, Samantha was able to land her dream job in marketing.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 07:39:28', '2023-05-08 07:39:28'),
(277, 79, 'Top Tips For Crafting A Great Resume', '1', 'top-tips-for-crafting-a-great-resume', '<h2>Top Tips For Crafting A Great Resume&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>So, just what should you make sure that you include on a resume that is designed to really wow potential employers? There are a few top tips to keep in mind, and these include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Choose Your Language Wisely</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The language you use in your resume should be clear and concise; try and avoid using overly flowery language or jargon, as this can detract from the overall message you are trying to convey, and may put off potential employers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead, focus on strong action verbs that demonstrate your skills and capabilities - this will help to make your resume stand out and make a lasting impression. It also shows potential employers that you are efficient, and can focus on getting the job done properly. To help, consider <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/\">tools</a> such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/readable\">Readable </a>and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a> to check that your work is clear and easy to follow.</p>', '2023-05-08 02:23:44', '2023-05-08 02:23:44'),
(278, 79, 'Focus On Your Achievements', '1', 'focus-on-your-achievements', '<h3>Focus On Your Achievements</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A resume should focus on what you have accomplished in your career, not just the tasks that you have performed. Make sure to highlight any awards, achievements, and successes that you have had in order to show potential employers your value.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When writing about your experiences, instead of simply listing tasks, you should focus on the achievements or successes that you had in each role. This will help to demonstrate your value as an employee and provide potential employers with a more detailed picture of what you can bring to the role. For example, if you increase the customer satisfaction ratings at your previous job, make sure to include the figures and how you achieved them.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Formatting Matters</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have written your resume, it is important to make sure that it is easy to read and digest. Choose a font that is clear and legible, and keep the formatting consistent throughout. Use bullet points whenever possible, as this makes it easier for employers to skim-read and find the key information.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Showcase Your Skill Set</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Employers are looking for job candidates with specific skill sets, so make sure to showcase these in your resume. Describe the skills you possess, and provide examples of how you have used them in previous roles.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Use Storytelling</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A great way to make your resume stand out is to use storytelling techniques. Tell a story about how you had an impact on your previous employer or organisation. This will help employers remember you and demonstrate the value that you can bring to their organisation.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Tailor Your Resume to the Job</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When writing your resume, make sure to customise the content for each job you apply for. This means focusing on the skills and experience that are most relevant to the particular role you are applying for, and which demonstrate your suitability clearly and obviously - doing this shows potential employers that you have taken the time to tailor your resume specifically for them, and helps you come across as a candidate dedicated to taking their role seriously, which can really help you stand out against other candidates.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Use Industry-Specific Keywords</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Including industry-specific keywords in your resume can be a great way to stand out from other applicants. Employers may use these keywords when searching for job candidates, so make sure to include them in your resume where appropriate.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Create a Compelling Summary</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The summary section of your resume is an opportunity to showcase your achievements and make a good first impression on potential employers. Keep it succinct and avoid clich&eacute;d phrases such as &ldquo;hard-working&rdquo; or &ldquo;team player. Instead, focus on quantifying your accomplishments with concrete examples, such as how you saved money or increased productivity in a previous role.</p>', '2023-05-08 02:32:51', '2023-05-08 02:32:51'),
(279, 79, 'Top Tools To Help You Create The Perfect Resume', '1', 'top-tools-to-help-you-create-the-perfect-resume', '<h2>Top Tools To Help You Create The Perfect Resume</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are looking for a little more guidance, here are some top tools to help you ensure your resume is as good as it can be:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A key element of a successful resume is to ensure that it is free from spelling and grammar errors. Grammarly is a great tool for this, as it will detect any mistakes in your writing and provide suggestions on how to fix them.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>ProWritingAid</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>ProWritingAid is another great tool for ensuring that your resume is free from any errors. It also provides detailed reports on your writing, giving you insight into how to improve it.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Hemingway is an editing tool that helps to simplify your writing. It highlights complex sentences and suggests ways to make them simpler, helping your resume to be more concise and easier to read.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Canva</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For a creative touch, Canva can be used to design a visually pleasing and professional-looking resume. It provides templates and tools for creating beautiful resumes with ease.</p>', '2023-05-08 02:42:48', '2023-05-08 02:42:48'),
(280, 79, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-20', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Every live job advert receives an average of 250 applications - making sure that your resume stands out for the right reasons has never been so vital.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 07:40:10', '2023-05-08 07:40:10'),
(281, 79, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-11', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Writing a great resume is essential to get noticed by potential employers. By following the above strategies and using the right tools, you can create an effective resume that will help you stand out from the competition, and land you the job of your dreams.</p>', '2023-05-08 02:43:43', '2023-05-08 02:43:43'),
(282, 61, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-23', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Here is an example of a case study of individual insight. This is a reading block that people will be drawn to and read.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 07:59:58', '2023-05-08 07:59:58'),
(283, 45, 'Conclusion', '1', 'conclusion-7', '<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Writing content that&#39;s optimized for both humans and search engines is the biggest challenge that content marketers face.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Writing smarter content is the key to building your blog audience. SEO copywriting is not difficult so long as you remember that you need to write for people and not just search engines. It&#39;s all about:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Understanding the target audience so you&#39;re clear on search terms and search intent.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Using a focus keyword and then creating relevant short tail and long tail keywords.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Using your content to answer questions and solve problems for your reader.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Using things like incoming links, title tags, meta descriptions, etc. to signpost to Google without disrupting the human experience (keep it relevant).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Just follow the above principles of successful SEO copywriting to create high-ranking web content that excites people to buy your clients&#39; products and services and take their site to the first page of Google.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-08 13:11:25', '2023-05-08 13:11:25'),
(284, 80, 'The Benefits of Google Analytics for Measuring Content Success', '1', 'the-benefits-of-google-analytics-for-measuring-content-success', '<p>Do you want to understand how your content is performing online? To get an accurate idea of the success of your online content, Google Analytics is the tool for you. Google Analytics has the potential to offer valuable information on audience engagement with your content, and this can make a huge difference to your overall success. Read to learn more. Then read on - this article will explore the advantages of utilising Google Analytics for measuring content success.</p>', '2023-05-09 06:53:40', '2023-05-09 06:53:40'),
(285, 80, 'What Is Google Analytics?', '1', 'what-is-google-analytics', '<h2>What Is Google Analytics?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics is a valuable tool that allows you to measure the effectiveness of online content. By monitoring important metrics and engagement data, very useful insights can be gained regarding content performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When used correctly, Google Analytics offers extremely useful information on website traffic sources and content conversion rates, which can inform marketing strategy decisions when utilised correctly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re looking for ways to measure the success of your content, Google Analytics is the tool for you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With its powerful metrics and analysis capabilities, it can provide invaluable insights into how well your content is resonating with audiences.</p>', '2023-05-09 06:54:13', '2023-05-09 06:54:13'),
(286, 80, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-25', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Google Analytics is used by around 55.49% of all websites - by adding your business to this list, you can track the success of your content in a data-driven way. This includes tracking metrics such as page views, time on page, bounce rate and referrals. With this data, you can create better content that resonates with your audience and drives more engagement and conversions.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-09 06:56:00', '2023-05-09 06:56:00'),
(287, 80, 'Key Features of Google Analytics', '1', 'key-features-of-google-analytics', '<h2>Key Features of Google Analytics</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the main features of Google Analytics that can be beneficial for copywriters include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Monitor Traffic</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics provides information on website traffic and visitor origins, and this data can play a key role in identifying successful channels and resonating content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Measure Engagement</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics also provides the ability to measure user engagement with content, including tracking metrics like average time spent on a page and click-through rate - this is ideal for helping you determine which pages your audience is engaging with, and where you can make improvements.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Track Social Engagement</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Using Google Analytics lets you track social media engagement across different platforms. You can see which pieces of content are getting the most shares, likes, and comments.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Analyse Referral Sources</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics is a tool that can be utilised to track the sources of website traffic; analysing this information can help you to provide insight into which channels are most effective for content distribution.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Track Campaign Performance</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics can be used to track the effectiveness and performance of campaigns, allowing observation of which campaigns generate the most traffic and conversions. This information can be utilised to optimise strategies and focus efforts on the most successful tactics.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Optimise Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics offers insights into user behaviour and content performance, which can assist in improving engagement and conversions through content optimization.</p>', '2023-05-09 07:23:32', '2023-05-09 07:23:32');
INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(288, 80, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-13', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>One of our clients is a small business that sells handmade jewellery online. We set up Google Analytics to track their content performance and measure the success of their blog posts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Through the data, we identified which topics resonated best with the client&rsquo;s audience and tailored future content based on these insights. We also tracked referral sources to see which channels were driving the most traffic to the site. With this data, we were able to optimise the website for maximum visibility and engagement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The results? The client saw an increase in website visitors and conversions by over 50%. This was a fantastic result that would not have been possible without the insights provided by Google Analytics!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-09 07:24:09', '2023-05-09 07:24:09'),
(289, 80, 'How Can Google Analytics Help You Measure Content Success', '1', 'how-can-google-analytics-help-you-measure-content-success', '<h2>How Can Google Analytics Help You Measure Content Success</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>So, now that we have taken a closer look at the general benefits of Google Analytics, it is time to consider the ways in which you can use this tool to measure the success of your content. Some of the main options include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Measure Traffic Metrics</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As we mentioned, Google Analytics is great for measuring traffic to your site, and this is one of the best ways to measure the success of your content - if you track how much traffic it generates, you can get an indication of how successful it is.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics makes it easy to track key metrics such as unique visitors, page views, and average time on the page. With these insights, you can get a better grasp of how well your content is performing.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Analyse Visitor Behaviour</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics can be used by businesses to measure visitor behaviour, including the average time spent on a page and bounce rate, providing valuable insight into user engagement and areas for potential improvement.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Monitor Engagement</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics also lets you track how engaged users are with your content. You can see which pages they spend the most time on, where they click, and how deep into an article they read. These insights give you a better understanding of what content resonates best with your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Track Social Engagement</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>With Google Analytics, you can also measure how much social media attention your content is getting. This includes the number of shares, likes, and comments it receives across different platforms. This data can help you determine which content pieces are most popular and which strategies are driving the most engagement.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Follow Conversion Paths</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics allows you to track conversion paths for each user. You can see how visitors interact with your site before converting it into leads or customers. This can help you identify which content pieces are most effective in driving conversions.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Analyse Referral Sources</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics also lets you track which website sources are referring the most traffic to your site. This data can help you understand which channels are working best for your content and where you should focus your efforts.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Gain Actionable Insights</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Analysing data from Google Analytics can provide insights to improve content strategies. These insights can help identify popular content and effective channels for engaging with the audience. Content can then be tailored to better meet audience needs for increased success.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Track Competitors</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics can be utilised to monitor the performance of your competitors&#39; content - and this can be a real goldmine of information. By analysing this data, you can determine the most effective topics and strategies for your field, which can aid in the creation of superior content in comparison to your competition.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Establish Benchmarks</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics can also be used to establish benchmarks for future success. By tracking key metrics such as page views, time on page, and bounce rate, you can identify what your target audience likes and use that data to create better content in the future.</p>', '2023-05-09 07:48:30', '2023-05-09 07:48:30'),
(290, 80, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-26', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Google Analytics is most commonly used by marketers in the retail sector - if your business is in this industry, leveraging the insights from this tool can help you to identify which content pieces are resonating best with your audience and which strategies are driving engagement.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-09 07:50:41', '2023-05-09 07:50:41'),
(291, 80, 'Other Tools To Measure Content Success', '1', 'other-tools-to-measure-content-success', '<h2>Other Tools To Measure Content Success</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to Google Analytics, there are other tools that you can use to measure the success of your content. These include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Content Optimization Tools</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Content optimization<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/\"> tools</a> are useful for improving content engagement and conversions. They allow you to analyse keywords, topics, and content formats that are most effective for your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the best tools on the market include <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/surfer-seo\">Surfer SEO</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/semrush\">SEMrush</a>, and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/yoast\">Yoast SEO</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Social Media Analytics Tools</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Social media analytics tools offer information on the performance of your content on various social networks. They enable you to monitor likes, shares, comments, and other forms of engagement on each post. Popular tools include <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/screamingfrog\">Screaming Frog</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/seo-powersuite\">SEO Powersuite</a> and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/serpstat\">SerpStat</a>, amongst others. &nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-09 07:51:23', '2023-05-09 07:51:23'),
(292, 80, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-12', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Analytics is a useful tool for tracking content performance through metrics such as engagement, referrals, conversions, and competitor performance. These insights can inform content creation that better aligns with the target audience&#39;s needs and optimises success.</p>', '2023-05-09 07:51:45', '2023-05-09 07:51:45'),
(293, 81, '5 Creative Ways to Organise Your Copywriting Portfolio', '1', '5-creative-ways-to-organise-your-copywriting-portfolio', '<p>A copywriter&#39;s portfolio is a necessary aspect of their profession, serving as a platform to display their top-notch work, generate examples for potential clients, and ensure that all writing is well-organised. Looking for inspiration? Then here are five innovative strategies to help you arrange your copywriting portfolio.</p>', '2023-05-10 13:49:25', '2023-05-10 13:49:25'),
(294, 81, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-27', '<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>97% of business owners said that content marketing is part of their marketing strategy. Staying organised gives you the best chance of landing these lucrative clients, and so it is well worth investing in the time to find your perfect strategy.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-10 13:50:38', '2023-05-10 13:50:38'),
(295, 81, 'How To Organise Your Portfolio', '1', 'how-to-organise-your-portfolio', '<h2>How To Organise Your Portfolio</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are five organising options available for portfolios, and the most suitable one depends on personal style and the nature of clients and projects. Some of the best options include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Organise by Client</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Organising your copywriting portfolio by creating separate folders for each client can simplify the process of finding their work when necessary. Be sure to include a cover page for each client that clearly states what type of work was completed and when it was completed.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Organise by Project Type</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you work on many different types of projects, organising your portfolio by project type can be a great way to keep everything in order. Create folders for each type of project that you do, such as website copywriting, newsletter writing, press releases, etc., and place all relevant samples in those folders.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This means that if a client approaches for a specific type of work, you will have your samples ready to present.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Organise by Platform</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you write for different types of platforms, such as print media or online media, create folders for each platform to keep all of your work organised. You can then create sub-folders for each type of project, such as print ads, website content, etc, and this will help you locate projects and pieces of work whenever required.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Organise by Genre</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Categorising your portfolio based on the genre can be useful in showcasing your expertise in specific writing styles, like technical or creative writing, allowing potential clients to easily locate relevant writing samples and quickly determine whether you are a match for their business.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Organise by Date</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Organising a portfolio by date can provide practical benefits for those who update it frequently and wish to keep a record of their work over time. Additionally, it may simplify the process of locating samples from a specific time frame - you can simply head to the relevant file, and locate the piece as needed with minimal fuss or stress.</p>', '2023-05-10 13:51:24', '2023-05-10 13:51:24'),
(296, 81, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-14', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>A successful copywriter, Emma, was looking for ways to organise her portfolio to make it more attractive and easier for potential clients to navigate, as she was struggling to get new work. She started by writing a professional profile and including it in her portfolio, as well as adding visuals to showcase her previous work. As Emma worked with a range of new clients frequently, she decided that organising her portfolio by the client was the secret to success - and it worked!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Soon enough, Emma&#39;s portfolio was becoming one of the most organised and well-presented in the industry. By keeping her portfolio organised and up to date, she was able to land more clients and grow her business, and she continues to thrive and flourish today.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-10 13:52:01', '2023-05-10 13:52:01'),
(297, 81, 'What To Include In Your Portfolio', '1', 'what-to-include-in-your-portfolio', '<h2>What To Include In Your Portfolio</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Now that we have taken a look at the best organisation options, you may be wondering what type of content you should include in your portfolio. Some of the most important essentials include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Writing Samples</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your portfolio should include examples of the writing you have done for different projects. This can be anything from blog posts or website copy, to press releases and white papers. Make sure to include a variety of samples, so potential clients can get an idea of your range as a writer - always check your samples with <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/\">tools </a>such as&nbsp; <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly </a>before including them!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Positive Feedback and Testimonials</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Including positive feedback from past clients and reviews from industry professionals can enhance your credibility as a writer and demonstrate your reliability and competence - this shows you have a strong background in the industry and builds trust.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Your Key Skills</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A crucial element to add to your portfolio is a comprehensive list of your writing skills. It should encompass your proficiency in creating various types of content and your capacity to write convincingly and efficiently. It&#39;s also important to be clear about what type of writing you specialise in - this can help potential clients know exactly what they&#39;re getting themselves into, and reassure them that you are capable of delivering on their project. Make sure you use a tool such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a> or <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/readable\">Readable </a>to keep this section accessible and clear.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Your Professional Profile</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When building a portfolio, it&#39;s crucial to feature a professional profile that highlights your writing experience, specialisations, and relevant qualifications. Providing links to related websites, like a portfolio or LinkedIn profile, can help clients easily find you.</p>', '2023-05-10 13:52:46', '2023-05-10 13:52:46'),
(298, 81, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-28', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>40% of all business owners said they outsource copywriting - there are plenty of clients just waiting to be impressed by your skills and talents.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-10 13:53:22', '2023-05-10 13:53:22'),
(299, 81, 'Digital or Physical?', '1', 'digital-or-physical', '<h2>Digital or Physical?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Deciding between a digital or physical portfolio depends on your needs and preferences. Digital portfolios are convenient as they are easily accessible and quickly updated. However, if you prefer a physical copy, you can opt for a printed version.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It can be a good idea to cover both bases and have a digital version that you can easily share with potential clients, as well as a physical copy for in-person meetings - this allows you to enjoy the very best of both worlds!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is beneficial to include visuals in your portfolio along with written content, such as screenshots of your work and design elements. This provides potential clients with a better understanding of your capabilities as a copywriter.</p>', '2023-05-10 13:53:55', '2023-05-10 13:53:55'),
(300, 81, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-13', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating an effective portfolio is a great way to showcase your skills as a copywriter and make sure potential clients can find and access your work. By including samples, positive feedback, social proof, your key skills, a professional profile, and visuals in your portfolio, you can ensure that it stands out from the competition. Organisation is key here - make sure you keep your portfolio up to date, and take some time to ensure that it is easy to navigate and professional.</p>', '2023-05-10 13:54:19', '2023-05-10 13:54:19'),
(301, 82, 'How to Make Client Value a Core Element of Your Copywriting Business Mode', '1', 'how-to-make-client-value-a-core-element-of-your-copywriting-business-mode', '<p>As a copywriter, you know the importance of building relationships with clients and providing them with value. But have you ever thought about how to make client value a core element of your business model? Whether you&#39;re just starting out or already established in the copywriting industry, understanding the basics of making client value a priority will help ensure success. In this article, we&#39;ll explore practical tips on how to make clients value the foundation of your copywriting business.</p>', '2023-05-11 08:15:31', '2023-05-11 08:15:31'),
(302, 82, 'What Is Client Value?', '1', 'what-is-client-value', '<h2>What Is Client Value?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Client value is defined as being the benefit that your clients receive from working with you. This refers to not only the actual copywriting services you provide, but also other key, intangible elements such as trust, expertise, and customer service.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you make client value a core element of your business model, it means that you strive to exceed your client&rsquo;s expectations in all aspects of the experience, creating a positive customer journey from initial contact, to final sign-off on the project.</p>', '2023-05-11 08:15:58', '2023-05-11 08:15:58'),
(303, 82, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-29', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Brands with superior customer experience bring in an average of 5.7 times more revenue, compared to their competitors who lack this attention to the customer experience.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-11 08:16:37', '2023-05-11 08:16:37'),
(304, 82, 'How Can You Center Client Value At The Heart of Your Business?', '1', 'how-can-you-center-client-value-at-the-heart-of-your-business', '<h2>How Can You Center Client Value At The Heart of Your Business?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to prioritize client value in your copywriting business, consider implementing several steps. For inspiration, here are some examples.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Understand Your Clients&rsquo; Needs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The first step in making client value a priority is to get to know your clients and understand their needs. To prepare for working with a company, take some time to research their industries, products, and services, as well as their goals and objectives. This will allow for a deeper understanding of how you can provide value and create impactful copy that is tailored to each specific client.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Develop an Effective Communication Strategy</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To prioritize client value, it is essential to establish a clear and effective communication strategy to keep them informed and satisfied. This can be achieved through regular meetings or calls and an open line of communication, ensuring that you are always on hand to address any concerns or queries and that you remain open and accessible - this can go a long way to building trust and reassurance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Using persuasive language and visual aids can also help convey important information, so make these a key part of your strategy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Make the most of communication <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/\">tools</a> such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/trello\">Trello </a>and Slack to maintain contact with clients, ensuring accurate and current project updates and delivery timelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Build Trust</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Trust is a crucial factor in any successful business relationship. To establish trust with clients, it&#39;s important to showcase reliability, professionalism, and dedication to high-quality work. This includes factors such as delivering work on time, maintaining honesty and transparency, and promptly addressing any requests they may have.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Effective customer service involves timely responses to inquiries, providing valuable advice and updates on project progress, and establishing trust to ensure client satisfaction - tick all of these boxes, and you will boost your success rates.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Display Your Expertise</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It goes without saying that producing quality work is essential for any copywriter. Take the time to research your clients&rsquo; industries, understand their needs, and deliver content that meets or exceeds their expectations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To effectively serve clients, it is essential to have expertise and knowledge relevant to their industry. Researching industry challenges and staying up-to-date on copywriting trends, making the most of key industry resources, and providing valuable services will lead to the creation of quality work and value for clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Always make sure that your work is of the highest quality with tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly </a>and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a> - poor spelling or grammar looks unprofessional, and can damage your relationship with your client.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Offer Value Above and Beyond the Norm</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As well as offering a great copy, you also need to go one step further. One of the best ways to make client value a priority is to offer value above and beyond the norm. This could involve creating unique content, developing groundbreaking copy, or coming up with innovative ideas that help your clients stand out from the competition. Take the time to think outside the box and focus on what makes your clients&rsquo; businesses special.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This can include conducting extensive research before you get started - make the most of tools such as<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hubspots-blog-topic-generator\"> HubSpot Blog Topic Generator</a> to come up with unique, relevant topics, and using<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/google-trends\"> Google Trends </a>to ensure that you are always up-to-date on the latest developments in their industry - this will help you to create copy that resonates with their audience and provides real value.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Make Your Services Flexible</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to making client value a priority, it&#39;s important to make your services flexible so that you can accommodate different requests from clients. You may want to offer discounts, special packages, and other perks to show your clients that you&#39;re willing to go the extra mile. This is a great way to demonstrate your commitment to client value, and it will help ensure you get repeat business in the future.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Showcase Your Results</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To demonstrate the effectiveness of your copywriting services, it&#39;s recommended to compile case studies, testimonials, and other relevant materials that illustrate the value you&#39;ve delivered to clients. This approach can instil confidence and provide evidence of your successful track record to prospective clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Create a Positive Experience From Start To Finish</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your relationship with your clients should be friendly and professional. Make sure you have an open line of communication and strive to create a positive experience for your clients - this will help you foster long-term relationships, and ensure that you can enjoy a successful copywriting business.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Establish Clear Expectations</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To ensure that your clients get the value they deserve, it&#39;s important to establish clear expectations from the start. Make sure you discuss deadlines, budget, and other details upfront so that there are no misunderstandings later on. This will help create a smoother working relationship and keep everyone on the same page throughout the process.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Invest in Yourself</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, it&#39;s important to invest in yourself and your business. Take the time to attend conferences and workshops, read relevant books and articles, and continue learning about the industry. This will help you stay on top of trends and develop your skills so that you can provide the best possible services for your clients - remember, you can&#39;t pour from an empty cup, so take the time to take care of yourself and your business.</p>', '2023-05-11 08:29:20', '2023-05-11 08:29:20'),
(305, 82, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-30', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Customer-centric companies are around 60% more profitable compared to companies that don&#39;t put their customers first - make sure your company is one of these by placing client value at the heart of your experience.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-11 08:30:26', '2023-05-11 08:30:26'),
(306, 82, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-15', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>As professionals, we understand that our clients need to feel valued and appreciated. That&#39;s why we make it a priority to go above and beyond for each of our clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, one of our recent projects involved teaming up with a major retail chain to deliver a comprehensive copywriting package that included SEO-optimized web copy, social media content, product descriptions, and more - a very exciting opportunity for the team.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To ensure that our client received the most value out of our services, we made sure to stay in close contact throughout the project. Before getting started, we worked to ensure that expectations were clear on both sides, that we had a good understanding of the client&#39;s needs and goals, and that our timelines were realistic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Throughout the project, we kept our clients updated on our progress and made sure to answer any questions they had. We also went beyond the original scope of the project to ensure that their content was SEO-optimized, engaging, and delivered on time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the end of the project, our client was incredibly happy with the results and the value they received from working with us. This is an example of why we always make sure that client value is at the core of what we do as a business - a small change really can make all the difference.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-11 08:31:16', '2023-05-11 08:31:16'),
(307, 82, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-14', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>By making client value a core element of your copywriting business model, you can ensure that you are providing quality services and creating value for your clients. This will help you build trust and foster long-term relationships with your clients, and ultimately help you grow your business into a successful, long-lasting enterprise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-11 08:31:39', '2023-05-11 08:31:39'),
(308, 83, 'How Guest Blogging Can Improve Your Copywriting Skills', '1', 'how-guest-blogging-can-improve-your-copywriting-skills', '<p>Guest blogging is a useful tool for copywriters to enhance their writing skills, regardless of their level of experience. It provides opportunities to create engaging content for diverse audiences, which can increase your marketability and improve your chances of securing new writing opportunities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keen to get started with guest blogging, but not sure where to start? Well, read on to discover how guest blogging can help you hone your copywriting skills.</p>', '2023-05-12 14:29:57', '2023-05-12 14:29:57'),
(309, 83, 'What Do We Mean By Guest Blogging?', '1', 'what-do-we-mean-by-guest-blogging', '<h2>What Do We Mean By Guest Blogging?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Guest blogging involves creating content for another website or blog, and this offers a wide range of benefits such as increased visibility, enhanced credibility, and opportunities for networking with other professionals in your industry. By creating content for someone else&#39;s website, you can show off your writing skills and establish yourself as an authority in the copywriting space.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Guest blogging encompasses various forms, such as blog post writing, social media content creation, and video series development. The possibilities are endless!</p>', '2023-05-12 14:30:27', '2023-05-12 14:30:27'),
(310, 83, 'The Benefits Of Guest Blogging For Copywriters', '1', 'the-benefits-of-guest-blogging-for-copywriters', '<h2>The Benefits Of Guest Blogging For Copywriters</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>So, just why should you get started with guest blogging? Here are a few benefits you can enjoy!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Improve Your Writing Skills</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Guest blogging for other sites offers valuable opportunities to enhance your writing skills by allowing you to practice various structures, topics, and styles to produce engaging and&nbsp;interesting content, ultimately leading to improved copywriting and writing abilities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating content for various websites and target audiences can facilitate the development of your writing skills and enhance your abilities as a copywriter. Through each piece, you can acquire useful experience and improve your capacity to compose more impactful copy that connects with readers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Build Your Authority</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Guest blogging provides you with an opportunity to reach new audiences and establish yourself as an authority in the copywriting space. It&rsquo;s a great way to network and build relationships with other professionals in your field, which can lead to more job opportunities down the line.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Increase Your Visibility</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Writing for other websites can enhance your visibility and increase your marketability as a copywriter. Having a portfolio of previous work can increase your chances of being considered for future job opportunities by potential employers or clients, and is a key weapon in your arsenal.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Expand Your Reach</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Guest blogging has the potential to increase the visibility of your work and expand your audience, as it provides an opportunity to connect with new readers and engage with them through comments and social media - this is perfect for boosting your presence and reputation.</p>', '2023-05-12 14:31:52', '2023-05-12 14:31:52'),
(311, 83, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-31', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>According to experts, guest blogging is one of the top ways to drive organic traffic to your site, making it a crucial tool to boost SEO and improve your copywriting skills.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-12 14:32:23', '2023-05-12 14:32:23'),
(312, 83, 'How To Get Started With Guest Blogging', '1', 'how-to-get-started-with-guest-blogging', '<h2>How To Get Started With Guest Blogging</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>So, now that we know the benefits, just how do you get started? Here are a few ideas:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Find The Right Platforms</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you start writing content for another website, you need to find the right platform. Look for sites that align with your skillet and target audience, and consider how much time you can devote to guest blogging - this is important for ensuring that the platform you choose won&rsquo;t be too demanding on your schedule.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Pitch Ideas</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you&rsquo;ve identified a few potential platforms, it&rsquo;s time to start pitching ideas. Brainstorm different topics and angles that you could write about, and reach out to the site&rsquo;s editor with your ideas. Make sure to include relevant examples of your work, so they can get a sense of your writing style.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Create Quality Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you&rsquo;ve been accepted as a guest blogger, it&rsquo;s time to put your skills to the test. Write compelling and engaging content that&rsquo;s tailored to your target audience. Make sure to proofread your work and add relevant images, videos, or graphics to keep readers engaged.</p>', '2023-05-12 14:32:59', '2023-05-12 14:32:59'),
(313, 83, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-32', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>60% of bloggers write an average of five guest posts per month - this is a great way to hone your copywriting skills and establish yourself as an authority.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-12 14:33:32', '2023-05-12 14:33:32'),
(314, 83, 'How To Ensure Your Articles Hit The Mark', '1', 'how-to-ensure-your-articles-hit-the-mark', '<h2>How To Ensure Your Articles Hit The Mark</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>When creating any type of copy, quality is the key priority - but this can be particularly important for guest blogging, which is all about building your authority. To make sure your articles hit the mark, here are a few tips to bear in mind:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Research Your Topic Thoroughly</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Make sure you have a thorough understanding of the topic you&rsquo;re writing about before you start; this will help you create more compelling content and establish yourself as an authority in the field. Start by researching the topic and gathering relevant data that you can refer to in your article.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be Authentic And Engaging</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your writing should be authentic, engaging, and informative; the purpose of an article is to provide readers with valuable information and a sense of learning upon completion, so make sure you use a conversational tone and incorporate personal anecdotes - this can enhance the relatability of the content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Create Visuals</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Incorporating visuals, such as images, videos, or infographics, can enhance the presentation of your article by adding visual interest and simplifying complex ideas.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Understand SEO</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To increase the visibility of your article, it is important to have a good understanding of SEO and to optimize your content accordingly. This includes researching appropriate keywords, implementing them in headings and throughout the text, and including a few internal links to other pages on the website.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Use Quality Tools</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You should also make your life easier by taking advantage of different tools that can help you create better-quality content. Some of the main tools to take advantage of include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Grammarly&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Grammarly is a useful tool for reviewing grammar, spelling, and punctuation. It can assist in detecting any mistakes or oversights that may have occurred during proofreading.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Hemingway Editor</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Hemingway editor is a useful tool for enhancing the clarity of your writing. It can assist in recognizing convoluted sentences and proposing methods for streamlining them, thus rendering them more comprehensible.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Google Trends</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s a good idea to stay up-to-date with the latest trends, and Google Trends can help you do that. This tool allows you to see which topics are currently trending, so you can tailor your content accordingly.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Answer The Public</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Understanding the inquiries people have about a particular topic is crucial for effective content creation. Answer The Public is a useful tool that generates keyword-specific questions that individuals have searched for.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>UberSuggest</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>UberSuggest is a useful tool for keyword research and generation. It can assist in identifying keywords that are popular and not overly competitive, enabling you to optimize your content more effectively.</p>', '2023-05-12 14:35:03', '2023-05-12 14:35:03'),
(315, 83, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-16', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Karen is a copywriter looking to improve her copywriting skills and build her reputation in the industry. After doing some research, she decided to start guest blogging. She used a variety of quality tools to optimize her content, including Grammarly for grammar and punctuation checks, Hemingway Editor for readability checks, Google Trends to stay up-to-date with trends, Answer The Public to generate keyword-specific questions, and UberSuggest to research relevant keywords.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By following these steps, Karen was able to consistently create quality content that resonated with her target audience. After a few months of guest blogging, she noticed an increase in her website traffic and more inquiries from potential clients. She also gained valuable industry contacts and was able to gain recognition as a copywriter. Karen&rsquo;s success is a testament to the power of guest blogging and the importance of utilizing quality tools and resources, and the difference that this can make to your copywriting career.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-12 14:35:38', '2023-05-12 14:35:38'),
(316, 83, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-15', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Guest blogging is an effective way to hone your copywriting skills and build your authority within your industry. However, it&rsquo;s important to make sure you&rsquo;re creating quality content that resonates with your target audience. By following the tips above, you can ensure your articles hit the mark and help to build your reputation as a copywriter.</p>', '2023-05-12 14:36:00', '2023-05-12 14:36:00'),
(317, 84, 'How to Align Your Website Copywriting with Your Content Strategy', '1', 'how-to-align-your-website-copywriting-with-your-content-strategy', '<p>Having a well-designed website that effectively communicates with your intended audience is crucial for achieving success in the current digital environment. However, it is not sufficient to simply have an impressive design - it is equally important to ensure that your website copywriting is aligned with a robust content strategy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Implementing a comprehensive content strategy can enhance your website&#39;s search engine optimization and ensure cohesive communication with your intended audience. We took a closer look at what we mean by a content strategy, and how you can align your website copywriting with it.</p>', '2023-05-15 10:16:06', '2023-05-15 10:16:06'),
(318, 84, 'What Is A Content Strategy?', '1', 'what-is-a-content-strategy', '<h2>What Is A Content Strategy?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A content strategy is a comprehensive plan for creating and delivering content that meets the needs of your target audience. It involves research, planning, and implementation of various types of content across multiple channels. From blogs and podcasts to videos, infographics, and white papers, a content strategy should be tailored to meet the goals of your organisation while also providing value to your readers.</p>', '2023-05-15 10:16:37', '2023-05-15 10:16:37'),
(319, 84, 'What Should Be Included In A Content Strategy?', '1', 'what-should-be-included-in-a-content-strategy', '<h2>What Should Be Included In A Content Strategy?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to website copywriting, your content strategy should include research on keyword optimization, SEO best practices, and the use of tone, style, and language that resonates with your target audience. We took a closer look at some of these elements below:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Keyword Optimization</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Keeping up with current trends and understanding the language of your target audience is key to creating content that will be successful. Utilising keyword research tools like <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/google-trends\">Google Trends</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/also-asked\">Also Asked</a> and others can help you determine which keywords are most commonly used in your industry and by your target audience. This will allow you to create content that is optimised for search engines, helping to increase your website&#39;s visibility.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Tone and Style</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As you write content for your website, it&#39;s important to consider the tone and style of your writing. Your copy should be easy to understand and engaging, but also reflect the values of your organisation. Using tools like <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a> can help you ensure that your content is clear and concise while avoiding common grammar mistakes.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Readability</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your website&#39;s copy should be written in a way that is easy to read, understand, and digest. The use of tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/readable\">Readable </a>can assist in assessing the readability of content and modifying it to ensure accessibility for all readers.</p>', '2023-05-15 10:17:18', '2023-05-15 10:17:18'),
(320, 84, 'What Is Website Copywriting?', '1', 'what-is-website-copywriting', '<h2>What Is Website Copywriting?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Website copywriting is the craft of writing content for websites. It includes creating both the design and the words used on a website, as well as optimising them for search engine ranking. A successful website copywriter must be able to write compelling copy that resonates with the target audience, while also ensuring that all text is optimised according to SEO best practices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When crafting website copy, it&#39;s important to keep in mind the overall content strategy and ensure that all text is aligned with it. Doing so will help to ensure that your website copywriting works together to create a cohesive story and communicates effectively to your target audience.</p>', '2023-05-15 10:17:44', '2023-05-15 10:17:44'),
(321, 84, 'Why Does Your Website Copy Need To Align With Your Content Strategy?', '1', 'why-does-your-website-copy-need-to-align-with-your-content-strategy', '<h2>Why Does Your Website Copy Need To Align With Your Content Strategy?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Aligning your website copywriting with your content strategy is essential for creating a cohesive, engaging experience for visitors to your website. This ensures that all of the text on your site works together to create a single story and help visitors better understand who you are and what you offer. Additionally, proper alignment can help optimise your website for search engine rankings, ensuring that more people are able to find and visit your website.</p>', '2023-05-15 10:18:15', '2023-05-15 10:18:15'),
(322, 84, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-33', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>60% of businesses do not have a solid marketing strategy, putting them at a serious disadvantage compared to their competition. Aligning website copywriting with content strategy is an essential element of a successful marketing strategy, as it helps to ensure that your message reaches the right people and drives conversions.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-15 10:18:44', '2023-05-15 10:18:44'),
(323, 84, 'How To Align Your Website Copywriting With A Content Strategy', '1', 'how-to-align-your-website-copywriting-with-a-content-strategy', '<h2>How To Align Your Website Copywriting With A Content Strategy</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Wondering just how you can align your website copywriting with a content strategy? Here are a few tips to get you started:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Start With Research</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you begin writing for your website, it&#39;s important to do some research. Take the time to understand who your target audience is, what their needs and interests are, and what kind of language they use. This will help you identify the right keywords to target in order to optimise your content for search engine rankings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The importance and significance of research cannot be overstated. Whether you are creating a website, blog post, or any other type of content, research is key to ensuring that your content is highly relevant and engaging.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tools such as Google Trends and Also Asked can be very useful in understanding the most popular search terms and topics related to your industry, and can really help you to get your head around just what your audience are searching for, and the type of content you need to produce.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Establish A Tone Of Voice</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have done your research, it&#39;s time to establish a tone of voice for your website copywriting. This includes deciding on the language, style, and tone that best suits your target audience. It&#39;s important to consider factors such as age, gender, education level, and interests when creating a tone of voice for your website - make the most of tools such as Hemingway and Readable to ensure that the content produced is suitable for your chosen audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Focus On The User Experience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To improve the user experience, it is important to create content that is clear, engaging, and relevant to your target audience. Structuring the copy on your website in an organised manner is crucial for easy navigation and understanding, which can lead to longer visitor engagement and desired actions.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Optimise For Search Engines</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, it&#39;s important to optimise your website copywriting for search engines. As we mentioned previously, utilising keywords in the right way can help to improve your search engine rankings and make sure that people can find your content easily. There are a number of tools available that can help you identify which keywords to target and how to incorporate them into your content - make sure that you use these wisely.</p>', '2023-05-15 10:19:59', '2023-05-15 10:19:59'),
(324, 84, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-17', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>One example of a successful website copywriting alignment with content strategy can be seen in the recent overhaul of the website for Kaleidoscope Toys. The company, which specialises in unique and traditional toys for children, needed to update their website to better engage their target audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To do this, they began by researching their customers&rsquo; needs and interests. Based on this research, they identified the keywords that would be relevant to their target audience. This enabled them to create content that was highly relevant and optimised for search engine rankings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They then took this a step further by creating a tone of voice that was conversational, friendly, and easy to read. This helped to ensure that visitors to the website felt comfortable and connected with the brand&rsquo;s message. Finally, they focused on the user experience by creating a website that was easy to navigate and understand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The result of this process was a website that was highly optimised for search engines, engaging and relevant for their target audience, and easy to use. Kaleidoscope Toys&rsquo; website overhaul has been incredibly successful, leading to an increase in traffic and sales for the company.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-15 10:20:49', '2023-05-15 10:20:49'),
(325, 84, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-34', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>38% of businesses consider themselves to be part of a highly competitive industry - having a solid, robust content strategy is essential for staying ahead of the competition.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-15 10:21:19', '2023-05-15 10:21:19'),
(326, 84, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-16', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Developing website copy that aligns with your content strategy is crucial for presenting a unified narrative and facilitating an enjoyable visit for your website&#39;s users. By adhering to the guidelines laid out in this article, you can guarantee that all content on your site collaborates to convey your message effectively to your intended audience and enhance your search engine optimization.</p>', '2023-05-15 10:21:42', '2023-05-15 10:21:42'),
(327, 85, 'The Benefits of a Collaborative Content Strategy', '1', 'the-benefits-of-a-collaborative-content-strategy', '<p>A collaborative content strategy can be a useful method for businesses aiming to improve their online presence by working together towards a common goal. This article discusses the benefits of a collaborative content strategy for businesses, including increased traffic and engagement, improved targeting of audiences, lead generation, and better customer relationships.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We also took a closer look at some of the top tips for creating an effective collaborative content strategy, such as using project management tools, like Trello and Ideaflip, to organise tasks; utilising collaboration tools such as Almanac to share ideas and resources, and setting up phased timelines to ensure on-time delivery.</p>', '2023-05-16 14:17:49', '2023-05-16 14:17:49'),
(328, 85, 'What is A Collaborative Content Strategy?', '1', 'what-is-a-collaborative-content-strategy', '<h2>What is A Collaborative Content Strategy?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As the name suggests, a collaborative content strategy is a strategic approach to creating digital content that leverages the skills and resources of multiple parties. It involves teams building upon each other&rsquo;s ideas, working together to create high-quality content that can be used to establish a strong brand presence online and increase engagement with customers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The collaboration process allows organisations to leverage different perspectives, experiences, and expertise from their partners to create content that resonates with their target audience.</p>', '2023-05-16 14:18:21', '2023-05-16 14:18:21');
INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(329, 85, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-35', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>According to research, companies that collaborate are 30% more innovative and at least 36% more productive than those that don&#39;t - this is a clear indication of the potential benefits of a collaborative content strategy.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-16 14:19:00', '2023-05-16 14:19:00'),
(330, 85, 'Benefits of Collaborative Content Strategy', '1', 'benefits-of-collaborative-content-strategy', '<h2>Benefits of Collaborative Content Strategy</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A collaborative content strategy offers various benefits, including some significant advantages, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Improved Quality</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaboration brings together diverse ideas, experiences, and expertise to create engaging content that resonates with the target audience. Multiple parties working together ensures comprehensive coverage and a unique way for businesses to distinguish and differentiate themselves from their competitors in content creation.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Increased Reach</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaborating with other organisations can lead to an expanded reach and access to a wider range of potential customers. Strategic collaboration can introduce content to new audiences and increase the likelihood of campaign success.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Cost Savings</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaborating with other parties can be a cost-effective solution in content creation as it allows partners to share the cost and expenses of production and distribution - this, in turn, boosts the potential profit that you have available.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Strengthened Relationships</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaborative content strategies can enhance connections with partners and customers, resulting in a stronger relationship with your target audience and potential long-term business benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Increased Creativity</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>By bringing together different ideas and perspectives, you can generate more creative solutions for your content. Collaboration provides the chance to generate unique content, which may interest your intended audience by thinking creatively.</p>', '2023-05-16 14:27:23', '2023-05-16 14:27:23'),
(331, 85, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-18', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>BM was one of the first adopters of a collaborative content strategy, and its success with it has become an example for other companies that wish to follow suit. With their strategy, IBM focused on leveraging their diverse resources and making sure that all stakeholders were aligned with their goals and objectives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first step of their process involved choosing partners who could provide the best content and resources for their goals. They then created a plan that detailed each party&#39;s contribution and the distribution of the content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IBM employed a strategy and regularly evaluated its progress to pinpoint opportunities for enhancement and implement required modifications. They utilised collaboration tools such as Google Docs and Trello to streamline effective teamwork among stakeholders.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IBM&#39;s collaborative content strategy resulted in more effective content that resonated with their target audience, demonstrating the potential benefits of such a strategy for any business. This case study serves as a useful example of these advantages.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-16 14:25:07', '2023-05-16 14:25:07'),
(332, 85, 'How to Implement a Collaborative Content Strategy', '1', 'how-to-implement-a-collaborative-content-strategy', '<h2>How to Implement a Collaborative Content Strategy</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As with any content strategy, the success of your collaborative efforts will depend on careful planning and execution. Here are some tips to help you get started:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Identify Your Partners</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When seeking collaboration opportunities, it is important to identify potential partners and evaluate their ability to contribute to the overall strategy. This involves considering the resources and expertise that each organisation can bring to the table and prioritising partners with a strong presence in the relevant field.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Establish Goals and Objectives</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Establishing clear goals and objectives for collaboration with potential partners is crucial for ensuring alignment and progress towards shared outcomes - make sure you are all in agreement before starting, and you will save plenty of time down the line.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Create a Plan of Action</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Next, create a plan of action that outlines how each party will contribute to the collaboration. Establish timelines and deadlines for each task, and consider factors such as distribution methods and promotion strategies.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Monitor and Evaluate</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To ensure success in collaborative content strategy, it is important to regularly monitor progress and evaluate outcomes to identify areas for improvement and make necessary changes.</p>', '2023-05-16 14:21:12', '2023-05-16 14:21:12'),
(333, 85, 'Using The Right Tools', '1', 'using-the-right-tools', '<h2><strong>Using The Right Tools</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>While all the tips and strategies that we have outlined above all play a key role in successful collaborative working, using the right tools can also help to make collaborative working a smoother and less stressful process, ensuring that all of the members of the team are able to work together without any hiccups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the best tools to help enable collaborative working include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/trello\"><u>Trello</u></a></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Trello is among the most popular options for project management and collaboration, offering users a wide range of features to help them keep track of tasks. The visual board makes it easy to assign tasks and see the progress of projects, while reminders can be set for important deadlines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Slack</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Slack is a great tool for efficient communication between team members, allowing users to quickly send messages and files with ease. It can be used for both private and group conversations, offering a range of features such as searchable archives and reminders.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Google Docs</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Many individuals consider Google Docs to be the perfect tool for collaborative writing, allowing multiple users to work together on documents. It also offers an easy-to-use chat feature, which makes it simple to discuss ideas without having to leave the document.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/ideaflip\"><u>Ideaflip</u></a></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Another great option is Ideaflip, which allows users to easily create digital sticky notes and collaborate on ideas in real-time. Users can share notes with other members of their team and make use of the in-built brainstorming tools to generate new ideas.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/almanac\"><u>Almanac</u></a></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, Almanac is a great tool for keeping track of all the information related to your collaborative projects. It provides users with an easy-to-use dashboard where they can store photos, notes and documents, as well as easily access project calendars.</p>', '2023-05-16 14:21:46', '2023-05-16 14:21:46'),
(334, 85, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-36', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>70% of employees said digital technology improved their collaboration - by taking advantage of the range of digital tools available, it is possible to make the process of collaborative working much easier and more efficient.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-16 14:25:45', '2023-05-16 14:25:45'),
(335, 85, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-17', '<h2><strong>Final Thoughts</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>By using the right tools, you can make the process of collaborative working much easier and more efficient. However, it is important to keep in mind that the success of any collaborative project will ultimately depend on careful planning, communication and execution - and using our top tips will help you to create a successful and beneficial collaborative content strategy.</p>', '2023-05-16 14:22:52', '2023-05-16 14:22:52'),
(336, 86, 'How to Use a Content Calendar to Streamline Your Content Strategy', '1', 'how-to-use-a-content-calendar-to-streamline-your-content-strategy', '<p>If you&rsquo;ve recently started a blog or other content-based business, you already know how important it is to have a strong content strategy. But it can be hard to keep track of everything that needs to be done, especially when things start getting busy. That&rsquo;s where a content calendar comes in.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A content calendar is essentially an organised schedule of the content that you plan to write and publish in the upcoming weeks and months. It gives you an overall view of your content strategy so that you can ensure consistency and quality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are looking to get the most out of your content creation, then we have put together all you need to know about content calendars, including how to make them, what they should include, and the best tools to help you out.</p>', '2023-05-17 14:06:08', '2023-05-17 14:06:08'),
(337, 86, 'What is a Content Calendar?', '1', 'what-is-a-content-calendar', '<h2>What is a Content Calendar?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In its most basic form, a content calendar is an organised plan of when you will create and publish your content. It can be used for multiple pieces of content across various channels and platforms. This could include social media posts, blog posts, video content, and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Content calendars are a valuable<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/\"> tool</a>, and provide a central hub for all your content creation activities, ensuring that you never miss an opportunity to connect with your audience. They also allow you to plan ahead, schedule posts in advance, and keep track of what content is performing best.</p>', '2023-05-17 14:06:42', '2023-05-17 14:06:42'),
(338, 86, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-37', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>91% of marketing pros surveyed by Semrush achieved success with their content marketing in 2021 - this is a testament to the importance of having a streamlined content strategy, and a content calendar is an essential part of this.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-17 14:07:13', '2023-05-17 14:07:13'),
(339, 86, 'Why Should You Use a Content Calendar?', '1', 'why-should-you-use-a-content-calendar', '<h2>Why Should You Use a Content Calendar?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A content calendar is essential for any business looking to grow its online presence. Here are some of the key benefits of using one:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Streamlining and Organising Your Workflow</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A content calendar allows you to keep track of when tasks need to be completed, which can help streamline your workflow and make sure that everything is done in the right order. Using this method can be beneficial for time management, task focus, and ensuring proper attention is given to each stage of the content creation process.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ensuring Your Content Is Relevant and Up-To-Date</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating a content calendar can improve the timeliness and relevance of your content. Utilising tools like <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/google-trends\">Google Trends</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hubspots-blog-topic-generator\">HubSpot Blog Topic Generator</a>, and Feedly can assist in helping you with staying informed on current events and topics, allowing for the creation of timely content that connects with your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Saving Time and Money</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating a content calendar helps to ensure that you are creating the right content for the right people at the right time, which will help you to save both time and money. By taking the time to plan ahead, you avoid having to waste resources on irrelevant or outdated content and also helps you to focus your content efforts on the topics and platforms that will bring the most value.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Boost Audience Engagement</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>By planning your content in advance, you can ensure that your content is always fresh and relevant, which will help to boost audience engagement. Scheduling content to be published at key moments throughout the year can also help to remind users of your brand and keep them coming back for more.</p>', '2023-05-17 14:07:54', '2023-05-17 14:07:54'),
(340, 86, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-19', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>ABC Candles is an online retail store that sells a wide range of products. They had been struggling to increase their website traffic and were looking for ways to improve their content strategy. After a discussion as to the best courses of action, the team decided to create a content calendar to help them plan, organise and schedule their content more effectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They initiated the process by organising their content in a spreadsheet, which included the subjects they intended to address, the content format (e.g. blog posts, videos, etc.), and the deadlines for each piece. By planning ahead, they ensured that their content remained up-to-date and relevant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The team also established a system to monitor analytics in order to evaluate the performance of their content. They were then able to use this to adapt their strategy quickly and ensure maximum effectiveness for each piece of content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ABC Candles experienced a 35% increase in website traffic in just a few months, which was largely attributed to the implementation of its content calendar system. The analytics indicated that the content was connecting better with readers, resulting in improved engagement and conversions. The team at ABC Candles was ecstatic, and they continue to use their content calendar to this day to help them ensure that their content remains successful and engaging.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-17 14:09:04', '2023-05-17 14:09:04'),
(341, 86, 'How To Create A Content Calendar', '1', 'how-to-create-a-content-calendar', '<h2>How To Create A Content Calendar</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Developing a content calendar is a simple process that does not necessitate the use of intricate software or tools. To effectively plan your content creation and publication, it is recommended to use a spreadsheet or document to list out the content and corresponding dates.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Decide On A Format</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the initial tasks is to select a format for your content calendar. Various document formats, including Excel spreadsheets and Google Docs, provide the flexibility to add or remove rows and columns as necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Choose Your Columns</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>After selecting a format, the next step is to determine the information to incorporate into the content calendar. When creating content, it may be helpful to include columns for the title, due date, format, and relevant links or notes, depending on the type of content being produced and its requirements or specifications.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Set Deadlines</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The next step is to set deadlines for each piece of content. This will help you to make sure that tasks are completed in a timely manner and also allows you to plan ahead and schedule content for future dates.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Fill in the Blanks</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you can begin to fill in the blanks and create a timeline for when each piece of content should be completed. This is especially important if you are publishing content on social media, as this will help make sure that your posts go out at the right times and don&rsquo;t get lost in the noise.</p>', '2023-05-17 14:09:37', '2023-05-17 14:09:37'),
(342, 86, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-38', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Just 33% of all businesses have a content strategy in place; to ensure that you are in the majority, make sure you create a content calendar - this will help you to plan ahead, stay organised and measure success.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-17 14:10:10', '2023-05-17 14:10:10'),
(343, 86, 'Ready-Made Content Calendars', '1', 'ready-made-content-calendars', '<h2>Ready-Made Content Calendars</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are looking for a ready-made content calendar option, there are a number of <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/\">tools</a> and templates you can use to quickly get started. Some popular options include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/trello\">Trello</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Trello is a handy organisational tool that can also double as a content calendar, helping you to keep track of tasks and deadlines. You can create &lsquo;cards&rsquo; for each piece of content, set due dates and assign tasks to team members.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>ContentCal</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>ContentCal is a content calendar tool that helps you to plan, schedule and measure your content performance across multiple channels. It allows you to collaborate with team members, visualise your content pipeline, and automate social media posts with ease.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Google Sheets</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Sheets is another popular option for creating content calendars. It&rsquo;s easy to use, and you can quickly set up columns and rows for all the information you need to include.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/coschedule-marketing-suite\">CoSchedule Marketing Suite</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Another popular option is CoSchedule&rsquo;s Marketing Suite. This platform helps you to plan, schedule and analyse your content across multiple channels from one central dashboard.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/almanac\">Almanac</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Almanac is another great option to help you organise and manage your content. It makes it easy to quickly create and share plans, manage deadlines and track performance in one central location.</p>', '2023-05-17 14:10:44', '2023-05-17 14:10:44'),
(344, 86, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-18', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>By taking the time to create a content calendar, you can save yourself both time and money by ensuring that your content is always relevant, timely and effective. Whether you choose to use a ready-made tool or opt for a spreadsheet, having a plan in place will help you to keep your content strategy on track and consistently engaging for your audience.</p>', '2023-05-17 14:11:17', '2023-05-17 14:11:17'),
(345, 87, 'The Business of Storytelling: How to Build Your Copywriting Career', '1', 'the-business-of-storytelling-how-to-build-your-copywriting-career', '<p>Are you a creative writer looking for a way to make a living? Does the idea of using your writing skills to earn money sound exciting? If so, copywriting might be the perfect career for you. Copywriting is an in-demand skill that allows writers to turn their creativity into cash; it involves crafting compelling messages and stories that entice readers and make them take action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this article, we will provide information on starting a career in copywriting, ways to earn a living as a copywriter, and strategies for building a successful career over time.</p>', '2023-05-18 12:38:31', '2023-05-18 12:38:31'),
(346, 87, 'What Do We Mean By Copywriting?', '1', 'what-do-we-mean-by-copywriting', '<h2>What Do We Mean By Copywriting?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is the process of creating effective content for various marketing materials, such as website copy, product descriptions, brochures, press releases, blog posts, email campaigns, and other mediums. This involves identifying and addressing the needs and preferences of your target audience through persuasive and engaging copy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting also requires strong research skills and the ability to write clear and concise sentences that are both informative and persuasive.</p>', '2023-05-18 12:39:06', '2023-05-18 12:39:06'),
(347, 87, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-39', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>The job market for copywriters is expected to grow by 7.6% by 2026 - -this is a great time to enter this market, and with the right tools and knowledge, you can make your copywriting career a success.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-18 12:39:42', '2023-05-18 12:39:42'),
(348, 87, 'Why Start A Copywriting Business?', '1', 'why-start-a-copywriting-business', '<h2>Why Start A Copywriting Business?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is an incredibly rewarding career that can provide a great source of income. As demand for copywriters grows, so does the potential to build a successful business. There can be a number of advantages that come with building your own copywriting business, and these can include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Flexibility</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As a freelancer or business owner, you have the freedom to set your own hours, work from wherever you&rsquo;d like, and even take on projects that interest you. You can also choose the types of clients you work with and what kind of copywriting jobs you take on.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Mastery</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting involves mastering both creative and technical skills, and as you hone these abilities, you can create copy that truly stands out - an opportunity that the freedom of running your own business allows you to enjoy. You can also develop your own unique style and voice that sets you apart from other copywriters to ensure that you always have a unique selling point.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Experiences</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The role of a copywriter offers chances to acquire knowledge in diverse industries and explore new subjects. Collaborating with various clients and taking on a range of tasks can enhance your abilities and connections, which can be highly fulfilling.</p>', '2023-05-18 12:40:50', '2023-05-18 12:40:50'),
(349, 87, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-20', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>John Smith is a successful freelance copywriter with years of experience in the industry. When he first started out, he had to invest heavily in the right tools and knowledge to get his business off the ground. Knowing that SEO and digital marketing strategies were essential for success, John invested in SEO Powersuite, Grammarly, Readable, and other software solutions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He also attended conferences and networking events to ensure he was up to date on the latest trends, constantly investing in himself and his business to ensure that he could offer the best service to his clients. After a few months, John&rsquo;s copywriting business was thriving and he was able to quit his day job and pursue freelance writing full-time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>John&rsquo;s story is proof that investing in yourself, your knowledge and the right tools can help you take your copywriting career to the next level - no matter where you start from.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-18 12:41:29', '2023-05-18 12:41:29'),
(350, 87, 'What Are The Key Elements Of A Successful Copywriting Business?', '1', 'what-are-the-key-elements-of-a-successful-copywriting-business', '<h2>What Are The Key Elements Of A Successful Copywriting Business?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>So, you have made the decision to start your own copywriting business. Before you get started, there are a few key elements that need to be in place for it to be successful.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Research the Industry</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you start your career as a copywriter, it&rsquo;s important to do your research. Learn about the different types of copywriting jobs available, such as website copywriting, SEO copywriting, and social media copywriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Quality Work</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>First and foremost, your work needs to be of the highest quality. This means taking the time to research each project thoroughly and crafting compelling copy that is free of errors and captures the attention of your audience. Additionally, it&rsquo;s important to remain consistent in your style and stick to deadlines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Get Educated</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Receiving an education in copywriting, or a related field such as marketing, advertising, or communications, is a great way to set yourself up for success in the industry. There are several online courses and certification programs available that can help you hone your skills and gain a better understanding of copywriting. Additionally, attending industry events and joining professional networks can help you stay up to date on the latest trends and best practices.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Build Your Portfolio</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To stand out from the competition, it&rsquo;s important to create a portfolio of your work that showcases your writing abilities. Various forms of content can be created, such as blog posts, website copy, email campaigns, press releases, and more. It&#39;s important to cultivate a distinct style that showcases your individuality and distinguishes your work from other copywriters.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Network and Pitch</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>After creating your portfolio, network with potential employers and clients. Look for social media groups related to copywriting and reach out to companies that may need your services, and attend industry events to meet potential clients in person. It is also a good idea to stay active on job boards like Upwork or Freelancer, as they can provide work opportunities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also promote your business by creating a website or blog, using tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/elementor\">Elementor </a>or <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/wordpress\">Wordpress</a>, or by attending relevant events, or engaging in social media marketing, all of which can really help to build your brand and attract new clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You should also make it a priority to work with other professionals such as editors and designers, as this can help you create an impressive portfolio that will make your services stand out from the crowd.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Always Focus On Professionalism</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When working with clients, it&rsquo;s essential to maintain a professional attitude throughout the entire process. This includes responding promptly to emails, providing regular updates on progress, and delivering projects on time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additionally, having a clear understanding of client expectations is key to ensuring successful results. Invest in tools such as Slack and Trello to remain in contact with your clients, and guarantee the highest quality work with spellchecker tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/readable\">Readable</a>, or <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hemingway-editor\">Hemingway Editor</a> to give your copy that polished professional feel.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Learn and Grow</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It is important to stay informed on industry trends and best practices as you gain experience. Consider attending continuing education opportunities, workshops, conferences, and networking events to expand your knowledge and skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Build A Copywriters Toolkit</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To achieve success in copywriting, it is important to possess the necessary tools in your toolkit such as knowledge of SEO, keyword research, analytics, and other digital marketing strategies. The good news is that you don&#39;t have to master these right away - there are a host of tools that can help enhance and improve the quality of your copy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the best tools to consider include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/seo-powersuite\">SEO Powersuite</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This suite of SEO tools offers comprehensive optimization and progress tracking for your content in search engines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Grammarly</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Grammarly is an automated proofreading tool that helps you make sure your content is error-free and polished. SEMRush</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Grammarly is an automated proofreading tool that helps you make sure your content is error-free and polished.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/semrush\">SEMRush</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is an all-in-one digital marketing toolkit that can help you with keyword research, SEO, and more. Google Trends Part of creating great copy involves staying up-to-date with the latest trends. Google Trends can help you do just that by tracking the popularity of topics and keywords over time, ensuring that you always offer your clients the most relevant, up-to-date information and topics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>l marketing toolkit that can help you with keyword research, SEO, and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/google-trends\">Google Trends</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Part of creating great copy involves staying up-to-date with the latest trends. Google Trends can help you do just that by tracking the popularity of topics and keywords over time, ensuring that you always offer your clients the most relevant, up-to-date information and topics.</p>', '2023-05-18 12:43:22', '2023-05-18 12:43:22'),
(351, 87, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-40', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>Copywriters are responsible for more than 50% of all content on the internet - if you want to make it in this industry, you need to have the right knowledge and use the right tools. Using SEO Powersuite, Grammarly, Readable, Google Trends and other digital marketing tools can give your business a boost.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-18 12:43:55', '2023-05-18 12:43:55'),
(352, 87, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-19', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Copywriting is both an art and a science, and having the right tools in your toolkit can be the difference between success and failure. With the right knowledge, approach, and tools, however, you can build a successful copywriting career that will continue to grow for years to come. So what are you waiting for? Time to turn to the first page, and ensure that your copywriting journey is guaranteed a fairytale ending.</p>', '2023-05-18 12:46:17', '2023-05-18 12:46:17'),
(353, 88, 'Why Content Strategy Is Crucial for Your Business\'s Success', '1', 'why-content-strategy-is-crucial-for-your-businesss-success', '<p>Content strategy is considered a key element for sustained success in businesses, as it involves creating and sharing content to engage customers and achieve business objectives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Developing a structured strategy for content creation, promotion, and evaluation can guarantee that your business communicates effectively with the appropriate individuals, fosters credibility with your following, and ultimately results in business expansion. This article will explore the importance of developing a content strategy in achieving business success and provide guidance on how to develop a successful plan.</p>', '2023-05-19 12:36:17', '2023-05-19 12:36:17'),
(354, 88, 'What Is A Content Strategy?', '1', 'what-is-a-content-strategy-2', '<h2>What Is A Content Strategy?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The purpose of a content strategy is to establish a framework for producing and disseminating content that effectively reaches your intended audience, and supports your business objectives. The process includes conducting research on customer preferences, producing captivating content, and monitoring its effectiveness. Your content strategy should also specify which platforms you&#39;ll use to publish and promote your content, as well as how you will measure its success.</p>', '2023-05-19 12:36:40', '2023-05-19 12:36:40'),
(355, 88, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-21', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>As a content marketing agency, we helped an e-commerce company to create and implement a successful content strategy. The main goal of the client was to increase website traffic and generate leads through content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Firstly, we worked with our clients to identify their target audience and research what topics were trending within their industry. Utilising tools such as Google Trends, Ubersuggest and Answer The Public allowed us to gain an understanding of what content was resonating with their audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Through a comprehensive analysis of their competitors&#39; content, we were able to gain insight into what strategies were successful for them and how to replicate them for our clients. We identified topics that had the potential to reach a larger audience and generated ideas on how to make the content more engaging by including visuals and other interactive elements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once we had identified the topics and formats that were performing well, we developed a content calendar that mapped out the client&rsquo;s upcoming posts and scheduled them in advance. We also provided advice on how to optimise the content for better engagement, such as including relevant keywords, using visuals and utilising social media channels to promote the content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, we tracked the performance of the content consistently in order to gain insights into what was working and what needed improvement. This allowed us to continually refine the content strategy and ensure that our client was getting the most out of their content. As a result, website traffic increased by 30% and lead generation improved by 50% -a result our client was more than happy with!&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-19 12:37:51', '2023-05-19 12:37:51'),
(356, 88, 'What Should Be Included In My Content Strategy?', '1', 'what-should-be-included-in-my-content-strategy', '<h2>What Should Be Included In My Content Strategy?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your content strategy should have several key components, and these include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Your Audience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The first step is to define your audience and determine the types of content that will resonate with them. This will help to ensure that your content reaches the right people and has a greater chance of success.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Your Goals</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your content strategy should also include specific goals that you wish to achieve, such as increasing website traffic or generating more leads. Having clear objectives will help you measure the effectiveness of your content and make adjustments if needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Content Creation Plan</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have defined your audience and goals, it&#39;s time to create an editorial calendar. This will help keep you on track and ensure that content is created and published regularly.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Distribution Strategy</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It is important to consider the distribution strategy for your content, including the location and method of distribution; remember that different platforms have different audiences, so it&#39;s important to understand which ones are best suited for your content. Additionally, you should develop a plan for promoting your content and engaging with your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Monitoring and Adjustment</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It is important to monitor the effectiveness of your content and make modifications as necessary. This involves examining information from different sources, such as the number of views or levels of engagement using tools such as Google Analytics. By analysing data and performance, you can fine-tune your content strategy for maximum effectiveness in meeting objectives.</p>', '2023-05-19 12:40:35', '2023-05-19 12:40:35'),
(357, 88, 'Why Is Content Strategy Important?', '1', 'why-is-content-strategy-important', '<h2>Why Is Content Strategy Important?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>So, just why does content strategy even matter? Content strategy is important for a number of reasons, and these include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>It Helps With Creating Engaging Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A content strategy helps you create content that is engaging, relevant, and tailored to your target audience. This will help ensure that your message resonates with the right people and builds trust with your customers, as well as ensure that your content stands out from the competition.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>It Helps With Meeting Your Goals</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A content strategy should incorporate measurable goals to monitor content performance and guarantee that objectives are being accomplished. Through analysis of the results, it is possible to pinpoint areas of improvement as well as areas of success in your content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>It Helps To Build An Audience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Implementing a content strategy can aid in developing a loyal audience that has confidence in your brand. Content strategy is important as it aids in creating content that connects with the intended audience, and can increase website and social media traffic.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>It Helps With Generating Leads</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A content strategy can serve as a means for customers to interact with your company and gain knowledge about your offerings, potentially resulting in lead generation. This, in turn, can then lead to increased sales and business growth.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>It Increases Visibility</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Implementing a content strategy can enhance online visibility by effectively reaching the intended audience with appropriate content. For businesses aiming to expand their online presence through social media and search engine rankings, this is particularly crucial.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>It Helps With Content Optimization</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>After developing a content strategy, it is essential to optimise the content for visibility on search engines. The process involves enhancing titles, meta descriptions, and keywords to guarantee that your content is searchable on the internet, as well as optimising your content for mobile-friendliness - this can also help you reach a larger audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To help ensure content is optimised, make the most of tools such as<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/seo-powersuite\"> SEO PowerSuite</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/surfer-seo\">Surfer SEO</a> and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/semrush\">SEMRush </a>-these are designed to help analyse your current content, and ensure that you have all you need to boost results.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>It Helps With Analytics and Reporting</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Another aspect of content strategy is to regularly monitor and analyse the effectiveness of your content. Analysing content performance allows for a better understanding of successful and unsuccessful pieces, and analytics can provide valuable insights into your audience&#39;s needs and interests, helping you to create content that is tailored to them.</p>', '2023-05-19 12:41:37', '2023-05-19 12:41:37'),
(358, 88, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-41', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>84% of organisations have a content marketing strategy - this is a crucial element of success for businesses.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-19 12:42:15', '2023-05-19 12:42:15'),
(359, 88, 'How To Create Your Content Strategy', '1', 'how-to-create-your-content-strategy', '<h2>How To Create Your Content Strategy</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>After understanding the significance of content strategy, let&#39;s explore the process of creating one. A successful content strategy should include the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1.&nbsp; Define Your Goals</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Defining your goals is an important step in creating content that is focused and effective in helping you achieve those goals. Are you seeking to enhance website performance by driving more traffic, generating leads, or boosting brand recognition? Improving your understanding of your goals can help you create high-quality content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2.&nbsp; Identify Your Audience</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to effectively engage with your intended audience, it is important to have a clear understanding of who they are. Consider the interests, needs, and preferences of your audience and develop content that is customised to their liking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tools such as Google Trends can be extremely useful in helping you to determine what topics are trending and what content is resonating with your audience, while assets such as Also Asked, Uber Suggest and Answer The Public can help to tailor your content to what people are searching for.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3.&nbsp; Research Your Competitors</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Studying the content produced by competitors can provide insight into the topics and formats that are popular among their audience, and can also inspire new ideas for creating unique content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4.&nbsp; Plan Your Content Calendar</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to ensure the success of your content strategy, it is crucial to consider future planning. Creating a content calendar can assist with maintaining a consistent schedule and guide the production of future content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating a content calendar can also help you plan and ensure that your content is posted regularly and consistently - make the most of <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/coschedule-marketing-suite\">CoSchedule Marketing Suite</a> to help you keep on top of scheduling. Additionally, use tools such as Google Analytics or Hubspot to monitor your content performance and determine what content is resonating with your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>5.&nbsp; Schedule Time For Analysis</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, it is important to schedule time for analysing your content performance. This can help you understand which pieces of content are resonating with your audience and which need more work. Analysing trends and audience engagement can offer useful information for creating content that is relevant and meets the needs and interests of your audience.</p>', '2023-05-19 12:44:00', '2023-05-19 12:44:00'),
(360, 88, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-42', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>64% of the most successful B2B marketers have a documented content strategy in place - if you want to succeed, you need to join this group and make the most of your content.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-19 12:44:37', '2023-05-19 12:44:37'),
(361, 88, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-20', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Creating and implementing a content strategy can be an overwhelming process, but with the right steps in place, it can become more manageable. To ensure that you are creating successful content, it is important to focus on two key areas: research and measurement.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Essentially, you need to determine what type of content your audience is engaging with, what topics they are interested in, and how you can help them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a little planning, plenty of research, and a solid content strategy, you will have all you need to maximise your marketing efforts and boost your chances of a successful content marketing campaign.</p>', '2023-05-19 12:45:15', '2023-05-19 12:45:15'),
(362, 89, 'How to Generate Content Ideas that Engage Your Audience', '1', 'how-to-generate-content-ideas-that-engage-your-audience', '<p>Generating engaging content for your audience is essential for success in the digital age. It doesn&rsquo;t matter if you&rsquo;re a blogger, an e-commerce store owner, or a content marketer&mdash;creating content that resonates with your readers is key to driving engagement.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But coming up with ideas can be daunting. Where do you start? How do you make sure that the content you create is something that your readers will actually find interesting and engaging? If you are facing these questions, we have good news for you - we have put together all you need to know about engaging content ideas, and the<a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/\"> best </a>ways to keep your audience engaged and responsive.</p>', '2023-05-22 11:08:54', '2023-05-22 11:08:54'),
(363, 89, 'What is Audience Engagement, And Why Does It Matter?', '1', 'what-is-audience-engagement-and-why-does-it-matter', '<h2>What is Audience Engagement, And Why Does It Matter?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Audience engagement is the process of actively engaging with your readers and viewers in order to keep them interested in your content. It is key to creating a successful online presence, as it encourages readers to take part in conversations, share content with their friends and family, and purchase products or services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to creating content that engages your audience, it&#39;s important to understand what makes them tick. What topics do they find interesting? What kind of content do they like to read or watch? Knowing your audience is the foundation for creating content that resonates with them.</p>', '2023-05-22 11:09:49', '2023-05-22 11:09:49'),
(364, 89, 'Case Study', '1', 'case-study-22', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Case Study</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>When it comes to generating content ideas that engage your audience, one company that is leading the way is Adobe. In order to better understand its customer&rsquo;s needs and interests, Adobe conducted an in-depth survey of its customers in 2018 that asked them what kind of content they were looking for. The results showed that customers wanted more video tutorials, how-to guides, product reviews and interviews with experts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In response to this feedback, Adobe created a content strategy that focused on creating high-quality video tutorials and how-to guides, as well as engaging interviews with industry experts. They also re-purposed some of their existing content such as blog posts and webinars in order to make sure they were getting the most out of their material. Finally, they used analytics tools such as Adobe Analytics to track the performance of their content and make sure it was resonating with their audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Through this comprehensive strategy, Adobe was able to come up with content ideas that were engaging and relevant to their customer&rsquo;s needs, helping them to build trust and connection with their audience. This, in turn, helped them to increase their sales, grow their customer base and become one of the leading brands in the industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-22 11:10:50', '2023-05-22 11:10:50');
INSERT INTO `article_contents` (`id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `type`, `slug`, `content`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(365, 89, 'Tips For Generating Engaging Content Ideas', '1', 'tips-for-generating-engaging-content-ideas', '<h2>Tips For Generating Engaging Content Ideas</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>So, just how do you go about generating content ideas that will keep your audience engaged and interested? We have a few suggestions:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Do Your Research</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s important to understand what topics and types of content resonate with your readers. Spend some time researching your audience by looking at competitors&#39; content, reading industry blogs, and paying attention to conversations on social media. This will give you an idea of what topics your target audience is interested in.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/answer-the-public\">Answer the Public</a>, <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/ubersuggest\">Ubersuggest </a>and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/also-asked\">Also Asked</a> can be very useful here - each of these gives you an insight into the mindset of the customers you are seeking and lets you know what they are looking for, how they are thinking, and where their priorities are.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This information then allows you to create content that is tailored to the needs of your readers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n2. Look For Trends</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Keep up with the latest trends in your industry and related industries. What topics are people talking about? What content is getting lots of likes and shares? Use this information to come up with content ideas that are relevant to your audience and will keep them engaged. Tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/google-trends\">Google Trends</a> can be very useful here, as you will be able to obtain a clear overview of the key trending topics in your industry and give you a chance to get ahead of the curve and meet your audience&#39;s needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Take Advantage of Social Media</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Social media is a great way to get feedback from your readers, which can help you come up with content ideas that will resonate with them. Look for conversations in which you can join, or start one yourself by asking your followers questions about topics related to your industry or products. See what kinds of answers you get, and use this information to generate content ideas that are relevant to your audience&rsquo;s interests.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Ask Your Audience What They Want</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also use surveys or polls to ask your readers what kind of content they want to see from you. Make sure the questions are clear and easy to understand, and keep it short and sweet - no one wants to spend hours filling out a survey! Once you have the results, use them to create content that your readers will love.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Use Content Generating Tools</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are truly stuck for ideas, there are a number of tools that can help you to come up with ideas for your content. <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/hubspots-blog-topic-generator\">HubSpot&#39;s Blog Topic Generator </a>and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/portents-content-idea-generator\">Portent&rsquo;s Content Idea Generator</a> are two great examples that you can use to generate fresh, creative ideas in just a few seconds.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n6. Be Creative With Your Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to generating content ideas, don&#39;t be afraid to get creative and think outside the box. Try mixing different types of content such as videos, infographics, audio clips and long-form articles to keep your audience engaged. Experiment with interactive elements such as polls, quizzes and surveys to make your content more engaging.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n7. Repurpose Your Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Repurposing content is a great way to get the most out of your existing material and add new life to it. Take an old blog post or video and re-work it into something fresh and new, like an infographic or podcast. Not only does this save you time, but it also helps to keep your readers engaged as they are seeing something new.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n8. Analyse And Use Your Results</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the most important parts of generating content ideas is to track the performance of your content and learn from it. Use analytics tools such as Google Analytics or HubSpot to monitor which posts are performing best, and use this information to inform future content that you create.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember that when it comes to business and marketing, knowledge really is power - you need to ensure that you are always in the know when it comes to your audience&rsquo;s trends, interests and preferences, and having the analytics and data there in front of you is the key to success.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n9. Make Sure Your Content Is Original</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As technology and AI tools continue to grow and evolve, it is more important than ever to ensure that your content is original and not copied from elsewhere. Not only does this show that you have taken the time to create something unique, but it also helps to build trust with your readers. Use tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/copyscape\">Copyscape </a>to ensure that your content is not plagiarised.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n10. Create High-Quality Content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to ensuring that your content is original, you also want to make sure that it is of high quality. No matter how great your idea is, if the execution isn&rsquo;t up to scratch, then no one will want to read it. Take the time to proofread and edit your work before you post it, and consider using an online editor such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/grammarly\">Grammarly </a>to help you spot any typos or errors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You should also ensure that content is divided into headings and subheadings to make it easy to read and that these include keywords that can help your piece rank - take advantage of tools such as <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/surfer-seo\">Surfer SEO </a>and <a href=\"https://theauthorspad.com/tool/semrush\">SEMRush </a>to generate relevant keywords and maximise your SEO.</p>', '2023-05-22 11:26:11', '2023-05-22 11:26:11'),
(366, 89, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-43', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>On average, audience engagement drops if a piece has a reading time of longer than seven minutes - make sure that you keep your content concise and to the point if you want to prevent people from losing interest.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-22 11:26:44', '2023-05-22 11:26:44'),
(367, 89, 'Final Thoughts', '1', 'final-thoughts-21', '<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>By leveraging these strategies, you can easily generate content ideas that will keep your readers engaged and coming back for more. Make sure you research your audience, ask them what they want to see, employ content-generating tools and re-purpose existing material to save time, use analytics to inform future content, create original work and ensure that the quality is high. With these tips in mind, you&rsquo;ll be able to come up with great ideas for your content in no time!</p>', '2023-05-22 11:27:15', '2023-05-22 11:27:15'),
(368, 89, 'Key Fact', '1', 'key-fact-44', '<div class=\"simplebox align-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"simplebox-title\">Key Fact</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"simplebox-content\">\r\n<p>73% of audience members admit that they tend to merely skim articles rather than reading them in depth - this means that you need to ensure that your content is clear, well-structured, and relevant if you want a chance of keeping their attention.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2023-05-22 11:27:42', '2023-05-22 11:27:42');

