(936, 0, 'White Noise', 'white-noise', '', '20', 'uploads/event/63c7f576439ea23-01-18-01-34-46.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'Worldwide', '2022-12-30', '', '2022-12-30', '', 'n/a', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, '', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-18 13:34:46'),
(937, 0, 'Martin Luther King Day', 'martin-luther-king-day', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c7f5e46c41223-01-18-01-36-36.webp', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'US', '2023-01-16', '', '2023-01-16', '', 'Martin Luther King Day, or Martin Luther King Jr. Day, is observed on the third Monday of January. It is also known as Martin Luther King’s Birthday. It is a federal holiday and a day off - most schools and businesses are closed. Martin Luther King Day is held in honor of Martin Luther King Jr., the famous civil rights leader.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, '', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-18 13:36:36'),
(938, 0, 'Presidents Day', 'presidents-day', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c7f62f7bc3623-01-18-01-37-51.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'US', '2023-02-20', '', '2023-02-20', '', 'Presidents\' Day, or, officially, Washington’s Birthday, is an American Federal Holiday that is celebrated yearly on the third Monday of February. Originally a day to celebrate George Washington and Abraham Lincoln, it is now meant to honor all U.S. Presidents, past and present, although several states still have individual holidays honoring the birthdays of Washington, Lincoln and other presidents.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, '', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-18 13:37:51'),
(939, 0, 'Mardi Gras', 'mardi-gras', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c7f69d4f54923-01-18-01-39-41.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'US', '2023-02-21', '', '2023-02-21', '', 'Mardi Gras, also known as Carnival, Fat Tuesday or Shrove Tuesday, is a celebration that takes place on the day before Ash Wednesday. Because of its grand parades and celebrations, it is a holiday in some places in America, and businesses and schools are closed for the day. In other states, it is a normal working day.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, '', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-18 13:39:41'),
(940, 0, 'Ash Wednesday', 'ash-wednesday', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c7f7128a6e023-01-18-01-41-38.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'US', '2023-02-22', '', '2023-02-22', '', 'Ash Wednesday is observed 46 days before Easter Sunday, and it signals the beginning of the forty days of Lent period. Also known as Day of Ashes, Catholics and Christians celebrate this day by focusing on prayer and penance. It is not a public holiday, and businesses run as usual.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, '', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-18 13:41:38'),
(941, 0, 'April Fools Day', 'april-fools-day', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c7fa71d6ccf23-01-18-01-56-01.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'US', '2023-04-01', '', '2023-04-01', '', 'A tradition that is celebrated in several countries, the origins of April Fool’s Day remain mysterious until today, and it is unlikely that we will ever know its true history. However, there are a few theories about where this day comes from:', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, '', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-18 13:56:01'),
(942, 0, 'Memorial Day', 'memorial-day', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c7fb0c6133b23-01-18-01-58-36.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'US', '2023-05-29', '', '2023-05-29', '', 'Memorial Day is observed in America on the last Monday of May, and it is a day to commemorate and remember the men and women who lost their lives while in service for the US military. It is a federal holiday, and as such, businesses and schools are closed, and most people have the day off work.It was officially became a federal holiday in 1971. Traditionally, people will visit cemeteries and memorials for American soldiers, and there are several parades around the country.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, '', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-18 13:58:36'),
(943, 0, 'Columbus Day', 'columbus-day', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8dbdbc14db23-01-19-05-57-47.webp', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'US', '2023-11-09', '', '2023-11-09', '', 'Columbus Day takes place on the second Monday of October. It is a federal holiday, so most banks and government offices are closed. Not all schools and post offices are closed for the day, so it is best to check beforehand. Some states do not observe the holiday, therefore, in those states, it is not a day off and many shops and businesses remain open. In most of those cities, the day is known as National Indigenous Peoples Day.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 05:57:47'),
(944, 0, 'Veteran\'s Day', 'veterans-day', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8dc1c467f123-01-19-05-58-52.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'US', '2023-11-11', '', '2023-11-21', '', 'Veterans Day is observed annually on November 11. If it falls on Saturday, the Friday before may be used for the holiday instead. If it occurs on a Sunday, then Monday may be used. It is a federal holiday, so most schools and businesses are closed. However, state and local governments, schools, and businesses are not required to close. Check locally.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 05:58:52'),
(945, 0, 'Patriot Day', 'patriot-day', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8dc6f5d1c423-01-19-06-00-15.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'US', '2023-09-11', '', '2023-09-11', '', 'Patriot Day is held on September 11 each year. Owing to its significance, many simply refer to Patriot Day by its date: September 11, or 9/11. It is an annual observance, but not a national holiday. Schools and businesses are open, however, it is common for commemorative ceremonies to take place. It’s important to note that Patriot Day is not the same as Patriots’ or Patriots Day, which commemorates the first battles of the American Revolutionary War.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:00:15'),
(946, 0, 'The Platinum Jubilee', 'the-platinum-jubilee', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8dcae17a7d23-01-19-06-01-18.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'UK', '2023-06-03', '', '2023-06-03', '', 'The Platinum Jubilee bank holiday is a weekend celebration from June 2 to June 5, 2022. The weekend is part of Queen Elizabeth\'s Platinum Jubilee celebrations that are taking place throughout the United Kingdom, the Realms, and the Commonwealth.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:01:18'),
(947, 0, 'Rio Carnival', 'rio-carnival', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8dd4306e5923-01-19-06-03-47.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'BR', '2023-02-17', '', '2023-02-25', '', 'The Carnival in Rio de Janeiro is a festival held every year before Lent; it is considered the biggest carnival in the world, with two million people per day on the streets. The first Carnival festival in Rio occurred in 1723.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:03:47'),
(948, 0, 'Floriade', 'floriade', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8ddf8c95db23-01-19-06-06-48.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'NL', '2023-09-16', '', '2023-10-15', '', 'Floriade is an international exhibition and garden festival, held every 10 years in the Netherlands. All have been World Horticultural Expositions and listed as an A1 category exhibition by the International Association of Horticultural Producers and hence recognised by the Bureau International des Expositions.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:06:48'),
(949, 0, 'Matariki', 'matariki', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8de443128023-01-19-06-08-04.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'NZ', '2023-07-14', '', '2023-07-14', '', 'In Māori culture, Matariki is the name of the Pleiades star cluster and the celebration of its first rising in late June or early July. This marks the beginning of the new year in the Māori lunar calendar. Matariki was first celebrated as an official public holiday in New Zealand on 24 June 2022.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:08:04'),
(950, 0, 'Oktoberfest', 'oktoberfest', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8de82ca25323-01-19-06-09-06.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'Munich', 'GE', '2023-09-16', '12:00', '2023-10-03', '22:30', 'The Oktoberfest is the world\'s largest Volksfest, featuring a beer festival and a travelling carnival. It is held annually in Munich, Bavaria, Germany.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:09:06'),
(951, 0, 'Nigerian General Election', 'nigerian-general-election', '', '16', 'uploads/event/63c8deba9b81a23-01-19-06-10-02.png', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'NG', '2023-02-25', '', '2023-02-25', '', 'The 2023 Nigerian elections will be held, in large part, on 25 February and 11 March 2023. The President and Vice President will be elected on 25 February, with incumbent President Muhammadu Buhari ineligible to run, being term-limited.[1] Additionally, there will also be elections on the same day for the Senate and the House of Representatives. On 11 March, twenty-eight gubernatorial elections will be held alongside elections to state houses of assembly in all 36 states.[1] Two additional gubernatorial elections will be held later in the year alongside potential rerun elections for regularly scheduled elections annulled from earlier in the year.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, '', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:10:02'),
(952, 0, 'Coronation of Charles III and Camilla', 'coronation-of-charles-iii-and-camilla', '', '16', 'uploads/event/63c8def5173a623-01-19-06-11-01.webp', 'Westminster Abbey', NULL, NULL, '', 'London', 'UK', '2023-05-06', '', '2023-05-06', '', 'The coronation of Charles III and his wife, Camilla, as king and queen of the United Kingdom and the other Commonwealth realms is set to take place on Saturday, 6 May 2023 at Westminster Abbey. It is meant to be the \"symbolic high point\" of his accession.[1] King Charles III acceded to the throne on 8 September 2022, upon the death of his mother, Queen Elizabeth II. The coronation will be a state occasion funded by the British government. It is expected to be shorter, more inclusive of other faiths and communities, and less expensive than previous coronations.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:11:01'),
(953, 0, 'Eurovision Song Contest 2023', 'eurovision-song-contest-2023', '', '20', 'uploads/event/63c8df2f583ee23-01-19-06-11-59.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'Liverpool', 'UK', '2023-05-13', '', '2023-05-13', '', 'The Eurovision Song Contest, sometimes abbreviated to ESC and often known simply as Eurovision, is an international songwriting competition organised annually by the European Broadcasting Union, featuring participants representing primarily European countries.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:11:59'),
(954, 0, 'Turkish General Election', 'turkish-general-election', '', '16', 'uploads/event/63c8df8ad215223-01-19-06-13-30.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'TR', '2023-06-18', '', '2023-06-18', '', 'The 2023 Turkish general election will be held on 18 June 2023.[1] Presidential elections are held to elect the President of Turkey using a two-round system. Simultaneously, parliamentary elections are held to elect 600 Members of Parliament to the Grand National Assembly of Turkey.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:13:30'),
(955, 0, 'Guatemalan general election', 'guatemalan-general-election', '', '16', 'uploads/event/63c8dfc48489823-01-19-06-14-28.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'GT', '2023-06-25', '', '2023-06-25', '', 'General elections will be held in Guatemala in 25 June 2023 to elect the President and Congress, with a second round of the presidential elections to be held in 20 August if no candidate wins a majority in the first round.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:14:28'),
(956, 0, 'Australia Day', 'australia-day', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8e0097be3923-01-19-06-15-37.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'AU', '2023-01-26', '', '2023-01-26', '', 'Australia Day is on January 26 and commemorates the establishment of the first European settlement at Port Jackson, now part of Sydney, in 1788.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:15:37'),
(957, 0, 'Royal Hobart Regatta', 'royal-hobart-regatta', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8e0483f18123-01-19-06-16-40.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'AU', '2023-02-13', '', '2023-02-13', '', 'Royal Hobart Regatta is a public holiday in Tasmania, where it is a day off for the general population, and schools and most businesses are closed. Sideshows, rides, and rowing competitions are what can be expected for the crowds who flock to the Royal Hobart Regatta in Australia. Held on the second Monday of February, the regatta is consists of aquatic competitions and is one of Tasmania’s oldest sporting events.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:16:40'),
(958, 0, 'Adelaide Cup', 'adelaide-cup', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8e0837ef2b23-01-19-06-17-39.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'AU', '2023-03-13', '', '2023-03-13', '', 'Adelaide Cup is a state holiday in South Australia that falls on the second Monday of March. This horse racing event has been the heart of South Australia’s sporting and social life since it was first run in 1864.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:17:39'),
(959, 0, 'Canberra Day', 'canberra-day', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8e0c635bff23-01-19-06-18-46.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'AU', '2023-03-13', '', '2023-03-13', '', 'Canberra Day is a public holiday in the Australian Capital Territory (ACT) on the second Monday of March each year. It commemorates Canberra’s official founding in 1913 and highlights a major festival in the territory.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:18:46'),
(960, 0, 'National Close the Gap Day', 'national-close-the-gap-day', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8e100d277b23-01-19-06-19-44.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'AU', '2023-03-16', '', '2023-03-16', '', 'National Close the Gap Day (NCTGD) is an annual awareness event that aims to close the health and life expectancy gap between the indigenous and the non-indigenous communities in Australia.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:19:44'),
(961, 0, 'Harmony Day', 'harmony-day', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8e13f0b4ad23-01-19-06-20-47.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'AU', '2023-03-21', '', '2023-03-21', '', 'March 21 is Australia’s Harmony Day, which celebrates the country’s cultural diversity. It coincides with the United Nations’ International Day for the Elimination of Racial Discrimination.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:20:47'),
(962, 0, 'March Equinox', 'march-equinox', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8e183cbdd823-01-19-06-21-55.png', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'AU', '2023-03-21', '', '2023-03-21', '', 'There are two equinoxes every year: one in March and one in September. In March, the Sun crosses the equator from south to north.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, 'annual', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:21:55'),
(963, 0, 'Palm Sunday', 'palm-sunday', '', '18', 'uploads/event/63c8e1b6edb5123-01-19-06-22-46.jpeg', 'n/a', NULL, NULL, '', 'n/a', 'AU', '2023-04-02', '', '2023-04-02', '', 'Many Christians living in Australia remember Jesus’ triumphal entry into Jerusalem on Palm Sunday, which marks the beginning of Holy Week. This day is also on the Sunday before Easter Sunday.', 'n/a', '', '', 0.00, '', NULL, 1, 7, '2023-01-17 13:06:55', '2023-01-19 06:22:46'),
